column42: Description
Starc to Guptill, no run,full, fast, outside off. No swing. Left alone
Starc to Guptill, FOUR,smack. Short of a length. Width. No Swing. Guptill stands tall and spanks it in front of point. Off the front foot
Starc to Guptill, 1 run,fuller, but still gives him width, driven squarer this time, but third man keeps them down to one
Starc to Mitchell, no run,full and straight, punched down the ground, but straight to mid-on

Starc to Mitchell, 3 runs,on a length, on the pads, flicked away to deep square leg. Looks like two but Hazlewood backhand-flicks it while diving, but there is no one there to relay it. They cash in, and take the third
Starc to Guptill, 1 run,on a length, angling away, runs it down to third man for one
Hazlewood to Guptill, no run,just short of a length, no room, angling in, pushed to leg
Hazlewood to Guptill, no run,again no room. Slight angle back in, headed for top of off. Punched to mid-off
Hazlewood to Guptill, no run,tucked away off the hip but straight to midwicket. Hazlewood is bowling the no-swing line. Taking Guptill's arms away from him by cramping him up
Hazlewood to Guptill, no run,just the slight width, Guptill manages to punch it with an open face, but can't beat the diving short cover
Hazlewood to Guptill, FOUR,shorter this time with the fine leg really square. The line is on the leg stump but the height is not high enough, and he plays the swivel-pull fine of that fine leg
Hazlewood to Guptill, no run,back to aiming for top of off. Punched to short cover again
Maxwell to Mitchell, SIX,Mitchell shows Pakistan what you need to do to the fifth bowler. Take him down. Lofts the first ball back over his head for six
Maxwell to Mitchell, 1 run,fired into the pads, worked away around the corner for a single

Maxwell to Guptill, no run,is that dropped?. Some turn from just short of a length, and yes Maxwell has got a bottom edge, which Wade can't collect. I wouldn't call it a drop because this is low and a healthy deflection
Maxwell to Guptill, 1 run,worked into the leg side for one
Maxwell to Mitchell, 1 run,no room, angling in, another single to leg
Maxwell to Guptill, 1 leg bye,fired into the pads for a leg-bye. He has closed out well after that early six
Hazlewood to Guptill, FOUR,short of a length, not much room, but Guptill has managed to punch this between point and cover-point. Excellent timing and placement
Hazlewood to Guptill, 1 run,into the pads, worked away to deep square leg for one
Hazlewood to Mitchell, no run,driven on the up, times it nicely, but hits it straight to extra cover
Hazlewood to Mitchell, no run,another good-looking stroke with a crunchy sound, but he has punched this straight to extra cover again

Hazlewood to Mitchell, OUT,slower ball, and it has still managed to carry to the keeper. Looks like a legcutter, could even be a knuckle ball, but it has moved just enough off the straight to take the edge from a similar punch from Mitchell. Wade dives in front to take it clean. It is a legcutter, replays confirm
Hazlewood to Williamson, no run,punched off the back foot, but can't get it past point
Cummins to Guptill, no run,short of a length, slight extra bounce, Guptill's reaction suggests it might have stopped a touch. Played to cover
Cummins to Guptill, no run,again hitting the higher part of the bat off just short of a length. No single even
Cummins to Guptill, no run,short of a length, slightly slow off the surface, defended to leg. It is standing up a little bit if you bash that hard length
Cummins to Guptill, 1 run,slower ball, short of a length, a touch down leg, helped away for a single
Cummins to Williamson, 1 run,stands up a little again, Williamson on his toes to work this to square leg for one. Staying short of a length
Cummins to Guptill, no run,short of a length, not much room, Guptill pushes at it, gets an edge to point
Hazlewood to Williamson, no run,on a length, holds its line a touch, defended to cover
Hazlewood to Williamson, no run,short of a length, wicket to wicket, slow off the surface and extra bounce. Williamson plays it back and looks at the surface
Hazlewood to Williamson, no run,gets some width but because of the slow pace off the pitch, struggles to place it. Punches it straight to mid-off, who is slightly wide
Hazlewood to Williamson, no run,on a length, top of off, Williamson defends to cover. Williamson 1 off 6 inside the Powerplay
Hazlewood to Williamson, no run,tries to make room but Hazlewood stays around off and just short of a length. It is not looking easy to time the ball the way it is coming off the surface

Hazlewood to Williamson, 2 runs,Williamson takes a risk, pulling from down to up even though this is not really a half-tracker. Doesn't time it, but it lands wide of deep square leg. breaks the maiden
Maxwell to Guptill, 1 run,full, on the toes, single to long-on
Maxwell to Williamson, 1 run,on a length, outside off, pushed to long-on for one
Maxwell to Guptill, no run,on a length, instead of turning it goes with the angle, defended back to him
Maxwell to Guptill, 1 run,slight width, driven with an open face, gets a single to deep cover
Maxwell to Williamson, 1 run,presses forward, sees flat trajectory, goes back, punches this to long-on
Maxwell to Guptill, 1 run,fuller, wicket to wicket, driven to long-on for one
Zampa to Guptill, 1 run,full, on off, driven to long-off for one
Zampa to Williamson, 1 run,short of a length, Williamson goes back to cut it for one
Zampa to Guptill, no run,on a length, can't drive, can't punch. Pushed to cover. Perfect length
Zampa to Guptill, no run,flatter, quicker, shorter, but punched straight to short cover again
Zampa to Guptill, 1 run,slightly slower, slightly fuller, turns a little, punched to deep cover
Zampa to Williamson, no run,half-volley, but driven right back to Zampa. Twenty-nine balls without a boundary now
Marsh to Guptill, 1 run,on a length, outside off, driven on the up, single to long-off
Marsh to Williamson, 1 run,short of a length, slow off the surface, punched down to long-off for one
Marsh to Guptill, 1 run,gets the length to pull, but gets just the single to deep midwicket

Marsh to Williamson, FOUR,finally a boundary. Williamson has had to manufacture it. Jumps out of the crease, and even though the ball is short, he manages to drive it over extra cover for four. First boundary in 33 balls

Marsh to Williamson, FOUR,muscled it. A filthy little short ball hoping it goes to deep midwicket for a single, but Williamson has throw in all his power behind it and placed it straight of deep midwicket
Marsh to Williamson, no run,he is down the wicket again, but Marsh does him in with a slower bouncer that hits him in the grille
Zampa to Guptill, 1 run,skiddy shortish ball, pulled for a single
Zampa to Williamson, 1 run,goes back to work this legbreak with soft hands into the leg side, but can't take on the second
Zampa to Guptill, 1 run,short of a length, on off, punched to long-off for one
Zampa to Williamson, 1 run,fuller, outside off, driven with an open face to deep cover
Zampa to Guptill, 1 run,on a length, slight turn, punched to deep cover
Zampa to Williamson, 1 run,down the wicket, ends up yorking himself up, gets a single to long-off
Starc to Williamson, 1 run,round the wicket, 141kph/87mph on the stumps and clipped through mid-on
Starc to Guptill, 1 run,pitched up and driven coming forward, just a single extra cover
Starc to Williamson, 2 runs,fired in full, doesn't quite nail the yorker and Williamson chips it up over cover wide of long-off for a couple

Starc to Williamson, FOUR,dropped, and it bounces for four! Williamson shovels a full toss towards fine leg, one hand off the bat, and Hazlewood seems to have it covered... only for the ball burst through the hands and then pop over his shoulder and bobble over the rope!
Starc to Williamson, FOUR,crunched down the ground, Williamson nails this coming forward and rifles four past the man back at long-off

Starc to Williamson, (no ball) FOUR,high full toss, 147kph and somehow Williamson has hoicked it for four! It'd a no-ball and a free hit, as well as the boundary, which he managed to swing away between long-on and deep midwicket

Starc to Williamson, 2 runs,full and wide, punched square and it takes a flying, sliding effort from Marcus Stoinis on the rope to prevent a fourth consecutive boundary. Is that lift-off for NZ, 19 off the over?

Zampa to Guptill, OUT,slogged down the throat of deep midwicket! Stoinis steadies himself under the catch, and it's Guptill who winces now. Lobbed up straight and he went for the big hit but never quite got hold of his slog-sweep. Guptill was the man to take Zampa down, but he's taken himself out instead
Zampa to Williamson, no run,tossed up on off and tapped away
Zampa to Williamson, 1 run,flighted, Williamson is forward and whips it on the full through midwicket
Zampa to Phillips, 1 run,pushed through, possibly the googly and Phillips works it behind square on the leg side
Zampa to Williamson, 2 runs,dragged down slightly and Williamson pulls into a gap on the leg side
Zampa to Williamson, 1 run,teasing, 92kph/57mph outside off, reaches for it and opens the face on a single

Maxwell to Williamson, 1 leg bye,short of a length and Williamson pulls and misses, hit on the back thigh... Maxwell was very interested in lbw, and Finch thinks about it all the way until the timer runs down. Think it probably pitched outside leg
Maxwell to Phillips, 1 run,floated up straight, worked through midwickert
Maxwell to Williamson, SIX,pongo from Kane! Bottom hand off the bat again, but he's nailed over deep midwicket... not a typical Williamson shot, but he gets it well over the rope for an 80m six

Maxwell to Williamson, SIX,slog-swept serenely into the stands! Williamson hits the gas and raises a 32-ball fifty, the captain stepping up. NZ doing a decent job of dismantling Australia's "fifth" bowler here
Maxwell to Williamson, 1 bye,full toss, seems to dip late and Williamson and Wade both miss it
Maxwell to Phillips, 1 run,darted on off from round the wicket and he chops through backward point
Cummins to Phillips, no run,over the wicket, 142kph/88mph on off stump, prodded to mid-off
Cummins to Phillips, no run,pace off this time, tapped towards point
Cummins to Phillips, 1 run,bit of width, another cutter from Cummins and Phillips ticks over with a glide behind square
Cummins to Williamson, 1 run,back of a length, 139kph and Williamson is up on his toes to punch through point
Cummins to Phillips, 1 leg bye,short ball, pace off again and Phillips it nowhere near it as he throws the bat at a pull, takes a blow on the shoulder and Williamson calls him through
Cummins to Williamson, 2 runs,mistimed over cover, a back-foot punch to another pace-off delivery, Maxwell goes scampering across from mid-off but won't get there
Zampa to Phillips, SIX,Phillips screwdriver! Drilled down the ground! He's the sixiest hitter in this NZ line-up and Phillips has planted his flag, lining up Zampa for a straight thwack

Zampa to Phillips, no run,flighted legbreak and he pokes at this tentatively... Wade and Zampa go up but Phillips and Marais Erasmus are both unmoved. No review from Finch, UltraEdge later confirms any sound was bat hitting pad
Zampa to Phillips, 1 run,tossed up on off, shuffles across and tucks into the leg side
Zampa to Williamson, 1 run,floated on on the stumps and nurdled towards midwicket
Zampa to Phillips, FOUR,chipped over cover, picks his spot! Looped up and he gets forward, keeps the head still, and lofts it towards the boundary
Zampa to Phillips, no run,pushed through on the stumps with plenty of overspin, patted down from the crease
Starc to Williamson, FOUR,slashes an outside edge wide of the keeper! Pitched up in the channel from over the wicket, goes hard and it squirts fine of short third for a boundary
Starc to Williamson, FOUR,spiralling leading edge, one bounce to the rope! Williamson rides his luck again, knows third isn't back and slices it up and over for four more!

Starc to Williamson, SIX,cutter on the pads, skelped all the way over deep backward square leg! Williamson is causing a conflagration in the Ring of Fire, just strolls across his stumps, picks up Starc and deposits him into the stands
Starc to Williamson, no run,goes round the wicket, flung full and wide and Williamson hasn't spotted this coming, can't get near it backing away
Starc to Williamson, FOUR,hammered! Pitched full at 144kph/90mph and Williamson slams it up and over point, opens the face at the last moment, and gets it well behind the sweeper

Starc to Williamson, FOUR,touch this time, pace off from Starc, but Williamson unfurls the trademark back-foot glide to third! Placed between two men on the edge of the circle... that's his fifth boundary of the over! Starc has given up 22!
Cummins to Phillips, 1 wide,pace off, wide of the stumps... too wide
Cummins to Phillips, 1 run,short into the pitch, Phillips swings it away through midwicket

Cummins to Williamson, 1 run,dug in and Williamson mistimes a swat back down the ground, Cummins gets a hand on it but they scamper one - can even think about two, as the bowler gives chase, but elect not to
Cummins to Phillips, 1 run,tucked through backward square leg
Cummins to Williamson, 1 run,well bowled by Cummins, pace off wide of the stumps and Williamson can only drag it for one
Cummins to Phillips, 1 run,short ball, another cutter and Phillips struggles for timing on the pull
Cummins to Williamson, 2 runs,pace off to finish and Williamson manages to squeeze this into a gap behind square on the leg side
Hazlewood to Phillips, no run,wow, that would have been something... length outside off and Phillips attempts to reverse-swipe it over third. Doesn't connect

Hazlewood to Phillips, OUT,heaved leg side...  but picks out deep midwicket! Hazlewood keeps a lid on it with a knuckle ball on a length, Phillips is unable to manufacture the power and Maxwell pouches it safely running around
Hazlewood to Williamson, FOUR,pace off, but flipped over short fine leg! Williamson is performing miracles in the desert for NZ. Ambles across and scoops it for four
Hazlewood to Williamson, no run,length in the channel, 123kph/77mh and he swings and misses this time

Hazlewood to Williamson, OUT,comes down, tries to hit him on to the bleachers - but finds long-off! There'll be no hundred for Williamson, but it's still the joint-highest score in a T20 World Cup final. Another variation from Hazlewood, legcutter out the side of the hand, and for once Williamson's timing failed him
Hazlewood to Neesham, 1 run,back of a length on the body and Neesham tucks it behinds square for one
Cummins to Neesham, 1 run,pitched up from over the wicket, driven through the covers for one
Cummins to Seifert, 1 run,back of a length with pace off, Seifert slaps it through point
Cummins to Neesham, SIX,Neesh-slammed! Pounded over the sight screen! Waits for the slower ball to sit up and heaves his forearms through a baseball smash down the ground
Cummins to Neesham, 1 run,dug in, even slower and he has to wait for it, so long that he ends up swatting it aerially into the vacant midwicket area for one
Cummins to Seifert, 1 run,in the pitch outside off, Seifert swings hard, cuts for one
Cummins to Neesham, 1 wide,cutter into the pitch again but this loops away wide of the left-hander

Cummins to Neesham, 2 runs,dragged leg side, they'll look to come back for two... has Neesham made his ground? Wade was confident, but the bat was just grounded over the line! Neesh survives, and it's another precious run to the total
Starc to Seifert, FOUR,misses the yorker, skimmed off the pads, Seifert sits back and breaks the wrists for a boundary through backward square
Starc to Seifert, no run,fires this down wide of off at 142kph/88mph, swing and a miss, there's a fumble from Wade but Neesham declines the opportunity
Starc to Seifert, 1 run,flung full and sliced down to third
Starc to Neesham, no run,pitched up wide of the stumps, 140kph/87mph in the slot... but Neesham sets himself and carves out a big slice of fresh air. He thinks that should have gone the journey

Starc to Neesham, 2 wides,hurled down the leg side, just misses the pads as Neesham swings across the line. This time Seifert scampers down as Wade throws at the striker's stumps from a horizontal position
Starc to Seifert, 1 run,pitched up and whipped through the leg side for one more
Starc to Neesham, 2 runs,full outside off at 143kph/89mph, Neesham bashes it down the ground towards long-off... Seifert is quick, Starc has to try to relay to the keeper's end but they'll get two
Boult to Warner, no run,oh he doesn't even try first ball. Goes into the pitch, outside off, and is cut to point
Boult to Warner, no run,on a length, angling in, hits the inner half of the bat
Boult to Warner, 1 run,short of a length, slight width, he runs it down to third man. Slight swing there
Boult to Finch, no run,slight swing again, not much, driven to mid-off
Boult to Finch, no run,short, quick, good carry, Finch looks to pull and is beaten. He is lucky he has not managed any touch because this quite wide outside off

Boult to Finch, no run,huge shout for lbw. Not given. They won't review it. Oh it looks close, though. Finch is down the wicket to this inswinger and is beaten comprehensively. A long way for the ball to go, and perhaps swinging enough to miss leg. It is hitting leg on replays but Finch is more than 3m down the wicket so the not-out call would have stayed on review
Southee to Warner, no run,short of a length, sticks into the surface, pulled uppishly to mid-on
Southee to Warner, FOUR,gets length, no swing, and there is width to free his arms. Clears extra cover with ease
Southee to Warner, FOUR,width again. This is not short enough to cut, but Warner creates his length by going deep and whips his wrists through the shot to go over point with the cut
Southee to Warner, no run,fuller, straighter, flicked back to Southee
Southee to Warner, 1 run,tucked away off the hip for one
Southee to Finch, 1 run,on a length, pretty straight, runs off the inside edge for a single
Boult to Finch, no run,short of a length, wide, sticky off the surface, fails to time the cut
Boult to Finch, FOUR,Finch gets away. Charges at Bould, takes this on the half-volley, and it doesn't matter it is a knuckle ball because he has got right to its pitch. Lofts this over mid-off

Boult to Finch, OUT,lovely catch by Mitchell. Boult bounces him after the charge last ball, gets a top edge but this is headed more towards deep midwicket than deep square where the fielder is. Mitchell makes all the ground to his left, and takes the catch sliding
Boult to Warner, no run,on a length, wicket to wicket, defended back to him
Boult to Warner, no run,short of a length, slowe off the surface, short-armed to mid-on
Boult to Warner, no run,short of a length, no room, punched straight to point
Milne to Marsh, SIX,and he provides pace. Marsh is facing his first ball of the final, but he loves him a length ball on the pads. Plays the pick-up over square leg for a massive six
Milne to Marsh, FOUR,short of a length, outside off, third man wide, and he opens the face to beat the man. Pace on, and Marsh is enjoying it
Milne to Marsh, FOUR,gives him pace again with no movement. He goes back to pull this in front of square. Along the ground this time. Deep square has no chance
Milne to Marsh, 1 run,driven on the up, but straight to mid-off
Milne to Warner, no run,short of a length, no room, punched to cover-point
Milne to Warner, no run,short of a length, wicket to wicket, Warner makes room and punches but straight to point
Southee to Marsh, 1 run,short of a length, into the pads, worked away for one
Southee to Warner, 1 run,looks to pull, the ball hardly arrives, and he gets a bottom edge for a single
Southee to Marsh, no run,short of a length, wicket to wicket, defended
Southee to Marsh, 1 run,tucked away to leg for a single
Southee to Warner, SIX,oh he is waiting for the slower ball now, and short-arms this over midwicket for a six. Too predictable there
Southee to Warner, 1 run,opens the face for a single
Milne to Warner, 1 leg bye,and now Milne is rolling his fingers on it. Beats the pull, goes for a leg-bye
Milne to Marsh, 1 leg bye,tucked to leg for another single
Milne to Warner, no run,makes room, but Milne is straight at him, and draws a dot
Milne to Warner, no run,on pace but proper bouncer, head high, drawing a leave from Warner
Milne to Warner, 1 run,slower ball, short of a length, on leg stump, Warner still manages to get a single past point
Milne to Marsh, no run,on a length, 143ks, not much room, Defended. Good comeback from Milne
Sodhi to Warner, 1 run,on a length, turning in, Warner pushes this on the walks, takes a single to long-on
Sodhi to Marsh, 1 run,on a length, no turn, Marsh goes back to punch this down to long-on for one
Sodhi to Warner, 2 runs,slightly short, pulled wide of long-on for two
Sodhi to Warner, 1 run,slow in the air, short of a length, punched to long-on for one
Sodhi to Marsh, 1 run,full, outside off, driven with an open face, but straight to deep cover
Sodhi to Warner, 1 run,stays on the back foot to punch this legbreak to deep midwicket for one
Santner to Warner, 1 run,Warner skips out of his crease, Santner goes wide, Warner recovers enough to cut this to deep cover
Santner to Marsh, SIX,what a swing. Santner bowls a tight line to cramp him up, but Marsh opens up the front leg and plays the big sweep over square leg. Another big six
Santner to Marsh, 1 run,fired into the pads, worked away for a single to deep square leg
Santner to Warner, 1 run,Warner stays back to work this length ball to deep midwicket for one
Santner to Marsh, no run,good comeback from Santner. A bit of body and revs into this. Gets it to dip on him, and then turn past his drive
Santner to Marsh, 1 run,slower in the air, middle and leg, driven down to long-on for a single
Sodhi to Marsh, 1 run,Marsh goes back to punch this length-ball legbreak to deep cover
Sodhi to Warner, FOUR,slider, going across, but a touch short, and Warner has absolutely flat-batted to drag this from wide outside off and hit it straight of long-on
Sodhi to Warner, 2 runs,reverse-sweeps this full ball for a couple to deep point. Takes the second on the throw as deep cover comes around
Sodhi to Warner, no run,down the wicket, Sodhi does well, shortens the length, slows the pace down, goes down leg, and Warner is lucky to get some body on it and save himself from getting stumped
Sodhi to Warner, FOUR,Sodhi is looking to bowl into the pitch but goes a touch too short, and Warner again flat-bats a pull, this time through square leg, for four more
Sodhi to Warner, SIX,too full this time. Right under his eyes. Warner lofts it right back over his head. Into the sight screen it goes. Australia racing away here
Santner to Marsh, 1 run,short of a length, wide, cut away in front of square for one
Santner to Warner, 2 runs,shapes up for the big slog sweep, but the late dip on it makes him keep this down. Warner still gets a couple to deep midwicket
Santner to Warner, 1 run,quicker, on a length, Warner looks to drop and run two, but Santner is quick at chasing it, and they settle for one
Santner to Marsh, no run,lovely bowling. Slows it right down, tosses it high, draws a drive and then beats it with the turn away
Santner to Marsh, no run,pushed on the up, but straight to extra cover
Santner to Marsh, 1 run,slow off the surface even though there is some width on offer. Concedes just the single to deep cover
Neesham to Marsh, SIX,short on the hip and swatted all the way over fine leg! Skiddy length but Marsh latches on to it immediately and crumps it dismissively for six
Neesham to Marsh, no run,length on fourth stump, 133kph/82mph and punched into the covers
Neesham to Marsh, 1 run,slower ball, Marsh waits and thumps a pull out to deep square leg

Neesham to Warner, SIX,in the slot and Warner bullocks it high over deep midwicket! Neither nor sort of ball from Neesham and he's swung into the crowd... Warner brings up a 34-ball half-century. He's coming for you, Kane
Neesham to Warner, 1 run,back-of-the-hand slower ball, I think, spins up off the surface to be tucked through midwicket
Neesham to Marsh, 1 run,pace off, length on off stump, punched through cover point
Santner to Marsh, 1 run,lobbed up slow and wide of the stumps, 86kph/53mph, cut for a single past extra cover
Santner to Warner, 1 run,over the wicket, flat and slightly quicker, twocked behind square on the leg side
Santner to Marsh, 1 run,smeared flat into the leg side, Phillips attempts the diving catch... taken on the bounce! Brilliant bit of work, nevertheless, keeps them to one
Santner to Warner, 1 leg bye,fired into the pads, tucked towards short fine
Santner to Marsh, FOUR,dragged down, Marsha is back in the crease, munched through midwicket! Brutal from the Bison, who's helping to lead the Straya charge tonight
Santner to Marsh, 1 run,slows his pace, floated up wide of the stumps, pulled down to long-on
Boult to Marsh, 1 run,back  of a length, punched past extra cover

Boult to Warner, OUT,splat! Boult strikes, stumps akimbo! Looks ungainly from Warner, attempting to hammer a crouching pull-cum-sweep through leg... the ball is on a length and just zips through, smashing into the polls and giving NZ a lifeline at the crucial moment
Boult to Maxwell, no run,back of a length, angled across from over the wicket, Maxwell flaps and misses
Boult to Maxwell, no run,dug in short at 140kph/88mph, mistimed on the pull towards midwicket
Boult to Maxwell, 1 run,back of a length on fourth stump, steered through cover point
Boult to Marsh, 1 run,fullish at 137kph and punched to long-on
Sodhi to Marsh, 1 wide,tossed up wide of the stumps... Marsh walks across and lets it go outside the tramlines

Sodhi to Marsh, SIX,clonked powerfully over long-on! Marsh climbs into a tossed-up Sodhi delivery, plants the front foot and mows it into the stands, brings up a fifty of his own. One ball quicker than Williamson earlier tonight
Sodhi to Marsh, 2 runs,drags this down and Marsh whirls it away through midwicket, between Phillips and Guptill but between them they track it down
Sodhi to Marsh, FOUR,drops short and this is muscled through midwicket! Bottom hand coming off the bat but properly blapped between the two boundary-riders for four more
Sodhi to Marsh, 1 wide,sprayed wide on the off side again
Sodhi to Marsh, no run,fizzes this down outside off, goes back and chops a bottom edge
Sodhi to Marsh, 1 wide,Sodhi is under pressure right now, bunging another full one wide into the tramlines
Sodhi to Marsh, no run,lands this, full outside off, punched for one
Sodhi to Marsh, 1 run,flattish legbreak and Marsh is back to cut a single through point
Milne to Marsh, no run,hurtles in and hits the pitch, pace off back of a length, blocked on off stump
Milne to Marsh, 1 run,short and slapped hard through backward square leg, just short of Mitchell! Does brilliantly to stop it on the volley, but NZ were praying it carried
Milne to Maxwell, FOUR,short and slugged between two outriders, didn't seem to really get hold of it but picks up four between deep backward square and fine leg
Milne to Maxwell, FOUR,dug in and top-edged over the keeper! Cramped him on the pull at 140kph but Maxwell swings like Happy Gilmore and gets it off the shoulder of the bat
Milne to Maxwell, no run,back of a length with pace off, looping through beneath the attempted pull
Milne to Maxwell, 1 wide,tennis-ball bouncer, 126kph/78mph and spinning up and over the batter, who watches it by and accepts the extra
Milne to Maxwell, 1 run,cue-ender in front of point... short of a length at 141kph/88mph and Maxwell hurls the hands, skews it away for one
Southee to Maxwell, FOUR,flicked away off the pads, Southee gets too straight to start with and a scrap of bat is enough
Southee to Maxwell, 1 wide,length ball down the leg side, Maxwell swings and misses - but it's a wide anyway
Southee to Maxwell, SIX,collared for a soaring six over fine leg! Bowled into the pitch and he's moved across to use the angle, ships it via airmail over the head of the man on the rope
Southee to Maxwell, 1 run,another bumper, doesn't get hold of this on the pull
Southee to Marsh, no run,length ball heading leg side, 133kph/82mph and Marsh takes it on the pads before the ball ricochets towards backward point. Came off the back of the bat, I think
Southee to Marsh, 1 leg bye,fired into the pads, deflected behind square
Southee to Maxwell, no run,shortish outside off and Maxwell miscues a cut towards backward point
Boult to Marsh, 2 runs,over the wicket, full on the stumps and driven down the ground
Boult to Marsh, FOUR,short ball with pace off, thoroughly Mitched through leg! He was almost waiting for that, leaning out to clobber four more between long-on and deep midwicket
Boult to Marsh, 1 run,fuller outside off and squirted through the covers
Boult to Maxwell, no run,short ball, pace off again, Maxwell is foxed and doesn't play a shot
Boult to Maxwell, 1 wide,down the leg side, 118kph/73mph, swings and misses
Boult to Maxwell, 1 run,length ball on the stumps, pace off and sliced towards short third
Boult to Marsh, 1 run,dropped! Tough caught-and-bowled chance, chipped straight at him by Marsh, got his hands up but just clanged off the fingertips
Milne to Marsh, no run,slower ball in the channel, Marsh swings and misses
Milne to Marsh, 1 run,pitched up at 144kph/89mph and drilled to long-off
Milne to Maxwell, no run,short and wide of the stumps, slower delivery and Maxwell swings hard but misses
Milne to Maxwell, no run,slapped in front of mid-off... another one falls just short. Southee does brilliantly to stop it on the bounce
Milne to Maxwell, 1 run,low full toss, swiped through backward square leg
Milne to Marsh, 1 run,fired full in the channel and punched to long-off. NZ look like they're making their peace with things already
Southee to Marsh, FOUR,clubbed down the ground past Neesham's dive, sitting on the back foot and pounded past long-off. No timing but plenty of rig behind that
Southee to Marsh, 1 run,chopped into the leg side
Southee to Maxwell, 1 run,hits a length, Maxwell rocks back and slaps insouciantly through midwicket
Southee to Marsh, 1 run,pace off, gives it some welly for one on the bounce to long-off

Southee to Maxwell, FOUR,reverse-swiped past short third, that'll do it for Australia's first T20 World Cup! Already the men in yellow are flooding on to the pitch from the dugout. Green'n'gold FTW, baby!
Starc to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 bye,bottom edged! Doesn't carry to Wade, he palms it away...some width outside off, Rizwan went after it. Well, that's been given a bye. Could have sworn he hit it
Starc to Babar Azam, no run,length ball on the pads, clipped sweetly but straight to square leg
Starc to Babar Azam, no run,full and wide outside off, a great-looking cover drive but straight to cover...could easily have had two boundaries
Starc to Babar Azam, FOUR,poor line, outside leg stump, Babar is able to catch up with it and flick to fine leg...147kph, but off target
Starc to Babar Azam, 1 run,full and straight, clipped off the pads wide of square leg
Starc to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,through him! Good length outside off, shapes back and scoots under the bat as he plays a square drive
Hazlewood to Babar Azam, no run,back of a length at off stump, that Test length, defended back up the pitch
Hazlewood to Babar Azam, FOUR,goes fuller and that's put away in style, gets forward and strokes a cover drive through the infield. Went with the swing. Lovely
Hazlewood to Babar Azam, 1 run,straighter, flicked just to the right of mid-on for a scampered single
Hazlewood to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,nagging length outside off, dropped down by his feet and he wants the single but is sent back
Hazlewood to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,good length, angled in at off stump, walks forward and pushes into the covers
Hazlewood to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,fuller at off stump, 138kph, driven to mid-off. Good over from Hazlewood
Maxwell to Babar Azam, no run,full and straight, Babar gets a leading edge as he looks to work to the leg side
Maxwell to Babar Azam, 1 run,flicks a straight delivery out to deep midwicket

Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR,almost a stunning catch! That would have been incredible from Warner. Maxwell round the wicket, Rizwan advanced down the pitch and lofted it straight. Warner ran back from mid-off, dived full length but couldn't hold on
Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,uses his feet again, this time just pushed into the off side
Maxwell to Babar Azam, no run,swings across the line of quite a full delivery and picks out square leg
Maxwell to Babar Azam, FOUR,excellent stroke, goes down on his back knee and sweeps this in the air backward of square, was just angling into middle and leg
Cummins to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 wide,full, angled down the leg side, Rizwan misses his whip but gets the wide
Cummins to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,back of a length at off stump, another swipe across the line and it takes the back pad into the off side
Cummins to Babar Azam, FOUR,flicked off the pads backward of square, terrific placement. Babar is up and running
Cummins to Babar Azam, 1 run,fuller, but again angling into the pads, flicked to deep square leg
Cummins to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,poor ball down the leg side but he gets away it, mostly, as Rizwan swats it straight to fine leg
Cummins to Babar Azam, no run,better delivery, back of a length at off stump, defended into midwicket. Rizwan racing up for the single but gets sent back
Cummins to Babar Azam, no run,almost a run out! Punched square off the back foot to point, Babar almost ran on the shot, would have been okay even with a direct hit from Maxwell I think
Hazlewood to Mohammad Rizwan, SIX,fantastic stroke! Back of a length, straight, Rizwan latches on with a front foot pull backward of square
Hazlewood to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,outside off, short of a length, dabbed to short third
Hazlewood to Babar Azam, 1 run,fuller outside off, a bit of a cross-batted swipe from Babar as he loses his shape, runs to mid-off
Hazlewood to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,full outside off, Rizwan aims to the leg side again and swings over the top of it
Hazlewood to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,a yorker at off stump, pushed to mid-off who is deep enough for the single
Hazlewood to Babar Azam, no run,back of a length outside off, swings hard and gets an outside edge to short third...a metre either side and that was four
Cummins to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,full at the stumps, it's almost a sweep shot that Rizwan ends up playing, straight to fine leg
Cummins to Babar Azam, 3 runs,full outside off, driven between cover and mid-off, not quite timed perfectly and Warner chases it down
Cummins to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR,a straight full toss, and it gets through the fielder at deep square...whipped very firmly, Maxwell got there with a dive but parried it
Cummins to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,good length at off stump, defended to the on side, 135kph
Cummins to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,back of a length, jars the splice of the bat as Rizwan defends it rather awkwardly

Cummins to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,dropped! But would have been a screamer. A length ball into the pads, Rizwan whips it away very strongly, just reaches Zampa on the full as he dives forward at fine leg. That got to him so quickly.
Zampa to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,full outside off, opens the face and dabs to short third
Zampa to Babar Azam, 1 run,gets across outside off and whips a full delivery to long-on
Zampa to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,very full, can only dig it out to the on side
Zampa to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,whips down the ground to long-on to bring up the fifty stand
Zampa to Babar Azam, no run,clips a full delivery into his boot which rolls back to the bowler
Zampa to Babar Azam, 1 run,uses his feet, Babar uses his feet but doesn't get to the pitch so just nudges to the off side. Tidy start from Zampa
Marsh to Babar Azam, 2 runs,full outside off, drives it square and deep point can't stop the second
Marsh to Babar Azam, FOUR,just back of a length and it's pulled handsomely through straight wicket...timed that so well
Marsh to Babar Azam, no run,round the wicket, well bowled, gets the yorker in and it's defended to backward point
Marsh to Babar Azam, 2 runs,full outside off, another strong drive, this time through cover and Cummins in action again
Marsh to Babar Azam, 1 wide,a loopy slower-ball bouncer, lets it go through and it's called
Marsh to Babar Azam, 1 run,full at the stumps, clipped to deep midwicket...Babar wanted the second, but Rizwan is firm in saying no
Marsh to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,round the wicket, low full toss at the toes, clipped to deep midwicket
Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,round the wicket, dragged down very short outside off, pulled to deep midwicket
Maxwell to Babar Azam, 1 run,goes back in the crease and tucks this off the pads through the leg side
Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,short, flat and quick outside off, a flat-batted drive to deep cover
Maxwell to Babar Azam, 1 run,straighter, worked off the stumps to deep midwicket
Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,clipped off the pads into vast open space on the leg side
Maxwell to Babar Azam, 1 run,touch shorter, he rocks back and pulls to long-on. Just the six singles from the over. Australia will take that
Zampa to Babar Azam, no run,pushed through and skids into the back pad but it's going well down leg side
Zampa to Babar Azam, 1 wide,tosses this very wide outside off, almost off the pitch
Zampa to Babar Azam, no run,very full at off stump, drives and can't beat cover on the edge of the ring
Zampa to Babar Azam, 1 run,full and straight again, clothed down to long-on
Zampa to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,uses his feet but can't get to the pitch, swings hard and it scurries down to long-on
Zampa to Babar Azam, no run,full outside off, square drives and can't beat point
Zampa to Babar Azam, OUT,taken at long-on! That's reward for a superb over from Zampa. Tossed up at the stumps, he goes for the slog sweep and it's easily taken at a reasonably wide long-on
Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,back of a length, sliding along with the angle outside off. Looks to dab it fine, but can't connect
Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,length ball drifting across to finish around off stump, swept to deep backward square leg

Maxwell to Fakhar Zaman, no run,full, angling down leg, appeal for caught behind from both bowler and keeper, but it didn't look like Fakhar came close to it with his bat while attempting to flick, I thought. May have brushed the pad. Bat brushed pad, it looks like
Maxwell to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,tossed up on off stump, steps out and drives to long-on
Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,steps out, not quite to the pitch of this ball, which straightens around leg stump, clipped back to the bowler
Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, 2 runs,steps out again, floats it up at his feet, clipped to the right of deep midwicket
Zampa to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,flat, angled across to pitch outside off, quite full, swiped down to long-on on the bounce
Zampa to Mohammad Rizwan, 2 runs,wrong'un, flighted high and wide of off stump. Drags a slog-sweep along the ground between deep midwicket and long-on

Zampa to Mohammad Rizwan, SIX,this one's in his arc, and he puts it away. Flat and quick, but a touch too full from Zampa, and he clears his front leg quickly and sinks onto his back knee to slog-sweep over the square leg boundary

Zampa to Mohammad Rizwan, 4 byes,more runs, and you wouldn't blame Wade too much for this. Flighted wide of off stump, legbreak with a lot of overspin. Dips to beat the cover drive, and Wade was unsighted as well as unsettled by the extra bounce. Past him quickly for four byes
Zampa to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,flat, angling down leg. Misses the sweep and is hit on the pad
Zampa to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,down the track, and Zampa bowls it quicker and wider. Drives forcefully but straight to long-off, on the bounce
Starc to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,back of a length, angling across to off stump, pulled towards deep square leg
Starc to Fakhar Zaman, no run,off-stump yorker, gets his feet out of the way and jams his bat down to squeeze it back to the bowler
Starc to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,back of a length just outside off, chopped to the left of backward point

Starc to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,slower bouncer, and Rizwan is through his hook too early. I thought it was the slower bouncer, but the speedgun says 144kph. Swings early at it, and he's smacked on the grill of his helmet. Ouch!
Starc to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,full, angling away from off stump, looks to drive through cover and is a bit early on it. Rolls towards mid-off off the inside half of the bat

Starc to Fakhar Zaman, no run,big appeal, but it's probably sneaking down the leg side. No reivew from Australia. Full and quick again, not a yorker, but it tails in late to beat Fakhar's cleared-front-leg whip. Smacks into his back pad
Hazlewood to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,length ball on the pads, whipped away, and fine leg falls to his left to keep it down to a single
Hazlewood to Fakhar Zaman, 1 wide,slants a slower ball across into wide-yorker territory, but ends up a touch too wide of off stump. Left alone

Hazlewood to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR,full, finishing on middle and off, and Fakhar clears his front leg and whips it away, clears midwicket, and leaves deep square leg too much ground to cover to his right

Hazlewood to Fakhar Zaman, no run,slower offcutter on a length, finishing around off stump. Looks to work it leg side, but extra bounce causes the ball to hit the high part of his bat and roll back to the bowler

Hazlewood to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,attempted yorker, ends up as a low-ish full-toss on middle and leg. Gets his front leg out of the way and whips to deep midwicket, who seems to have dropped back after that boundary

Hazlewood to Mohammad Rizwan, SIX,bang. That's a proper slog, and Hazlewood landed this right in the slot for that sort of slog. Slower delivery, but not that much slower, and on a length just outside off. Plenty of room to free his arms and swing across the line to clear the forward square leg boundary

Hazlewood to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,wide yorker, reaches out and stabs it to deep point to bring up his third fifty of the tournament. What a year this has been for him, but he'd want to finish this innings off with some serious acceleration. 41 balls to get to the landmark
Cummins to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,slower length ball outside off, presses forward and dabs into the point region

Cummins to Fakhar Zaman, (no ball) FOUR,bad ball. Was it above the waist? Yup, no-ball signalled. High full-toss around hip-high, finishing just outside off. Stays next to the line and uses the pace to steer it fine of short third. Lovely shot

Cummins to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,slower ball, back of a length, angling in towards off stump. No pace or room to work with on the pull, and he hits it aerially, but he checks his shot to ensure it lands well in front of deep square leg
Cummins to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,length ball wide of off stump, good line against Rizwan. Slower one too. Reaches out and flat-bats to extra-cover on the edge of the circle
Cummins to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,slower ball angling across and finishing full just outside off. Clears his front leg and drags a standing sweep out to deep backward square leg
Cummins to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,full-toss, but wide of off stump, and Rizwan reaches out to slash it away. Only manages a bottom edge that rolls to the keeper
Cummins to Mohammad Rizwan, 2 runs,slower ball, back of a length, just outside off. Shuffles across and works it into the wide mid-on region. No one in the circle there, so they pick up two easily
Zampa to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,looped up wide of off stump, driven to sweeper cover
Zampa to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,steps out and makes room. Floats it wider to make him reach out. Flat-bats it hard to extra-cover. Hits it hard, so he has to dive to make his ground at the other end
Zampa to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,slows down a wrong'un that finishes just outside off, swept along the ground to deep midwicket
Zampa to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,quick, angled in towards leg stump. They know Rizwan is good on the sweep, so they've kept deep backward square leg very fine. Keeps the sweep down to one run
Zampa to Fakhar Zaman, no run,flat, back of a length, fired across to finish outside off. Not short or wide enough for the cut, bottom-edges towards the keeper

Zampa to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,down the track to the leg-stump ball, doesn't quite get to the pitch, and the line cramps him for swinging room. Slogged along the floor to deep midwicket, and Zampa ends a super spell with a super over. Just the 22 runs off his four
Hazlewood to Fakhar Zaman, no run,he's stuck to this angle and line to Fakhar so far. Full and slanted to finish wide of off. Looks for a cute sweep from there, can't connect

Hazlewood to Fakhar Zaman, SIX,this time he doesn't get it wide or full enough. It's just wide enough to give him swinging room, and just short enough of the blockhole to allow him to find elevation. Clears his front leg and hits sweetly through the line to comfortably clear long-off
Hazlewood to Fakhar Zaman, 2 runs,very full on off stump, whipped to deep midwicket
Hazlewood to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,now he finds the wide-ish yorker despite Fakhar standing so deep in his crease. Jams his bat down and squeezes it out to extra-cover

Hazlewood to Mohammad Rizwan, (no ball) FOUR,and he bowls a high full-toss not that wide outside off. Poor bowling, and apart from the no-ball (it was chest high, or higher) Rizwan can drag a pull from that line and clear midwicket

Hazlewood to Mohammad Rizwan, SIX,wham, super shot. He had three back on the off side and he bowls a full one angling into the stumps. Attempted yorker, I suppose, but the length is nowhere near as full as he wants it. Steps across and towards the ball, and brings his wrists into play for a jawdropping whip over the wide long-on boundary
Hazlewood to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,steps out and Hazlewood widens the line of this fullish ball. Doesn't time this lofted drive, ends up falling short of wide long-off coming in off the rope
Starc to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,wide of the crease, and he goes in a straight line to nail this wide yorker. Looks to make room and step out, can't put bat to ball as he reaches out for the slash

Starc to Mohammad Rizwan, OUT,wide line again, but not quite the yorker. But the line pulls Rizwan out of shape as he tries to hit this over mid-off. Doesn't middle it at all, and he ends up hitting a balloony catch straight to the fielder

Starc to Fakhar Zaman, SIX,Wow. Attempted yorker, angling in towards off stump, but the length is not quite full enough. What a shot, though. Clears his front leg, and brings his bottom wrist fully into play to launch it high over the wide long-on boundary
Starc to Fakhar Zaman, 2 runs,full, angling into the stumps, and Fakhar clears his front leg to whip it along the ground to the left of deep midwicket

Starc to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR,oh man, this is some serious, serious bottom-hand power. Sends the umpire tumbling to save himself from a nasty injury. Attempted yorker again, ends up as a low, inswinging full-toss on the stumps. Gets that front leg out of the way, and just powers his wrists through a helicopterish drive that would have smacked Chris Gaffaney on the head had he not fallen out of the way in time
Starc to Fakhar Zaman, 1 wide,slower ball, ends up angling down the leg side, past the attempted swipe from Fakhar
Starc to Fakhar Zaman, 2 runs,in the blockhole on leg stump, clipped down the ground towards long-on. Too full to get any power on it, but that allows him to sprint through for two

Cummins to Asif Ali, OUT,he can get the big wicket, certainly. Seemed to be in the slot, on a length and just outside off, for the big hit, but it was the slower ball, and Asif didn't quite catch it. Ends up hitting it straight to long-on

Cummins to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,c Smith b Cummins, again, except Smith lets a regulation catch slip through his fingers at long-off. Slower length ball angling away from off stump. Goes for the big hit and doesn't get the power he wants, and Smith gets under it - moving forward and to his right - only to put it down
Cummins to Shoaib Malik, 1 run,shortish slower ball outside off, chopped away into the point region
Cummins to Fakhar Zaman, no run,good slower ball, offcutter jammed into the pitch on a shortish length, angling across to finish just outside off. Swings through the pull and misses

Cummins to Fakhar Zaman, no run,on-pace, just back of a length, angling across into the fifth-stump channel. Looks to clear his front leg and slog it over the on side, but he can't connect. Hard to line up a bowler when the changes of pace are accompanied by difficult lengths

Cummins to Fakhar Zaman, 1 leg bye,great over. Ends it with a short ball that climbs awkwardly at him from that blind spot outside leg stump. Steep bounce, and it beats the attempted pull and smacks into his helmet. Looks okay, after the physio comes on to check on him
Starc to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,slower ball, back of a length outside off. Waits and flat-bats to long-on

Starc to Shoaib Malik, OUT,bowled him. Back of a length angling into middle stump, some sort of cutter bowled into the pitch. Looks to swat it into the leg side, but it sneaks under his bat and pegs back middle stump
Starc to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run,short, angling slightly down leg and finishing at shoulder height. He's kept fine leg very fine, so the gloved pull only gets a single. Excellent field placement

Starc to Fakhar Zaman, SIX,bam. Looks for the yorker, ends up bowling a half-volley on the stumps, and Fakhar is ready and waiting, front leg out of the way, for another sweetly struck bottom-handed loft, this time over wide long-on. Effortless

Starc to Fakhar Zaman, SIX,this isn't the best over Starc has bowled. And Fakhar brings up what has been a terrific fifty. Again he looks for the yorker, and again he isn't full enough. Maybe he hasn't adjusted to Fakhar sitting so deep in his crease. Anyway, clears that front leg again and absolutely hammers the whip over the midwicket boundary

Starc to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,slower ball, back of a length, and this sort of ball has been harder to hit all evening than the yorker. Sticks in the pitch a little, angles in towards off stump, and Fakhar pulls without too much timing towards deep midwicket
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Warner, no run,great start! Full outside off, shaping away, beats the edge by a long way
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Warner, 1 run,full at the stumps, tapped to the on side

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Finch, OUT,what a stunning delivery! He's done it again. Full, swings back in at Finch, does him for pace as well and traps him straight in front. That was just too good. Wonderful bowling

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Marsh, no run,huge, huge appeal for lbw! Crazy scenes. They have called for the review. This is an unplayable yorker. He might be run out as well. One thing at a time. Speared in full at middle and leg, late swing. Actually, they check the run out first and he's okay there. Hits him full on the toe. Wow, umpire's call on impact and hitting the wickets. Breathe.
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Marsh, no run,what a beauty! This is amazing stuff from Shaheen. A good length ball outside off, sharp inswing and beats the inside edge
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Marsh, no run,good length at off stump, defended, a moment of calmness. WHAT. AN. OVER.
Imad Wasim to Warner, no run,round the wicket, angled across outside off, cut to point
Imad Wasim to Warner, 1 run,worked off the pads into square leg
Imad Wasim to Marsh, no run,slides in at middle and leg, played back down the pitch
Imad Wasim to Marsh, 1 run,backs away to leg and square drives into the covers for a scampered single
Imad Wasim to Warner, 1 run,brings out the reverse sweep, takes it off the stumps and finds short third
Imad Wasim to Marsh, 2 runs,angled into the pads, flicked backward of square for a brace
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Warner, no run,length ball outside off, crunches a drive but straight to cover
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Warner, (no ball) 1 run,full at the stumps, driven to mid-on who is deep enough for the single...and he's overstepped. Very tight call
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Marsh, no run,banged in a short, a slower ball at 129kph, Marsh is through his pull and it goes on the second bounce to Rizwan
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Marsh, FOUR,gets this through, full outside off, Marsh drills through the line and slots it between cover and mid-off
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Marsh, no run,good comeback, back of a length and straighter, takes a thick inside edge to short fine leg
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Marsh, 1 run,a slower ball, on a length at off stump, grips a little in the surface, pushed towards point where Shadab can't quite collect cleanly
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Warner, no run,well bowled, spears in a yorker at middle leg, 149kph and Warner does well to keep it out
Imad Wasim to Marsh, 1 run,full at the pads, gets a leading edge towards mid-off as he looks to tuck into midwicket
Imad Wasim to Warner, SIX,huge! Stand and deliver stuff from Warner. On a length, he stays in the crease and just monsters through the line over deep midwicket
Imad Wasim to Warner, FOUR,excellent batting...steps to the leg side and square drives through the covers. Superb use of the crease
Imad Wasim to Warner, FOUR,comes over the wicket but Warner finds the rope again, a real slingy delivery, Warner sweeps from underneath the ball and sends it over fine leg
Imad Wasim to Warner, 1 run,worked off the stumps into midwicket
Imad Wasim to Marsh, 1 run,tucked through midwicket and they stay at the single...strong response in that over
Haris Rauf to Marsh, SIX,crunched! Back of a length, Marsh picks it up superbly cleanly and swat-pulls it over deep midwicket. Immense power
Haris Rauf to Marsh, FOUR,good length outside off, this is a thick outside edge - although reasonably controlled - but it races fine of third man even though the fielder didn't have far to move
Haris Rauf to Marsh, 1 run,short of a length outside off, driven firmly off the back foot into the covers where it's well cut off
Haris Rauf to Warner, 1 run,back of a length outside leg stump, follows Warner, tucked into midwicket
Haris Rauf to Marsh, 1 run,fuller at off stump, might have been a slower ball, pushed through mid-on...not that much slower, still 133kph
Haris Rauf to Warner, 1 run,shapes to move outside leg, clears his front leg, but then mostly holds his position and taps a length ball to the on side
Hasan Ali to Warner, 1 run,round the wicket, full at the stumps, clipped to short fine leg
Hasan Ali to Marsh, FOUR,short at the body, in Marsh's arc, pulls it backward of square, wide and over short fine leg
Hasan Ali to Marsh, 1 run,good length outside off, dabbed into the backward point area
Hasan Ali to Warner, 1 run,round the wicket, quite well bowled, short of a length and angled in at leg stump, Warner steers down to third man
Hasan Ali to Marsh, no run,pushes this back-of-a-length delivery square into the off side, 136kph
Hasan Ali to Marsh, 1 run,goes for the yorker, dug out to mid-on
Shadab Khan to Marsh, no run,full outside off, square drives to point
Shadab Khan to Marsh, OUT,big top edge, and taken! Huge moment. Marsh goes for the slog sweep, gets too far underneath it, deep square has an entirety to think about and takes it well
Shadab Khan to Warner, 1 run,worked off the pads into midwicket...does Warner take things more carefully now?
Shadab Khan to Smith, no run,full and straight, tries a paddle-sweep and doesn't make contact
Shadab Khan to Smith, FOUR,short outside off, takes a thick edge just wide of the keeper as Smith pushes off the back foot...touch of fortune
Shadab Khan to Smith, no run,short of a length, a sweetly struck back-foot drive and an excellent stop at backward point...that would have raced away

Mohammad Hafeez to Warner, (no ball) SIX,what happened there?! It's come out as a double-bouncer, almost rolled down the pitch, Warner makes to move outside leg and swing it over deep midwicket and it's a no-ball
Mohammad Hafeez to Warner, 2 runs,full outside off, crunches a skimming drive down towards long-off where there's a fumble
Mohammad Hafeez to Warner, 1 run,angled in at the pads, pushed through midwicket
Mohammad Hafeez to Smith, 1 wide,poor delivery, pushed well down the leg side
Mohammad Hafeez to Smith, 1 run,better delivery, full outside off, driven just wide of the bowler
Mohammad Hafeez to Warner, no run,pushed into the covers
Mohammad Hafeez to Warner, 1 run,steps to leg and square drives this off the stumps into point
Mohammad Hafeez to Smith, no run,mistimes this back to the bowler as he steps away to leg
Shadab Khan to Warner, SIX,what a stroke! That's a magnificent shot. He looks like a man on mission. Lovely footwork to skip down the pitch then a huge lofted drive over wide long-on
Shadab Khan to Warner, 1 run,clips a full delivery towards long-on, Warner wanted the second and Smith quite rightly sends him back. Warner just able to turn in time

Shadab Khan to Smith, OUT,taken at deep midwicket! Another big top edge off Shadab. Very similar to the Marsh wicket, going for the slog sweep, goes way into the night sky. Smith knew as soon as he hit it. Another well-judged catch
Shadab Khan to Warner, 1 run,drives a full delivery out to deep cover
Shadab Khan to Maxwell, 1 run,goes deep in the crease, knocks a googly into midwicket. Not entirely sure he picked it
Shadab Khan to Warner, 1 run,short outside leg stump, he's a little fortunate here as Warner's pull finds deep backward square
Hasan Ali to Warner, FOUR,round the wicket, superbly played by Warner who is across onto off stump and pulls a short-of-a-length delivery behind square
Hasan Ali to Warner, 1 run,back of a length outside off, square drives to deep cover
Hasan Ali to Maxwell, no run,short of a length at off stump, defended
Hasan Ali to Maxwell, 2 runs,gets inside a short ball, angled in at middle and leg, pulled around the corner and good work at long leg by Malik
Hasan Ali to Maxwell, 1 run,gone with a hit! Maxwell pushes a full ball to cover and sets off. Fakhar, a left-handed fielder, collects and Warner wasn't in the frame with a direct hit
Hasan Ali to Warner, 1 run,full toss at off stump, worked out to deep midwicket

Shadab Khan to Warner, OUT,big, big appeal, and it's given! HUUUGE wicket for Pakistan, and Rizwan and Shadab are both over the moon! Lovely delivery, tossed up across the left-hander and pitching on a length, wide of off stump, inviting the cover drive. Goes hard at it, and edges behind. It was the legbreak, but it didn't turn that much, but it did bounce a little more than expected
Shadab Khan to Stoinis, 1 run,tossed up just outside off, stretches out for a delicate lap-sweep through backward square leg
Shadab Khan to Maxwell, no run,back of a length outside off, chopped hard to backward point
Shadab Khan to Maxwell, no run,flat length ball straightening towards off stump, blocked towards extra-cover
Shadab Khan to Maxwell, 1 run,back of a length, sharp turn from just outside off. Wanted to push into the covers, gets a thick outside edge that rolls to the right of backward point
Shadab Khan to Stoinis, 1 run,back of a length wrong'un finishing on middle stump, goes back and works it into the midwicket region
Imad Wasim to Stoinis, no run,looks to make room, follows him with a flat arm-ball at leg stump. Looks to push into the off side, gets a thick inside edge into the leg side
Imad Wasim to Stoinis, no run,length ball, this one straightens slightly on an off-stumpish line. Punched to extra-cover
Imad Wasim to Stoinis, no run,length ball, a little slower than usual, and it keeps going with the angle as Stoinis looks to drive inside-out. Inside-edge into the boot
Imad Wasim to Stoinis, 1 run,a rare (slightly) turning delivery outside off, just back of a length. Punched to deep point
Imad Wasim to Maxwell, no run,nicely bowled. A bit of in-drift towards middle stump, cramps Maxwell who's shaping to drive to long-off. Hits it back to the bowler in the end

Imad Wasim to Maxwell, 2 runs,there's the attempted reverse-sweep from Maxwell, but the length is a touch short for that, and the arm ball follows him and leaves him without too much room to swing his arms. Hits the glove and loops over the keeper, to his right
Shadab Khan to Stoinis, 1 run,back of a length outside off, flat-batted towards long-off, who's stationed quite wide

Shadab Khan to Maxwell, OUT,got him, Shadab continues to turn this Pakistan's way. Length ball spinning away from the stumps, and Maxwell chances his arm with the reverse-sweep. Kind of falls over to the leg side while hitting it, and doesn't nail it as well as he can. Ends up hitting it too close to deep square leg, where Haris Rauf, initially moving to his left, almost overruns the ball, but dives to his right and takes a crucial, crucial catch. Shadab's now taken out Smith, Warner and Maxwell. Wow

Shadab Khan to Stoinis, SIX,ooh, just gets it wide enough of the fielder. Tossed up just outside off, and he picks the googly and goes with the swing, just clearing the boundary to the left of deep midwicket
Shadab Khan to Stoinis, no run,quicker legbreak now, just outside off, gets forward to push to extra-cover
Shadab Khan to Stoinis, 1 run,flatter, straightens towards off stump. Makes room and punches to sweeper cover
Shadab Khan to Wade, no run,length ball, wrong'un, finishing around off stump. Gets forward and defends to extra-cover

Haris Rauf to Stoinis, no run,back of a length close to off stump, lets it come and dabs to the right of backward point. Wade hares out of his crease and Stoinis sends him back, and Shadab, sprinting to his right from backward point, could have run Wade out had he hit the stumps direct at the bowler's end, but he snatches at it and misses
Haris Rauf to Stoinis, 1 leg bye,back of a length slower ball at the hip. Misses the flick and picks up a leg bye into the backward square leg region
Haris Rauf to Wade, no run,back of a length, angling across to finish just outside off. Looks to dab towards third man, but only manages an edge that bounces in front of Rizwan diving to his left

Haris Rauf to Wade, FOUR,shot. Angles this across to finish outside off, and lands it a touch too full. Right in the slot for Wade to launch it back over the bowler's head. Flat hit, lands just inside the rope to the right of long-on

Haris Rauf to Wade, 1 run,digs this in short, and it's quick and it angles across and gets up to shoulder height outside off. Difficult to pull from there, and it hits the high part of the bat and goes on the bounce to long-on

Haris Rauf to Stoinis, no run,lovely slower ball. Back of a length in the corridor. Looks to run it down to third man, completely misjudges the pace, and it beats his bat and bounces twice more before reaching Rizwan. It almost beats him by turning like an offbreak just before reaching him
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Wade, 1 run,back of a length, angling into leg stump to deny Wade room. Tucked away to deep square leg

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Stoinis, 1 run,slower ball into the pitch, back of a length and angling across to finish around off stump. Looks for the pull, ends up bottom-edging into his body to the right of Shadab at short midwicket. Again there's a run-out chance, but he throws on the turn and misses at the bowler's end. There was no single there, but they chanced it and got it
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Wade, no run,quick bouncer just outside off, too quick for Wade as he stepped out, made room, and looked to slash it away. The bowler saw him coming and dug it in
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Wade, 1 run,into the blockhole on leg stump, clipped away to deep square leg

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Stoinis, 2 runs,back of a length, slanting across to finish on a fifth-stumpish line. Looked to push into the on side, and it's the cutter that leaves him off the pitch. Thick leading edge flies to the left of backward point

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Stoinis, 1 run,shortish slower ball pitching around leg stump and finishing around off. Makes a bit of room, rides the bounce, and slaps to deep point. No real pace to hit that anywhere else
Hasan Ali to Stoinis, FOUR,full outside off, and that's put away. Almost a half-volley, and he uses the room for a flat-bat drive to beat extra-cover diving right and long-off diving left
Hasan Ali to Stoinis, (no ball) 2 runs,full on middle and leg, clipped to the right of deep midwicket
Hasan Ali to Stoinis, 2 runs,slower ball, short on off stump, pulled firmly to the right of deep midwicket
Hasan Ali to Stoinis, 1 run,back of a length, offcutter finishing on off stump, shuffles across and tucks this to the left of midwicket
Hasan Ali to Wade, 1 run,in the blockhole on middle and leg, clipped quietly into the midwicket region, no one in the circle there
Hasan Ali to Stoinis, 1 run,hard length on off stump, skids through quickly and cramps Stoinis on the pull. Checks his shot and plays a short-arm jab to deep midwicket
Hasan Ali to Wade, no run,good finish to the over from Hasan. Fullish slower ball angling away from off stump. Swings too early at the lofted hit over the leg side, and fails to connect

Haris Rauf to Stoinis, no run,back of a length, slower ball close to off stump. Punched back to the bowler. He shuffled across to it and got too close to the line while looking to hit through the covers

Haris Rauf to Stoinis, 2 runs,excellent shot, but he only gets two for it. It's in the blockhole on off stump, and he lifts his front leg out of the way and whips it hard with his bottom hand, but Malik slides to his left at deep midwicket and makes a super save

Haris Rauf to Stoinis, SIX,bam, that's what Stoinis can do. Not a bad ball in terms of intent, digs it into that back-of-a-length zone, but it sits up just outside off, and Stoinis holds his shape nicely and muscles it away over the midwicket boundary

Haris Rauf to Stoinis, FOUR,there's that power again. Terrific stuff. He's manufactured room to really smash two near-yorkers with immense power in this over. Up on an off-stumpish line, and he gets his front leg out of the way and whips through the line with his bottom hand to hit it past the bowler and beat long-off sprawled to his right

Haris Rauf to Stoinis, no run,back of a length legcutter, straightens on off stump at 147kph, and Stoinis can only block it back. Was shaping to work it leg side, but he saw the release and knew it would straighten
Haris Rauf to Stoinis, 1 run,slower ball, shortish, just outside off, pulled towards deep square leg

Hasan Ali to Stoinis, 1 run,back of a length, angling into the stumps and denying Stoinis room. Shuffles across to work it through square leg. Stoinis, pushing his bat into the crease, and Hasan, running back to the stumps to collect the throw, semi-collide at that end
Hasan Ali to Wade, 2 runs,full on leg stump, whipped to the left of deep midwicket

Hasan Ali to Wade, SIX,wow, that's a big, big hit at a big, big moment. Length ball angling across to finish outside off. It's not the easiest ball to hit, it's the offcutter, but Wade manufactures a lot of bottom-hand power to launch that high and far over long-on
Hasan Ali to Wade, 1 run,in the blockhole on off stump, seemed to swing a bit from middle to off. Swiped towards deep midwicket

Hasan Ali to Stoinis, 1 run,slower ball, into the pitch, finishes at just under waist height close to off stump. Can't get any elevation off those skiddy back-of-a-length balls, and he pulls along the floor to deep midwicket

Hasan Ali to Wade, FOUR,full on leg stump, and that's superbly put away, great wrist work. He's working slightly against the angle on this flick, even though it was on leg stump, and he got his front leg out of the way and whipped it to beat short fine leg to his right and still get it a long way away from deep square leg, to his left

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Stoinis, no run,edged, and Rizwan isn't sure if it's carried. It's that difficult length just short of a length, and it's the cutter angling across Stoinis. Looks to pull, gets the bottom edge, and it falls just short of Rizwan diving to his left

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Stoinis, 1 leg bye,appeal for lbw as Stoinis shuffles across and misses a leg-side whip. Not given, and Pakistan have reviewed... Did it pitch in line. And if so, was it missing off stump? It was just short of a length too, so height may also be an issue. No bat on it. The ball pitches just outside leg, so Stoinis lives on
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Wade, 1 wide,looks for the yorker, ends up sliding it down leg, past the attempted flick

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Wade, 2 runs,dropped! Hasan Ali's not having the greatest of games here. Fullish, angling into the stumps, and Wade swings too early at his slog, toe-ends it in the air to the left of deep midwicket, where Hasan runs too quickly, almost overruns the ball, and lets it slip through his fingers

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Wade, SIX,shot, what a terrific shot that is from Wade! Looks for the yorker, and Wade expects it. Shuffles across, exposes all his stumps, and absolutely middles the pants off this scoop over short fine leg. Carries over the boundary with ease

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Wade, SIX,six more, Wade is on absolute fire here. This was a fullish cutter, coming into him from just outside off, and he simply clears his front leg and whips it away over midwicket

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Wade, SIX,wow, wow, wow. 6, 6, 6. And Australia are in the final. Another attempted yorker, and again, Wade shuffles across to expose all his stumps, and scoops it over the boundary behind him. Literally over the keeper's right shoulder. What an incredible shot. What an incredible finish from Wade. New Zealand finished last night's game in the 19th over. Australia have done the same tonight
Southee to Buttler, 1 run,short and at leg stump first up, Buttler nicely on top of that to pull to fine leg
Southee to Bairstow, no run,full outswinger, curving away nicely from the corridor. Jonny's feet are moving. Leans in nicely and drives on the bounce to extra cover
Southee to Bairstow, 1 run,good length and into middle stump, gets forward and pats this off the inside half of the bat to steal a single from mid-on

Southee to Buttler, no run,no feet from Buttler. This is a lovely outswinger again, swung late from a middle and off line and curves away viciously as Buttler feels for it with his hands away from the body. Beaten
Southee to Buttler, no run,full and into leg stump, can't get the flick away, that's onto his pad
Southee to Buttler, FOUR,full and at middle stump, swung away again but this time Buttler is right on top of the ball as he closes the face and cuts the movement to flick this through square leg
Boult to Bairstow, no run,good length and marginal shape inwards, but solidly defended into the leg side
Boult to Bairstow, no run,good length and slanted across middle stump. Bairstow sets up for a short-arm pull and misses. Cops that on the back thigh

Boult to Bairstow, no run,narrowly past off stump! What a ball that is, whew! Full an swung in from an off stump line. Bairstow thinks he has that covered as he looks to drive to mid-off's left. But that ball leaves him after pitching. Unplayable
Boult to Bairstow, 2 runs,good length and just outside off, punched on the rise to mid-off's left and they'll take Williamson's arm on
Boult to Bairstow, no run,well directed bouncer. At middle stump, awkward and headed for the ribs. Bairstow watches closely and sways away from that

Boult to Bairstow, FOUR,past the keeper and four fortunate runs. Short of a length and in the corridor, backs away to create room and has a big slash at that to find the inside edge and then the fine leg boundary
NULL
Southee to Buttler, 1 run,good length at off stump, gets forward and drops it into the covers with soft hands
Southee to Bairstow, no run,walks down at that but Southee has swung it in and cramped him. Lifts off a length and catches the thigh guard
Southee to Bairstow, no run,good length and late swing away from off stump. Has a little walk down again but is forced to defend this to mid-on
Southee to Bairstow, no run,short of a length and tight at middle and leg. Skids on quickly and beats his attempted swipe off the back foot
Southee to Bairstow, no run,good length and swung away from middle stump. Leans in and closes the face on this, uppish before it rolls out to mid-on

Boult to Buttler, FOUR,oh well done. This is full and swung in towards middle and leg. Buttler stays leg side of that, gets the front leg away from the ball to create room and then pats firmly to get this between non-striker and mid-off
Boult to Buttler, FOUR,caressed. Good length and across off stump, stays leg side of it again but reaches out this time and punches on the up through the covers
Boult to Buttler, no run,short of a length just outside off, waits on that and dabs it to backward point
Boult to Buttler, 5 wides,dug in too short and clears both the batter and the keeper. Boult's surprise goes awry, that's sailed over from a middle stump line

Boult to Buttler, 2 runs,full and shaping in at off stump, stays leg side and drills this to mid-off's right. Williamson dives and tumbles to his right to stop. But this direct hit at the non-striker's end has pinged into the leg side and they take a second
Boult to Buttler, no run,short of a length and across the corridor, looks for the pull and is beaten on the under-edge
Boult to Buttler, 1 run,short and down leg side, a controlled pull down to fine leg
Southee to Buttler, 1 run,full and just outside off, draws him into the cover drive without a big stride. Inside edge sprints down to fine leg
Southee to Bairstow, FOUR,shot! Good length and skidding on nicely at an off stump line. Bairstow stands tall and uses the bounce on this to offer the full face and chip that over the bowler's head
Southee to Bairstow, no run,short of a length and skidding on low past leg stump. Shapes to pull and is struck outside the line
Southee to Bairstow, 1 run,full and at middle stump, gets forward and drives along the ground to long-on
Southee to Buttler, 1 run,short and headed for the helmet as Buttler backs away to make room. Hacks at that for an under-edge down to fine leg
Southee to Bairstow, 1 run,good length and just outside off, punched on the rise to mid-off's left

Milne to Bairstow, OUT,taken at mid-off! Williamson lunging to hold on. They've sent it upstairs with the soft signal out. This is a pretty friendly delivery first up from Milne - full and right there for the cover drive outside off. Bairstow goes with hard hands and can't keep it down. It dips to Williamson's left and he has taken this well above the ground and there's no doubt on the replays. The Bairstow experiment doesn't quite work out for England, New Zealand have stemmed the flow
Milne to Malan, 1 run,good length and onto the pads, can't get the glance away. It trickles pitch side
Milne to Buttler, no run,full and just outside off, driven neatly along the floor to short extra cover
Milne to Buttler, 1 run,short and outside off, comes on nicely as he pulls firmly out to deep square
Milne to Malan, no run,short of a length and across the corridor, gets deep in the crease and looks to pull. Cops it on the back thigh
Milne to Malan, 1 leg bye,short of a length and rising up to beat this pull, into the thigh
Sodhi to Malan, 1 run,full and tossed up at leg stump, gets forward and flicks to deep backward square
Sodhi to Buttler, 1 run,good length and a googly, at leg stump. Gets back and whips it out to deep midwicket
Sodhi to Malan, no run,short of a length and sliding on in the corridor. Malan's looked to make room and chop that through the off side. Beaten
Sodhi to Malan, 1 run,short and just outside off, slower this time. Really waits on that before punching to sweeper cover

Sodhi to Buttler, 1 run,beats him in flight but Buttler gets something behind that. This length ball dipped quickly outside off and Buttler had to throw his body at it after stepping out and not coming close. Safely stabbed to sweeper cover in the end
Sodhi to Malan, 1 run,good length at off stump, punched to sweeper cover off the back foot
Santner to Malan, 1 run,good length and flat outside off, slight turn inwards. Has a big hoick off the front foot and gets it out to deep midwicket off the inside edge
Santner to Buttler, no run,full at leg stump, gets forward and closes the face, leading edge to extra cover
Santner to Buttler, FOUR,classic Jos. Good length and at the stumps, gets low very quickly and taps this on its head to get the reverse sweep past point
Santner to Buttler, 2 runs,good length and quicker, angled in at middle stump. Gets down and shapes for the reverse, adjusts to lap sweep it instead
Santner to Buttler, no run,tossed up full and slow outside off, mistimed reverse sweep to short third
Santner to Buttler, 1 run,length and in at leg stump, punched down to long-on off the back foot

Sodhi to Buttler, OUT,Buttler's been given lbw and he reviews. It's a legbreak, good length and turning away from middle and off. He brings out the reverse sweep and misses. Rapped in front of off stump. Was it turning away enough to miss? It wasn't! Huge wicket for New Zealand. That's hitting the middle of off stump. England lose Buttler, England lose a review, and it is Ish Sodhi doing the business for New Zealand once again
Sodhi to Ali, 1 run,full and at off stump, gets forward and drives along the floor to long-off
Sodhi to Malan, 1 run,full at off stump, driven to long-off's right
Sodhi to Ali, no run,short of a length and sliding across off stump, under-edge on the attempted cut
Sodhi to Ali, 1 run,full on middle stump, gets forward and flicks to deep midwicket's left
Sodhi to Malan, FOUR,finds the gap! Good length and just outside off. Not quite driving length but he's improvised and use the bounce to go inside-out and sufficiently to long-off's right
Neesham to Ali, 1 run,good length and across the corridor, gets forward and drives on the rise to sweeper's right
Neesham to Malan, no run,good length and across the corridor. Shuffles and has a slog across this, beaten

Neesham to Malan, 1 run,drpped by Conway stretching to his left. Only a part-timer, but he'll feel like that was there for the taking. This is good length and angled away, he looks to drive on the rise and gets an edge that's low to the keeper's left. He manages to get two hands but can only parry to third man
Neesham to Ali, no run,short and across the corridor, mistimed pull, off the toe end to midwicket
Neesham to Ali, 1 run,short of a length at off stump, pulled out to deep square

Neesham to Malan, FOUR,sweeeeeeet. Lovely flowing drive from Malan. Good length and just outside off, sliding on nicely for a drive on the rise. And he leans in with a half-stride and gets his arms through this nicely. Sweeper gives a long chase to his left and then puts in a big dive to no avail
Phillips to Ali, 1 run,biffed through the line, one bounce to long-off
Phillips to Malan, FOUR,round the wicket, and that's superb timing! Steps to leg, opens the face, and the stance, bashes the ball on the up through his favoured covers, and away to the rope!
Phillips to Malan, no run,so nearly loses his leg stump! Attempted reverse sweep, misses, ball skids by
