Phillips to Malan, FOUR,donked on the up once more! High, tight to the long-off fielder, but there's power behind that lofted drive, and over the rope it goes!
Phillips to Malan, 1 run,fired into the toes, tickled to the leg side, looking for two, but Moeen says no
Phillips to Ali, 1 run,on the pads, whipped to square leg. A good over for England to kick things off after drinks
Milne to Ali, 1 run,slower ball, back of a length as Moeen waits and taps into the gap at midwicket

Milne to Malan, 3 runs,flogged through the covers again! All along the turf this time, and smoked too... that's hugely encouraging for Malan, who is nailing his favourite stroke now. But Phillips does brilliantly with a sprint and dive to claw it in
Milne to Ali, 1 run,Moeen's turn to hit with the angle, across the left-hander, out to deep cover
Milne to Malan, 1 run,full length, clipped out of the blockhole, another single to square leg
Milne to Ali, no run,slower bouncer, Moeen winds into the pull but can't connect
Milne to Ali, 1 run,full toss, patted with firm placement into the covers. A tidy second over from Milne, as England keep ticking for now
Sodhi to Ali, 1 wide,fired down the leg side, Moeen can't connect on the pull
Sodhi to Ali, 1 run,a trot to the pitch, clipped to mid-on, optimistic thoughts of a second, but nope
Sodhi to Malan, 1 run,reverse sweep, excellently intercepted with a dive at point. Malan timed it well, waiting on the stroke outside leg, but denied the boundary
Sodhi to Ali, 1 run,tossed up, dipping on a full length, Moeen is momentarily deceived in flight and settles for stump preservation
Sodhi to Malan, no run,another reverse sweep from outside leg, not timed this time as point gathers
Sodhi to Malan, 1 run,clattered behind square with a premeditated hop to the off side, panned on the full toss with an aggressive sweep
Sodhi to Ali, FOUR,too wide, and that's a freebie! Moeen reaches across his crease, places the ball past point on the cut, and that races through the acres of space in the deep
Milne to Malan, 1 run,hacked out to the off side, back of a length and hitting down on the cut
Milne to Ali, 1 run,full, and cuffed to the on side
Milne to Malan, no run,short, and that's a swishing pull, can't connect this time
Milne to Malan, 2 runs,thumped on the full, and dropped in the followthrough! Right at the toe of the bat, firm strike, and Milne flings out a hand but can't close the fingers. Tough chance
Milne to Malan, 1 run,very full again, opens the face and places the push into the cover region
Milne to Ali, 1 run,full toss, but Moeen can't capitalise, too early on his swing as the ball fizzes out to mid-off
Boult to Ali, 2 runs,very full, flashed off the toes in front of square, an instant call for two and back they come
Boult to Ali, 1 run,Moeen goes for it, and gets away with it! Seizing on the knuckle-ball, full length, and not remotely timed, a high skier plugs short of Southee, sprinting in from long-off
Boult to Malan, 1 run,short, Malan smashes up into the off side, another single but not finding the boundaries right now
Boult to Ali, FOUR,precious runs! Over-pitched on the legs, Moeen is ready for it, closing the face on the pads, and picking off the four through backward square
Boult to Ali, 1 run,crashed hard through the line, not timed again, but Moeen's mind is made up now...
Boult to Malan, 1 leg bye,attempted paddle over the leg side, not timed but they rush the single as the keeper comes up to collect
Southee to Malan, SIX,back of a length, and pumped over square leg for the first six of the night! Southee rolls his fingers and pays the price!

Southee to Malan, OUT,hacked across the line, and Malan has feathered it! Another short ball, but a fraction fuller, and a thin under-edge. A good hand from Malan, but he's gone just as he was posed to cut loose
Southee to Livingstone, 1 run,full length, clipped to the on-side to get up and running
Southee to Ali, no run,very full, wide line, Moeen can't connect, inside the tramlines. Fine delivery
Southee to Ali, 1 run,bashed through the line, but with no timing, as Southee hits a length outside off and invites the big wind-up
Southee to Livingstone, 1 run,spliced pull, lands wide of square leg! Another single as Southee bends his back and catches the new man unawares
Sodhi to Livingstone, 1 wide,too wide, a bonus run for England
Sodhi to Livingstone, 1 run,outside off, rocking back, and chopped to deep cover
Sodhi to Ali, SIX,swatted lustily over the leg side! A step to leg to open the stance, and monster-munched over the longest boundary! Moeen is teeing off to order!
Sodhi to Ali, no run,another shimmy to the pitch, but a flatter response from Sodhi, thudding into his thigh pad as the bat swings through
Sodhi to Ali, no run,huge wind-up, right across the left-hander, who can't reach it with a wild swipe
Sodhi to Ali, 2 runs,saw him coming again, slid through flatter, yanked around the corner for two. Tight for the second run but safe enough
Sodhi to Ali, 1 run,more marching to the pitch, can't get this one away either, but he keeps the strike with a push to long-off
Milne to Ali, SIX,too short, too slow, too languid from Moeen! Hanging back in the crease, lining up the short ball, and hoisted over midwicket by a distance!
Milne to Ali, 1 run,fuller length, wider line, a toe-ended slap from Moeen, hauled to the on-side and they think about the second
Milne to Livingstone, 1 run,banged in short, Livingstone pulls but can't get on top of the stroke. Sodhi gathers at backward square
Milne to Ali, 1 run,dumped through the line, Moeen checks the stroke outside off on a full length, one bounce to long-off
Milne to Livingstone, 1 wide,wide outside off, attempted slower ball. Overcooks it
Milne to Livingstone, no run,Livingstone has a massive wind-up, over midwicket. And misses. But the intent is plain!
Milne to Livingstone, SIX,Clattered violently back over the bowler's head! Yet another final-ball boundary, and a huge statement of intent from Livingstone! Slot ball, slotted!
Boult to Ali, 1 run,fires in the yorker, worked to leg
Boult to Livingstone, 2 runs,full toss, outside off, and outside Livingstone's arc. Reaches for it with a cross-batted slap to deep cover
Boult to Livingstone, FOUR,flapped from back of a length, out through wide long-off, Guptill gallops and dives, but can't reach it! This is the big finish England ordered...
Boult to Livingstone, 1 run,full toss, very straight, cuffed out to point, slightly skewed on point of impact
Boult to Ali, no run,well bowled, banged in short, but took the pace off as Moeen was suckered and bails out of his pull
Boult to Ali, 1 run,pumped off the full length to extra cover. Tightened up well in that over. Can England find the big finish now?
Neesham to Ali, 1 run,full length, outside off, languidly driven to long-off

Neesham to Livingstone, OUT,holes out to long-off! Livingstone kneels into a drill over the off side, reaching into the full-length wide ball, but he can't clear the ropes, nor beat Santner stationed on the edge of them!
Neesham to Ali, FOUR,that's a fine fifty for Moeen! Full toss, outside off, helped on the up, one bounce past the wide long-off sweeper!
Neesham to Ali, 1 run,full toss again, that was a let-off for Neesham, Moeen flicks off his pads, but only as far as backward square
Neesham to Morgan, 1 wide,fires it out wide, but overcooked. Moeen attempts to steal the strike but can't do so
Neesham to Morgan, 2 runs,banged in short, Morgan pulls without power, but Boult at backward square fumbles... and they come back for two... was that deliberate? That would be meta-cricket if so...

Neesham to Morgan, 2 runs,sliced high out to deep cover... must be out ... but Phillips loses his footing and puts it down! A let-off for Morgan and England, as his heels give way, and that's a bonus two for England
Woakes to Guptill, FOUR,short of a length and some shape way, but plenty of time for Guptill to wait on this and try to slap it over extra cover. It comes off the toe end but is clear
Woakes to Guptill, no run,good length and curved away outside off. Curved a long long way away. Guptill throws his hands at that and is beaten

Woakes to Guptill, OUT,taken at mid-on! It's a full ball at leg stump, some bend towards the off stump but nothing significant movement-wise. But it's just enough to draw the leading edge as Guptill closes the face too soon on his attempted flick. Massive blow
Woakes to Mitchell, 1 run,full and onto the pads, leans in an flicks out to deep square
Woakes to Williamson, no run,short of a length and swung away from the corridor. Has a jab at that outside off and is beaten
Woakes to Williamson, 3 runs,full and searching for swing that doesn't arrive. It's at middle and off and Wiliamson clips it wide of mid-on who has to put in a tumble at the boundary
Jordan to Williamson, no run,short and steep in the corridor, gets on his toes for the punch but can't get behind the bounce of this one. Harmlessly trickles into the off side
Jordan to Williamson, no run,full and just outside off, leans in and drives to mid-off
Jordan to Williamson, no run,inside edge past off stump by a safe enough distance. This sticks in the pitch, a short ball outside off. Williamson is tentative on his attempted cut
Jordan to Williamson, 1 run,good length at leg stump, shuffles and pushes to long-on's right off the back foot
Jordan to Mitchell, 3 runs,good length and slanting onto the pads. Waits on that and flicks it well in front of the man at deep square
Jordan to Williamson, 1 run,good length and into leg stump, flicked straight to midwicket
Woakes to Williamson, no run,short of a length and at the hips, glances aerially but it's on the bounce in the end to short fine
Woakes to Williamson, no run,steps out and is cramped. Good length ball gets tight on him and all he can do is fend this into the pitch
Woakes to Williamson, no run,good length and into leg stump, looks to flick that and cops it on the thigh

Woakes to Williamson, OUT,they've got him! Lots of dots in Williamson's innings and in the end he's tried to break the shackles with a ramp shot. It's gone terribly wrong, he's top edged it to Adil Rashid's right at short fine and that is taken comfortably. Good length and rising at an off stump line and he was down early to try and put this away. Not to be
Woakes to Mitchell, no run,past the outside edge. Good length, in the corridor, drawing him forward before moving it away off the surface
Woakes to Mitchell, no run,good length and just outside off, mistimed drive on the rise, rolls pitch side
Jordan to Conway, no run,short of a length, slammed into the pitch and moving away. Conway has a swish away from the body and is beaten
Jordan to Conway, no run,short of a length and tight at off stump, defended into the pitch off the inside half
Jordan to Conway, no run,good length and wide outside off, has a big drive at that and is beaten on the under-edge
Jordan to Conway, 1 wide,good length and slanted down leg side with the angle, past his glance
Jordan to Conway, no run,short and skiddy in the corridor, Conway wants to get on top of that for the pull but that's hurried onto him and gotten very tight at the body. Jordan fields to his left
Jordan to Conway, no run,short of a length and in at middle stump, pushed into the leg side with the angle
Jordan to Conway, FOUR,oh lovely shot. Good length and rising outside off, gets a half stride out and goes inside-out over extra cover with a high elbow and solid balance
Woakes to Mitchell, 2 runs,safely between two fielders. Full and just outside off, might have been a slower one. He goes through with an attempted lofted drive. Gets it between mid-off and mid-on
Woakes to Mitchell, FOUR,good length and into leg stump, stands tall and has a well-timed whip at this to get it behind square
Woakes to Mitchell, 1 run,slower ball at a length on middle stump, pushed to mid-on off the back foot
Woakes to Conway, no run,good length and in the corridor, looks to drive with the angle but gets an inside edge past the stumps
Woakes to Conway, 1 run,good length at middle stump, steps out and punches on the rise to mid-off
Woakes to Mitchell, no run,full slower ball at middle stump, defended down the pitch
Rashid to Conway, FOUR,short of a length and across off stump, plenty of time to rock back and punch this firmly through extra cover
Rashid to Conway, 1 run,good length and turning in marginally from off stump, gets forward and drives it past the non-striker
Rashid to Mitchell, no run,googly and then an lbw appeal. He was forward, trying to flick into the leg side, was struck in front of middle
Rashid to Mitchell, 1 run,full at middle stump, jammed down to long-on
Rashid to Conway, no run,good length and spun down leg side, beaten on the sweep
Rashid to Conway, FOUR,crunched past mid-off! This is a length ball outside off, he steps out to the pitch of it and gets a lovely flowing drive to the fielder's right
Wood to Mitchell, no run,good length and tight at off stump, defended hurriedly into the off side
Wood to Mitchell, no run,length and tight at the body, nudged out
Wood to Mitchell, 2 runs,short of a length and just outside off, hurried aerial pull, dragged wide of long-on
Wood to Mitchell, 1 run,falls short of fine leg running in. Short and rising in the corridor, looks for the hook but is caught under it and gets a top edge
Wood to Conway, 1 run,short of a length and across the corridor, has a swish and gets a thick outside edge to third man
Wood to Mitchell, 1 run,good length at off stump, pushed out towards mid-off
Rashid to Mitchell, no run,good length and turning away from off stump, reverse sweep straight to backward point
Rashid to Mitchell, no run,good length and sticking in the surface and getting big as he brings out another reverse sweep. Beaten this time
Rashid to Mitchell, 1 run,good length and pushed straight on at middle stump, gets deep in the crease and pushes to long-on
Rashid to Conway, 1 run,tossed up outside off, gets forward and drives to long-on
Rashid to Mitchell, 1 run,dropped short at middle stump, laboured pull out to deep midwicket
Rashid to Conway, 1 run,good length at middle stump, steps out and drags this drive out to long-on
Wood to Conway, no run,short of a length and climbing over off stump, steps out, gets leg side, chucks the hands at it, and misses
Wood to Conway, 1 run,short of a length and at the body, hauled down to fine leg

Wood to Mitchell, no run,bouncer at an off stump lines, looks for the hook and is beaten by pace. Buttler appeals for a catch behind and Morgan's interested for about five seconds before deciding not to review that
Wood to Mitchell, 1 run,short of a length and tight at off stump, makes room and slashes. Mistimes it out towards mid-off
Wood to Conway, 1 run,short of a length and skidding across middle stump at 150kph, squares him up and he can only drop this into the off side with soft hands
Wood to Mitchell, 2 runs,short and wide outside off, shuffles into line and flat-bats this to long-on....whose throw has deflected off the stumps to give them an extra run
Livingstone to Conway, no run,good length, dipping outside off, gripping and then turning past the sweep
Livingstone to Conway, 1 run,length and turning away outside off, reaches out and drives to sweeper cover with the turn
Livingstone to Mitchell, 1 run,switches to wristspin against the right-hander. Short of a length and skidding on straight in the corridor, hurried punch down towards long-on
Livingstone to Conway, 2 runs,length and just outside off. Steps out and looks to go over extra cover with the the turn, can't make the pitch of it and ends up slicing in front of sweeper
Livingstone to Conway, FOUR,well done. Good length and at the stumps, steps out and creams this half-volley, lofted over the bowler and well to long-off's left
Livingstone to Conway, no run,good length and at off stump, reverse sweep straight to backward point
Wood to Mitchell, FOUR,lumped back through the line! Mitchell loiters on the back foot and pans the length ball hard back through Wood's shins! Power
Wood to Mitchell, 1 run,attempted pull from a full length, rising into the hip but can't connect
Wood to Conway, (no ball) 1 leg bye,banged into the surface once more, Conway hops to work to leg, but can't connect... but it's a no-ball! England's first of the tournament...
Wood to Mitchell, 1 run,Wood does the basics right, hitting the pitch on the angle, and Mitchell's attempted pull finds only the splice
Wood to Conway, SIX,gives himself room, and clobbered violently over third man for six! That's pure flamboyance, climbing into the back-of-a-length ball at 140kph
Wood to Conway, 1 run,closes up the angle with good wheels, tucked to the leg side, but this is a big over for New Zealand as Wood's figures take a hit
Wood to Mitchell, no run,gets out of the over well, as Mitchell leans back for a ramp, but the short ball keeps following him, and passes through to the keeper
Livingstone to Conway, no run,fired onto a full length, outside off with the legbreak this time to the left-hander, his attempted sweep misses out
Livingstone to Conway, no run,poked to the off-side, good areas on the offbreak this time
Livingstone to Conway, 2 runs,a bottom-handed thump, up and over the leg side. One bounce to the midwicket sweeper. Tidy so far...
Livingstone to Conway, no run,crashed hard, met on the full but Livingstone does well with an outstretched hand in his followthrough to intercept
Livingstone to Conway, FOUR,lots of air outside off, and Conway chases this one with alacrity! Kneeling into the stroke, unleashing the levers, and crashed through extra cover

Livingstone to Conway, 1 run,tossed up, tempting the arc, but Conway's slog-sweep is slightly greedy as the ball bobbles out to the leg side. This is decent from Livingstone, he's keeping it tidy as England try to hide away their four overs of back-up spin
Rashid to Conway, 1 run,slow through the air, 82kph, dipping outside the left-hander's arc, and cuffed to the off side
Rashid to Mitchell, 1 leg bye,slow once more, that's a bit of a half-tracker truth be told, but Mitchell's eyes lit up like a jackpot in Vegas, and he nearly played on off his back thigh!
Rashid to Conway, 2 runs,tickled down the leg side, not quite placed to beat fine leg
Rashid to Conway, 1 run,attempted reverse sweep, but backward point is on hand to limit the damage. The rate creeps up to 11s

Rashid to Mitchell, SIX,tossed up, sliced high to long-off ... and Jordan saves six brilliantly inside the rope! Stunning work, timing his leap, stretching back, plucking the catch and dropping it back in play... but no! It's clipped the boundary triangle on the way down, and that's six after all!
Rashid to Mitchell, 1 run,tucked to the on-side for the single. New Zealand stay in touch with the rate
Livingstone to Mitchell, 1 run,over the wicket, looped onto a good length, nudged to the on-side
Livingstone to Conway, 2 runs,cuffed off a full length to the leg-side, gathered at long-on
Livingstone to Conway, no run,thumped off the back foot, and did that carry to Livingstone...? No, on the half-volley as he wrings his fingers in mild discomfort

Livingstone to Conway, OUT,dragged down the track, beaten by the lack of turn! Out of the front of the hand from Livingstone, Conway runs straight past it in his eagerness to get a move on, and Buttler flicks off the bails. A valiant hand, but a vital incision!

Livingstone to Phillips, 1 bye,so nearly skids into the stumps first ball! Full length, missed drive, Buttler misses it too and flicks off the bails, and New Zealand burgle a second as the shy goes wide at the non-striker's end

Livingstone to Mitchell, 1 run,worked to the off side, this is turning into a mighty night's work from Livingstone. No sign of Moeen, and I'm not sure England will turn to him at this rate. The sixth bowler is doing the business
Wood to Mitchell, 1 run,back of a length, another deck-hitting bomb outside off, and a flat slap to mid-off
Wood to Phillips, 1 run,on the back foot, tapped to cover, another sharp single but New Zealand need boundaries... it's at 12 an over now
Wood to Mitchell, 2 runs,outside off, on the full, sliced high down to third man. Gathered on the bounce. Three balls for Wood to complete a decent spell
Wood to Mitchell, FOUR,banged in short, well directed too, but Mitchell swings hard off the eyebrows, and the top-edge flies safe through fine leg!
Wood to Mitchell, 1 run,short, and angled into the body, a firm pull in the air to deep square leg, but can't beat the sweeper

Wood to Phillips, 1 run,goes full, attacking the stumps, hits the deck in his followthrough, but Phillips' drive is gathered with a tumble by Jordan. Wicketless from Wood, but he's done the needful through the middle overs

Livingstone to Phillips, OUT,tossed up on off stump, driven through the line, but it's a spiralling leading edge!. Billings sets himself at long-off, and makes no mistake! Huge wicket! Livingstone is dragging this contest England's way now...
Livingstone to Mitchell, no run,beauty! Tossed up again, and this legbreak grips, perhaps the first to do so all night. Buttler gathers as Mitchell misses
Livingstone to Mitchell, no run,attempted reverse sweep, thuds into Buttler's pads outside off. Outstanding bowling
Livingstone to Mitchell, no run,another dot as Mitchell swings at the wider one and misses
Livingstone to Mitchell, 1 run,tighter line, tucked to the on-side. This is a mighty over. Can he finish it?
Livingstone to Neesham, 1 wide,oops, overcooks it, down the leg-side.
Livingstone to Neesham, 1 run,slogged out of the fuller length, gathered at midwicket. Hats off Liam Livingstone, that was a spell and a half
Jordan to Neesham, SIX,round the wicket, in Neesham's arc, and pumped over midwicket! Every bit as smoked as his Super over six... that's travelled a big distance!
Jordan to Neesham, 2 leg byes,fired into the pads, leg-sided, but very full, and it takes the deflection to square leg. Buttler hurtles round, but not quick enough to cut off the second
Jordan to Neesham, 1 wide,fired down the leg side from round the wicket, Jordan is trying to stay out of his arc, but that's a poor ball
Jordan to Neesham, FOUR,it was the off-stump line, but that's been carted, hard through long-on! Neesham is giving New Zealand a vital leg-up here!
Jordan to Neesham, 1 wide,urgh... wide outside off. He's struggling to get out of this over ... Buttler is unamused... big balls coming up. In every sense!

Jordan to Neesham, SIX,slower ball ... hacked high into the leg side... is this the moment... Bairstow rushes round at long-on, clings on, relays the catch as he falls over the rope... but he's not convinced he's completed it! Yep, his knee has hit the rope, and that's another six! A Boult moment in reverse?!
Jordan to Neesham, 2 runs,pounded high through the line, same direction, less power... but Bairstow and Livingstone look at one another, and the ball plugs between both! Crumbs!
Jordan to Neesham, 1 run,better from Jordan, fired into the blockhole, and slapped behind square... another single. That's England's most expensive over of the tournament, and what a time for it!
Rashid to Neesham, no run,back of a length, bashed down the ground, could have been a single but the non-striker concedes that he impeded Rashid, and they turn it down
Rashid to Neesham, SIX,flambeed into the night sky! Down on one knee and mashed high onto the grass banks at midwicket!
Rashid to Neesham, 1 run,wrong'un, wide line, might have been called if it had been left... Morgan's shy goes wide, that would have been out!
Rashid to Mitchell, SIX,too short, and nailed high over long-on! That's power from Mitchell, rocking back on impact and lifting it high over the ropes! New Zealand are surging now!
Rashid to Mitchell, 1 run,outside off, back of a length, cuffed into the off side. Just a single to allow England some room to breathe...

Rashid to Neesham, OUT,back of a length, a slap from Neesham... straight at Morgan in the covers! Another googly, wide line, Neesham's weight was going the wrong way, Morgan juggles it but clings on. A lifeline from Rashid's final ball... but has he turned the game too far for New Zealand?
Woakes to Mitchell, 2 runs,slower ball, toe-ended inches out of Woakes' reach, past the stumps, and they hustle for the second
Woakes to Mitchell, SIX,slower ball again, and Mitchell makes no mistake! Rocking back, swinging lustily, up into the stroke, and over the ropes at long-on!
Woakes to Mitchell, SIX,too short, and that'll be the game for New Zealand now! Flogged with fury, big levers extending through the stroke, high over midwicket for an 86metre six!
Woakes to Mitchell, 1 run,another bouncer, flapped off the eyebrows, doesn't get hold of it... but it's safely short of square leg
Woakes to Santner, 1 run,it's in the slot for Santner to have a swing, out through the leg side, on the bounce to deep midwicket
Woakes to Mitchell, FOUR,full toss, clawed through backward square! And that's the game for New Zealand!
Mohammed Shami to Baard, 1 run,big outswinger from middle stump to start. At a length and squares him up as he closes the face on this, leading edge ends up at third man
Mohammed Shami to van Lingen, 1 wide,good length and down leg side, can't get the bat on that. Pant grabs one-handed to the right
Mohammed Shami to van Lingen, no run,good length and curved in at off and middle, punched on the rise towards the non-striker
Mohammed Shami to van Lingen, 1 run,short and wide just outside off, slashed to third man
Mohammed Shami to Baard, no run,good length and just outside off, driven on the rise, and on the bounce to Jadeja at backward point
Mohammed Shami to Baard, 1 leg bye,good length and into leg stump, looks to flick and cops that on the pad
Mohammed Shami to van Lingen, 1 run,short of a length and just outside off, stabbed on the up to cover's right
Bumrah to van Lingen, 1 leg bye,misfires the inswinging yorker, it's too full. Van Lingen is caught off guard, tries to slog this into the leg side and cops it on the pad just below the knee roll
Bumrah to Baard, 1 run,attempted yorker at off stump, gets forward and looks to drive. Thick inside edge onto boot
Bumrah to van Lingen, FOUR,another full toss and this one is put away. No swing on this, it sits up nicely in the corridor and he stands tall and pats this past his partner
Bumrah to van Lingen, no run,offcutter at a length just outside off, driven on the up to backward point
Bumrah to van Lingen, no run,good length and tight at middle stump, pushed to midwicket from the crease
Bumrah to van Lingen, FOUR,swiped away. It's an offcutter, short of a length at a middle and leg line. Sits up nicely for van Lingen and he waits on that and pulls off the front foot
Mohammed Shami to Baard, 1 wide,attempted yorker is sprayed down leg side, beaten on the flick
Mohammed Shami to Baard, no run,good length and just outside off, punched on the rise to mid-off

Mohammed Shami to Baard, SIX,oh gorgeous! Wow, Stephan Baard. Walks down the pitch, gets a short stride out and meets this full ball at a middle stump line before swishing it gloriously over the wide long-on boundary. Made a plan, and executed it beautifully. Lovely balance on that
Mohammed Shami to Baard, 2 runs,good length and into leg stump, gets forward and turns this through square leg
Mohammed Shami to Baard, 1 run,short of a length at middle stump, pulled out to deep square
Mohammed Shami to van Lingen, no run,yorker outside off, has a chop at it and is beaten
Mohammed Shami to van Lingen, no run,yorker outside off again, stays leg side of it and looks to drive. Beaten again
Ashwin to Baard, 1 run,short of a length outside off, punched to long-on off the back foot
Ashwin to van Lingen, no run,good length and tight at off stump, pushed into the covers
Ashwin to van Lingen, 2 runs,good length and at middle stump, steps out and this doesn't turn. Flat-bats it over the bowler but that isn't timed very well. Long-off cleans up
Ashwin to van Lingen, 1 run,good length and into leg stump, whipped through midwicket off the back foot
Ashwin to Baard, no run,good length and down leg side, shapes to reverse sweep and then lets it go. So the wide isn't given
Ashwin to Baard, 2 runs,good length at middle stump, waits on that and nudges it with soft hands in front of deep midwicket
Bumrah to van Lingen, 1 run,short of a length and into middle stump, hurriedly pushed to midwicket with the angle
Bumrah to Baard, no run,bouncer angled in from middle and off, ducks under that
Bumrah to Baard, 1 run,short and up at the ribs, pulled with the angle to fine leg's left
Bumrah to van Lingen, OUT,taken at mid-off! Short and rising outside off, but coming in with the angle from Bumrah around the wicket. He wants to flat-bat this over mid-off but ends up slicing it
Bumrah to Williams, no run,good length at off stump, defended off the back foot
Bumrah to Williams, no run,full and in at off stump, feet planted firmly on the crease as he has a stab at this. Ends up at mid-on off the inside half
Jadeja to Baard, 1 run,good length at off stump, driven with the turn to long-off
Jadeja to Williams, no run,length and tight at the stumps, pushed to midwicket

Jadeja to Williams, OUT,got him by a long way. Good length, flat, landing well before Williams can come anywhere close to the pitch of it after stepping out. It grips and turns away too as Williams has an ungainly swish at this. Pant gathers and takes a pause before flicking the bails off
Jadeja to Erasmus, no run,good length at off stump, defended on the front foot
Jadeja to Erasmus, no run,good length and tight at off stump, defended down the pitch
Jadeja to Erasmus, no run,good length at off stump, defended on the front foot

Chahar to Baard, no run,just short of Rohit diving to his left from slip, behind Pant. This was a legbreak down leg side, he was looking to sweep and it got big on him. Came off the spine of the bat and possibly also the glove to clear Pant and loop in front of Rohit
Chahar to Baard, no run,good length and turning away outside off, beaten on the drive
Chahar to Baard, 1 run,length outside off, swept along the floor to deep square
Chahar to Erasmus, no run,beats him in flight. Erasmus is shaping for a booming cover drive but Chahar has managed to dip that ball very quickly outside off before straightening it past the shot
Chahar to Erasmus, no run,googly, short of a length and turning in to the corridor, shapes to cut and check-punches it into the covers instead
Chahar to Erasmus, no run,good length and tight at off stump, defended off the back foot
Jadeja to Baard, no run,good length and sliding onto the stumps, backs away and drives back to the bowler

Jadeja to Baard, FOUR,oh lovely shot. Good length outside off, he shuffles to get inside the line of this, it gets big on him but he watches closely and then places the sweep between deep square and deep backward square
Jadeja to Baard, no run,full and just outside off, driven on the bounce to extra cover

Jadeja to Baard, OUT,big appeal for lbw and it is given. <strike>Erasmus</strike> Baard has reviewed but it isn't looking too good for him. This is an arm ball, good length and sliding on towards the stumps. Once again he shuffles to line up the sweep, but this time there's no room with the ball sliding in with the angle. He catches that on the thigh, right in front of middle stump. It's three reds on the review
Jadeja to Loftie-Eaton, 1 run,good length at the stumps, driven to long-off
Jadeja to Erasmus, 2 runs,top edge lands safely. Full ball at off stump, he's late in the decision to play the lap sweep and doesn't get too far down for it. Clears both keeper and slip
Chahar to Loftie-Eaton, 2 runs,good length at middle stump, gets forward and flicks to deep square's right
Chahar to Loftie-Eaton, 1 run,good length on off stump, pushed into the off side with soft hands. Pant sprints to his left and flicks that back form between his legs. They're safely through though
Chahar to Erasmus, no run,full and just outside off, driven firmly and on the bounce to extra cover
Chahar to Erasmus, 1 run,short of a length at middle stump, pulled out to deep midwicket
Chahar to Loftie-Eaton, 1 run,length at middle stump, flicked through midwicket
Chahar to Erasmus, no run,tossed up full and wide outside off, looks for a big sweep and misses as it turns away

Ashwin to Loftie-Eaton, OUT,straight to Rohit at slip. This is tossed up nicely outside off from around the wicket, pitching at a length and turning away. Some extra bounce too. Nicol Loftie-Eaton has a cut at that and gets a thick edge that goes loopily to Rohit
Ashwin to Wiese, 2 leg byes,starts with a flat one on the pads and is tickled to fine leg
Ashwin to Wiese, 1 run,good length probing at off stump, punched to deep point
Ashwin to Erasmus, 1 run,on the front foot to tap this softly towards point and there's no fielder there so they steal a quick single

Ashwin to Wiese, no run,beauty. Carrom ball completely beats him. Pitches on a length on off, and weise is playing inside the line, ends up feeling for it like a blind man with a stick as it spins past outside edge and off stump
Ashwin to Wiese, no run,full toss now, laced to cover, who makes a good diving stop to deny runs
Chahar to Erasmus, no run,tossed up on the stumps, slapped to cover
Chahar to Erasmus, 1 run,given air, wider line outside off, squirts it to deep point by reaching for it
Chahar to Wiese, 1 run,a bit flatter, still wide outside off, chopped through cover
Chahar to Erasmus, FOUR,bang. Drags it down too short, and Erasmus saw it early, rocked back and unleashed a fierce pull over deep midwicket
Chahar to Erasmus, 1 run,nice loop on a length on off, goes for the reverese sweep, doesn't get hold of it, gloved to short third man
Chahar to Wiese, FOUR,tossed up outside off, invites the big drive and Wiese goes for it but gets a thick outside edge only. Unfortunately for the bowler, there's no slip so it goes for four
Jadeja to Erasmus, 1 run,flat on a length on off, stays beside it and punches to point
Jadeja to Wiese, no run,fuller on the stumps, driven back to the bowler
Jadeja to Wiese, no run,stays beside the ball and cuts, but straight to backward point
Jadeja to Wiese, 2 runs,flattish into him, whipped off his toes, and that's been placed well at midwicket which allows a second run
Jadeja to Wiese, 1 run,length ball on off, punched through cover
Jadeja to Erasmus, 1 run,fuller but sliding on the pads, worked softly to square leg. No fielder there so Jadeja hares across so that they can't get a second
Ashwin to Erasmus, no run,down teh track, not quite to the pitch, looks to tuck it midwicket side but gets a leading edge. Cover dives to his left to stop it
Ashwin to Erasmus, no run,saw him coming down and bowled flatter and shorter outside off, jabbed back to the bowler
Ashwin to Erasmus, 5 wides,that one's gone down legside and Erasmus tries to sweep but doesn't connect - Pant can't collect either so it's five wides

Ashwin to Erasmus, OUT,and he's been caught behind. Don't think the length was there to cut, but that's the shot he went for, seemed to skid onto him a bit outside off and he gets a thin edge that sticks in Pant's gloves.
Ashwin to Smit, 1 run,length ball on a fifth stump line, pushed through point
Ashwin to Wiese, 3 runs,sliding on the pads for the second time in the over, and Wiese glances him fine. Sub fielder Ishan Kishan fumbles the take running to his right and allows a third
Ashwin to Smit, 1 run,a bit shorter outside off and cuts it to deep point
Chahar to Smit, no run,given some air, outside off, sliced towards short third man
Chahar to Smit, 1 run,tossed up very full, smacks the full toss to long-off
Chahar to Wiese, 1 run,length ball on off stump, punched through cover. Seemed to almost change his action a bit while delivering it, did Rahul Chahar
Chahar to Smit, 1 run,fuller outside off, pushed through cover

Chahar to Wiese, (no ball) FOUR,too short outside off and he stands tall to cut this through point. Uh oh, he's also over-stepped. This was another one with the run-up that starts from around the wicket but ends up over.
Chahar to Wiese, 1 run,can't nail the free hit, flatter and quicker into the pitch, swatted to long-on
Chahar to Smit, FOUR,tossed up wide of off-stump, he reaches for it to slap it, gets a thick top edge that flies over Rohit at slip and into the boundary
Jadeja to Wiese, 1 run,length ball on off, punched through cover
Jadeja to Smit, 1 run,darted into him, flicked off his pads through midwicket
Jadeja to Wiese, no run,fuller angled into him, jammed to cover. Quicker ball, he had to get bat down quickly
Jadeja to Wiese, 1 run,length ball on off, stays beside it to punch to deep point
Jadeja to Smit, no run,a mite more air on this, very full on the stumps, pushed back down the pitch

Jadeja to Smit, OUT,super catch by Rohit at cover. Got him driving early by slowing it up a bit and giving it a bit of air, Smit can't time the shot at all. Ball's dying on Rohit but he dives forward and to his right to pluck it
Ashwin to Wiese, no run,good length on middle and leg, tucked to short midwicket
Ashwin to Wiese, no run,beaten pushing forward, and the ball hits pad, but going down
Ashwin to Wiese, 1 run,punched to the man on the cover boundary

Ashwin to Green, OUT,castled. Lovely loop and turn on it, classic offspinner's dismissal. He's drawn half forward, the ball loops and dips on him like a sine curve, pitches and turns past the bat to hit stumps
Ashwin to Frylinck, 1 run,fuller, on off, pushed through cover
Ashwin to Wiese, no run,on the front foot to defend this length ball on off.
Bumrah to Frylinck, no run,good length angling across him, pokes at it and is beaten on the outside edge
Bumrah to Frylinck, no run,back of a length, still angling across, bunted back to the bowler
Bumrah to Frylinck, 2 runs,fuller on leg stumps, clipped off his boots through backward square leg
Bumrah to Frylinck, 4 leg byes,another leg stump yorker, he can't glance it fine but it does clip his pad and goes very fine, so that'll be four leg-byes
Bumrah to Frylinck, no run,sharp bouncer, dug in short and going across him, has to sway out of the way to let it pass
Bumrah to Frylinck, 1 run,good length outside off, punched through cover
Mohammed Shami to Frylinck, 1 run,full ball into him, just short of yorker length, flicked off his toes through square leg
Mohammed Shami to Wiese, 1 run,another full ball tagetting the blockhole, punched to long-on
Mohammed Shami to Frylinck, no run,dug in short outside off, very quick one, sways out of the way quickly

Mohammed Shami to Frylinck, 5 runs,four overthrows. Antoher full ball, this one was on off, he was on the front foot to tap towards point. They set off for a quick single. Jadeja the fielder and he's swooping in like a hawk, collects and has a shy at the striker's end in one fluid motion - happened too quickly for backing up and it's four. Would have been out with a direct hit
Mohammed Shami to Wiese, 3 runs,another good yorker but dealt with very well too, getting feet out of the way while losing balance a bit, but using that momentum to clip it through midwicket
Mohammed Shami to Frylinck, 2 runs,back of a length outside off, punched nicely through backward point to end a productive over - 12 off it.
Bumrah to Wiese, 1 run,another yorker tailing into him but Wiese is dealing well with those, getting front leg out of the way and getting bat down in time for flicks through midwicket
Bumrah to Frylinck, no run,bouncer on the stumps, he was backing away to make room, tries to cut it but can't connect
Bumrah to Frylinck, 1 wide,loses radar from round the wicket and goes down legside. Will have to rebowl that.

Bumrah to Frylinck, no run,bowler misses running out the batter. Yorkeron middle stump, he was making room, managed to make good contat with the drive. Bumrah sticks out his right hand and holds it, but Frylinck is well down the crease. Bumrah lines up the stumps and has a shy but must misses. Batter was miles down the track
Bumrah to Frylinck, 1 run,pushed to long-on

Bumrah to Wiese, OUT,slower ball does it. Wiese was taking a few steps down the track, but Bumrah not only yorks him again, but also with pace off. Wiese too early into his chip, goes off the toe end for a simple catch to extra cover
Bumrah to Frylinck, 2 runs,low full toss into him, whipped away through midwicket
Mohammed Shami to Trumpelmann, no run,length ball nipping into him, was looking to whip it but can't connect, wears it on the pads
Mohammed Shami to Trumpelmann, no run,dug in short outside off, goes for the pull, but connects only with air
Mohammed Shami to Trumpelmann, SIX,smoked. Shami missed his yorker, and Trumpelmann plants front foot down and swings it over long-on

Mohammed Shami to Trumpelmann, FOUR,great effort by Rahul at long-on but he can't hold on. Short ball outside off, sits up for him, he thumps a pull wide of long-on. Rahul runs to his right and dives, gets a hand to it on his right but can't stick
Mohammed Shami to Trumpelmann, 2 runs,full into him, squirted off the inside edge through square leg
Mohammed Shami to Trumpelmann, 1 run,full on off, flicked powerfully to square leg. Landed and spun away but Suryakumar sticks out his left hand and stops it to keep them to one
Trumpelmann to Rahul, 1 run,full inswinger at leg stump, gets forward and flicks to deep square
Trumpelmann to Sharma, no run,beats the outside edge. Full inswinger at off stump, gets forward to defend and that doesn't swing back in as much as he expects

Trumpelmann to Sharma, FOUR,dropped at short fine! Short of a length and curved into his hips. Whips with the angle and this dips to short fine's right. He lunges to his right and gets two hands on it, but tumbles over as the ball slips by. Van Lingen the man there
Trumpelmann to Sharma, 1 run,length at leg stump, clipped to deep square
Trumpelmann to Rahul, no run,good length at off stump, defended off the back foot
Trumpelmann to Rahul, no run,good length outside off, driven neatly on the rise to extra cover
Wiese to Sharma, no run,good length at leg stump, punched uppishly towards mid-on
Wiese to Sharma, no run,good length at off stump, defended down the pitch

Wiese to Sharma, FOUR,backs away and gets it over mid-off. Banged in short of a length and at middle stump. Makes room and carves from under this. It's off the high part of the bat but there's enough to find the boundary
Wiese to Sharma, no run,short of mid-on. Short of a length and rising up at rib height. Looks for the pull and gets it off the sticker of the bat, with one hand coming off as he looks to force it

Wiese to Sharma, SIX,sweeeet. Times on to perfection at last. Good length and into leg stump, gets low with a bent back knee and then uses the pace and angle of this to caress this over the fine leg boundary
Wiese to Sharma, 1 run,good length and just outside off, chopped down to third man
Trumpelmann to Sharma, FOUR,good length and rising across the corridor, looks to drive straight on the rise. It comes off the toe end but again there's enough to evade mid-off
Trumpelmann to Sharma, no run,full and tight at the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
Trumpelmann to Sharma, no run,just short of midwicket. Short and at middle stump, miscues a pull and ends up slicing it. Midwicket was already on the floor and lunging forward but was never making it
Trumpelmann to Sharma, 2 runs,chipped over midwicket. Good length and at the stumps, steps out and looks to clip that over midwicket but once again the timing isn't there

Trumpelmann to Sharma, 2 runs,short of a length at the stumps, splits his legs to make room and has a wild hack across the line of this. Comes off the inside part of the bat and trickles wide of midwicket. Long-on cuts it off though
Trumpelmann to Sharma, 1 run,short and at the chest, sweet sounding pull, firmly and straight to deep backward square on the bounce
Wiese to Sharma, 1 run,good length and at the stumps, waits on it and pushes towards mid-on

Wiese to Rahul, SIX,wow! Rahul's pick-up shots over the leg side generally go behind square, but this one's gone in the midwicket region. Pure balance this. Good length at middle stump, the only thing going for Rahul is the angle. He gets his bottom hand active and uses his wrists to sort...shovel...that
Wiese to Rahul, no run,good length and wide outside off, reaches out and mistimes the drive
Wiese to Rahul, no run,knuckle ball a length outside off, Rahul looks to lunge into that for the drive on the up, but that skids through from underneath
Wiese to Rahul, no run,length and into middle stump, looks to flick, closes the face too early. Leading edge to short third
Wiese to Rahul, no run,offcutter at a length just outside off, looks to force it through the covers off the back foot, it rolls down the pitch off the inside half

Scholtz to Sharma, no run,Scholtz comes on and reviews an lbw decision first up. It's a length ball at off stump, Rohit gets down for the sweep, trying to go behind square. He's caught that on the right bicep, in front of off stump or perhaps just outside it. Impact outside confirms tracker
Scholtz to Sharma, FOUR,short and wide outside off, waits on that, and slaps it on the rise through cover. Too much room there
Scholtz to Sharma, no run,good length at middle stump, defended on the front foot

Scholtz to Sharma, SIX,handsome, handsome. This is tossed up at leg stump, he steps out and is in danger of not reaching the pitch of this. So he has to lean in to get there and he does that and then just chips it over long-on using his body weight. Superb
Scholtz to Sharma, no run,tossed right up at off stump, clears the front leg and looks to bludgeon that over the leg side. Inside edge onto boot
Scholtz to Sharma, 1 run,good length and into leg stump, clipped through midwicket
Smit to Sharma, 1 run,full and into leg stump, flicked out to deep square

Smit to Rahul, FOUR,too easy if you bowl there. It's short of a length but there is too much width with this. And it is coming in with the angle. Rahul waits on that and punches late, on the up, and elegantly through cover
Smit to Rahul, 1 run,good length and into leg stump, flicked to deep midwicket
Smit to Sharma, 1 run,offcutter at a length on leg stump, steps out and turns that into the midwicket region off the thick inside edge

Smit to Rahul, 2 runs,just clears cover. Full slower ball wide outside off. Rahul wants to drill that over the extra cover boundary but hasn't picked the slower one. Ends up carving it and it plonks in the outfield
Smit to Rahul, 1 run,good length and into leg stump, flicked through square leg
Frylinck to Rahul, 1 run,good length and slower, at leg stump. Flicked through midwicket
Frylinck to Sharma, 1 run,good length at off stump, hangs deep in the crease and clips through square leg
Frylinck to Rahul, 1 run,slower ball at a length on middle stump, backs away and swings that on the bounce to deep midwicket
Frylinck to Sharma, 1 run,slower short ball at off stump, waits and waits before this controlled pull to short fine's left
Frylinck to Rahul, 1 run,slower ball at middle stump, waits on it and flicks down to long-on
Frylinck to Sharma, FOUR,slower ball, short, and slanted down leg side. Waits on it and uses the angle for an aerial pull past short fine
Smit to Rahul, 1 run,good length at middle and leg, punched to long-on off the front foot
Smit to Sharma, FOUR,good length and angled into leg stump from around the wicket. Stands his ground and uses the angle to nudge that past short fine
Smit to Sharma, no run,good length slower ball at off stump, looks to flick and gets an inside edge onto his thigh
Smit to Sharma, no run,full slower ball outside off, gets down on one knee to try and sweep this past short fine. Beaten
Smit to Sharma, 1 run,fifty for Rohit Sharma. It's a low full toss at leg stump, shuffles and reaches out before clipping this towards deep midwicket
Smit to Rahul, 1 run,full slower ball at leg stump, driven to long-on
Loftie-Eaton to Rahul, 1 run,good length at off stump, backs away and punches to long-off
Loftie-Eaton to Sharma, no run,yorker at leg stump, jammed down the pitch
Loftie-Eaton to Sharma, no run,yorker outside off, stays leg side of this and tries to chop it through cover, can't get it off the square
Loftie-Eaton to Sharma, FOUR,tossed up outside off, steps out and meets it at the pitch before pumping it over the bowler's head
Loftie-Eaton to Sharma, 1 run,full and at middle stump, driven down to long-on
Loftie-Eaton to Rahul, 1 run,full on off stump, driven with the turn to long-off
Frylinck to Rahul, 1 run,short of a length in the corridor, clears the front foot and pulls to deep midwicket
Frylinck to Sharma, 1 run,short and just outside off, chops to sweeper's left
Frylinck to Rahul, SIX,good length and angled into leg stump from around the wicket, stands still and only the arms move as he scoops this over short fine
Frylinck to Rahul, 1 run,short and just outside off, pulled to deep midwicket

Frylinck to Sharma, OUT,they have him at last. Full slower ball outside off, shuffles to get in line and looks for the old-fashioned slog over deep midwicket. The ball sticks in the pitch and straightens a touch and that is enough to induce the top edge. Hangs high in the point region and Green settles under it to complete the catch
Frylinck to Rahul, 1 run,length ball going across him, cuts it through point
Loftie-Eaton to Rahul, 1 run,dragged short, he goes back and pulls forward of square
Loftie-Eaton to Yadav, no run,good length o nthe stumps, on the front foot to defend back down the pitch

Loftie-Eaton to Yadav, 2 runs,good job by the man running to his left from deep point. This was tossed up well wide of off, Suryakumar skilfully reached it and steered it through backward point. Looked like four, but Baard sprinted hard to save it
Loftie-Eaton to Yadav, FOUR,regal. It's the Surya trademark inside out extra cover drive that is over the in-field. So languidly done.
Loftie-Eaton to Yadav, 1 run,this is slightly outside off and he uses wrists to loft over cover again but it's more square and there's a fielder there, so just one
Loftie-Eaton to Rahul, 1 run,flattish on middle and leg, pushed to long-on
van Lingen to Rahul, 1 run,length ball going across him, chopped through point

van Lingen to Yadav, 1 run,lovely shot but just one run. Length ball on middle and leg, stands tall and shows the full face of the bat to punch it back past the bowler. Reminiscent of another Mumbai batter, albeit one who was shorter and opened in white-ball cricket
van Lingen to Rahul, 2 runs,lovely timing again, punched through cover

van Lingen to Rahul, FOUR,wrists of steel by Rahul. If steel could be flexible without losing its strength. Overpitched on leg stump and he flicks it with a twirl of the wrists, one bounce into the square leg boundary
van Lingen to Rahul, 1 run,length ball going across on a fifth stump line, has to get a mite low but is in control of the cut shot. Short third man fumbles it a bit, that was well timed too
van Lingen to Yadav, no run,fuller outside off, driven to cover on the front foot
Loftie-Eaton to Rahul, 1 run,slightly short of a length outside off, waits on it and cuts in front of point

Loftie-Eaton to Yadav, FOUR,brings out another one of his favourites, the little dink to paddle-scoop it fine. Moved across early, fullish ball outside off and he picked it expertly to the fine leg boundary
Loftie-Eaton to Yadav, no run,fuller outside off, goes to sweep hard, gets a top edge onto helmet  that rolls towards gully
Loftie-Eaton to Yadav, no run,tossed up wider outside off, making him fetch the sweep, he tries but can't connect
Loftie-Eaton to Yadav, 1 run,length on off, comes on the front foot to drive to long-off
Loftie-Eaton to Rahul, no run,good length outside off, drawing him on the front foot, opens the face to steer to short third man
Trumpelmann to Yadav, 1 run,fuller outside off, squirted to deep point with a front foot drive
Trumpelmann to Rahul, FOUR,lovely straight drive, lofted over the bowler's head, and into the straight boundary. Bat turned in his hand a bit but he still timed it well
Trumpelmann to Rahul, 1 run,length ball coming into him, moves across and swivels to pull to fine leg. Came off the bottom half of the bat
Trumpelmann to Yadav, no run,sharp bouncer. SKY was moving across and Trumpelmann dug it in short, batter had to drop his hands and forego the pull shot
Trumpelmann to Yadav, FOUR,dismissed. Slower ball, too short outside off, he rocks back and whacks it across the line, pulling powerfully to the deep midwicket boundary
Trumpelmann to Yadav, 1 run,another good short ball, this time SKY goes for the pull, gets a top edge with the ball near throat height, but it lands safely, well short of deep square leg
Loftie-Eaton to Yadav, FOUR,tossed up outside off, and he's opened the face to drive it through point. Great timing on it again
Loftie-Eaton to Yadav, no run,gets some drift into the batter, who's looking to drive inside out. Ball hits pad
Loftie-Eaton to Yadav, 1 run,fuller, driven to long-off
Loftie-Eaton to Rahul, 2 runs,too short, rocks back to pull, not quite timed perfectly though it's in the gap between long-on and deep midwicket, so they get two
Loftie-Eaton to Rahul, 1 run,fuller on the stumps, driven to long-on to raise fifty for Rahul. Another typically pretty innings, full of great strokeplay
Loftie-Eaton to Yadav, 1 run,full toss on the stumps, thumped through cover
van Lingen to Yadav, 1 leg bye,back of a length on leg stump, looks to flick it, rolls off pads to short fine leg. Scores level.
van Lingen to Rahul, FOUR,back of a length outside off, stands back and punches this past mid-off and into the boundary to close out the win.
Hamza Tahir to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,tossed up wide, and crunched into the covers
Hamza Tahir to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,danced down the ground and nearly ended up yorking himself
Hamza Tahir to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,goes across the stumps to try and swipe it over midwicket. Swing and a miss
Hamza Tahir to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,darted back into Rizwan, who defends
Hamza Tahir to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,reached for it from outside off and swept it to square leg. Wanted to come back for two but a little slip put paid to any chances of that
Hamza Tahir to Babar Azam, no run,thick inside edge onto the pad. Good start for Hamza, and Scotland
Wheal to Mohammad Rizwan, 2 runs,a touch too straight, allowing Rizwan to bunt it into the onside and circle back for two
Wheal to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,drags length back, and Rizwan defends
Wheal to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,stayed a little low on him, but he manages to get it to mid-off and rotate the strike
Wheal to Babar Azam, 1 run,gets off the mark with a little checked drive to cover
Wheal to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,clipped nicely over the infield on the leg side, and now Rizwan has more T20 runs this year than any other player in a calendar year, eclipsing Chris Gayle in 2015
Wheal to Babar Azam, 1 run,runs it down to third man
Sharif to Babar Azam, no run,little chip into the onside
Sharif to Babar Azam, 1 run,driven into the offside
Sharif to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,oh, is that dropped? Clipped to fine leg in the circle, oh no, it's well short! I need specs
Sharif to Babar Azam, no run,good-looking drive to mid-off
Sharif to Babar Azam, FOUR,gorgeous! No one's stopping that. A touch of width and a shade too full. Babar leans into it and times it through the cover region
Sharif to Babar Azam, 1 run,smart little flick to midwicket as Babar keeps the strike
Watt to Babar Azam, 1 wide,dragged down legside
Watt to Babar Azam, 1 wide,another little drag-down by Watt
Watt to Babar Azam, no run,punched to deep cover
Watt to Babar Azam, 1 wide,darted it in but he needs to find his radar. That's his third wide in four balls
Watt to Babar Azam, no run,clipped to deep midwicket
Watt to Babar Azam, no run,tried to heave it over extra cover but gets a thick inside edge. Watt gives you nothing to work with
Watt to Babar Azam, no run,wicket-to-wicket, driven back to him
Watt to Babar Azam, 1 run,dropped! Smashed back to Watt, absolutely nailed. Seems to have hurt his hand as that ball smashes into the thumb and popped out
Watt to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,yorker length, defended back to him. Great over despite the extras
Wheal to Babar Azam, 2 runs,no timing, Babar scooped it into the air. Mid-on had to get his skates on if he was to race back and catch it, but it falls well in front of Sharif in the end
Wheal to Babar Azam, FOUR,lovely pick-up and deposited over wide midwicket for a boundary. Babar read the line so early there and knew exactly what he wanted to do
Wheal to Babar Azam, 1 run,he Kanes it down to third man. That's what that run-down to third man should be called

Wheal to Mohammad Rizwan, SIX,oh, isn't that's majestic! The head goes across the arm speed is frightening and he jabs it over cow corner for a colossal six That is a region he enjoys scoring in so much
Wheal to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,good comeback. Yorker that's defended back to Wheal. He saw Rizwan lurking outside his crease and the shy at the stumps had the batter diving
Wheal to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,dragged down the legside, he should have put it away past fine leg but misses out
Sharif to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,danced down the ground but he sends it wide
Sharif to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,turns it round the corner to square leg
Sharif to Babar Azam, 1 run,runs it down to third man
Sharif to Mohammad Rizwan, no run,took the pace off and went wide, Rizwan couldn't quite get bat on it. Wry smile from the little man
Sharif to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run,whipped round to long-on and the pair exchange ends
Sharif to Babar Azam, no run,took a little walk down the ground - Hayden would approve - but the bowler bangs it in short and fetches himself a dot ball to round out the over. Smart cricket

Hamza Tahir to Mohammad Rizwan, OUT,he's got Rizwan, has Hamza! He bowled a good first over and tossed it out wide again, drawing Rizwan to the offside, but he only manages a little under-edge the keeper nabs on to!
Hamza Tahir to Fakhar Zaman, no run,comes around the wicket, defended into the onside
Hamza Tahir to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,rushed it through flat
Hamza Tahir to Babar Azam, 1 run,eased down the ground
Hamza Tahir to Fakhar Zaman, no run,pushed him back, defended back to the bowler
Hamza Tahir to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,skipped down the ground but couldn't quite get underneath it
Berrington to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,nudged down to long-on
Berrington to Babar Azam, 2 runs,little wristy flick to wide long-on and they ease back for a couple
Berrington to Babar Azam, 1 run,driven back down the ground
Berrington to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,poked to mid-off and scampers through for a single; a direct hit would have made it interesting
Berrington to Babar Azam, 1 wide,dragged down legside
Berrington to Babar Azam, 1 run,works it away to long-on for a single
Berrington to Fakhar Zaman, no run,straight drive clatters into the stumps, which means he ends with a dot ball
Watt to Babar Azam, SIX,it's onto the roof! Babar going through the gears now. Watt pitches this one right in the arc, and Babar gets down on one knee and blisters it over cow corner
Watt to Babar Azam, 2 leg byes,little flick off the pads after Watt darted it through
Watt to Babar Azam, 1 run,driven to long-off
Watt to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,eased to long-on
Watt to Babar Azam, 1 run,slashed to sweeper cover
Watt to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run,low full toss, squeezed to the onside
Greaves to Fakhar Zaman, 2 runs,wide, forcing Fakhar to reach for it and guide it to deep point
Greaves to Fakhar Zaman, no run,sliced to backward point
Greaves to Fakhar Zaman, no run,misses out, smashes it straight to Coetzer at backward point again

Greaves to Fakhar Zaman, OUT,and that's Fakhar Zaman done for! He hasn't really shone through the five games so far, and this time tried to reach for it and clobber it over cow corner, only to pick out Michael Leask perfectly
Greaves to Mohammad Hafeez, no run,darted into him on the stumps, makes room and punches to cover
Greaves to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run,strays on the pads and is flicked through midwicket
Hamza Tahir to Mohammad Hafeez, no run,full ball outside off, tapped to cover
Hamza Tahir to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run,tossed up from a bit wider of the stumps, full on off, driven through cover
Hamza Tahir to Babar Azam, no run,going very wide of the crease is Hamza and angling them in, this is patted back to the bowler
Hamza Tahir to Babar Azam, 1 run,has a good old heave at this one outside off, gets it off the bottom half of the bat through midwicket

Hamza Tahir to Mohammad Hafeez, 2 runs,down the track, gets to the pitch but can't quite time it perfectly and the ball runs through midwicket off the inside half of the bat. He was looking to loft it straighter I think

Hamza Tahir to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR,nails the straight drive this time. down the track again, gets to the pitch with nifty footwork and swings it clean over the bowler's head and into the straight boundary
Greaves to Babar Azam, FOUR,dragged too short and he's read the length quickly, gone down on his knee and swept hard through a vacant backward square leg area
Greaves to Babar Azam, 1 run,fuller, given more air, drifts a bit inwards too, Babar on the front foot to work this through square

Greaves to Mohammad Hafeez, no run,googly, but too short, whipped off his pads to short fine leg. Looking for single and sent back as the throw comes in and the keeper takes off the bails, but Hafeez has just about made it. A better throw, flat and straight to the keeper, would have been tight
Greaves to Mohammad Hafeez, no run,short again, punched but can't beat point
Greaves to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run,fuller into him, chipped almost casually towards long-on. Bounces well in front of the man
Greaves to Babar Azam, 1 run,drags it short again and Babar gets into position to control his pull shot well, but there's a deep midwicket in place so it's only a single
Watt to Babar Azam, no run,darted into him on a length, misses the flick and is struck on the pads, going well down leg
Watt to Babar Azam, 1 wide,that one's too far outside off, he'll have to rebowl that
Watt to Babar Azam, FOUR,smashed. Marginally shorter and he latches onto that with a fierce pull shot that bisects long-on and deep midwicket. Went like a rocket.

Watt to Babar Azam, FOUR,and after the power, there's the touch. Tossed up wide yorker on a sixth stump line, babar just gets his bat down horizontal and along the pitch to steer it through backward point. Lovely.
Watt to Babar Azam, 1 run,fuller on the stumps, on the front foot to flick off his toes through midwicket
Watt to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run,full toss on off stump, pushed to long-off
Watt to Babar Azam, 1 run,good length on off, he's on the front foot to work it through midwicket
Berrington to Babar Azam, 1 wide,slower ball but loses control of it and slides down leg. Wide. Batter was looking to sweep but can't connect
Berrington to Babar Azam, 1 run,yorker on a fifth stump line, swung across the line in a wide long-on direction
Berrington to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR,shot. Wandered down the track and creamed a cover drive, not keeping it down, over the in-field and into the boundary
Berrington to Mohammad Hafeez, 2 runs,this is an even better shot but Leask has made good ground to his right to stop it at the cover boundary. Went inside out again, using wrists dextrously
Berrington to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run,fuller outside off, steered to short third man. Fumble by the man allows a single
Berrington to Babar Azam, 1 run,good length on the stumps, turned through midwicket
Berrington to Mohammad Hafeez, no run,good length close to off stump, glided to short third man
Sharif to Babar Azam, 1 leg bye,good length nipping into him and ends up on the pads, tries to flick it but it takes the pad and rolls towards short leg

Sharif to Mohammad Hafeez, SIX,that one's outta here. It'll need a travel agent to find it's way back to the stadium. Slower ball full on off, in the slot for Hafeez to bring out a magnificent golf swing of the bat that sends it way over long-on
Sharif to Mohammad Hafeez, no run,beaten outside off. Back of a length, looked to pull but beaten by the pace being taken off the ball

Sharif to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR,gorgeous. Hafeez was making a bit of room and Sharif bowled it wide outside off, but he just stretches the bat out with magnificent timing and carves it over cover for four

Sharif to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR,the Professor is 'taking class' as they say. Too full, sliding down leg and a powerful flick to the square leg boundary. There's fielders there but Hafeez is timing them so well they have no chance

Sharif to Mohammad Hafeez, OUT,rapped in front by one that has come back in but Hafeez will review. Great comeback by Sharif, who bowled an off-cutter on a length. Hafeez looking to pull it from Sharjah to Dubai, misses it completely. And it's three reds so Hafeez's sparkling innings has ended. Scotland needed that wicket.

Hamza Tahir to Babar Azam, 1 run,down the track, Tahir bowls it into him but he works it off his pads through the legside to raise yet another fifty</>. Possibly not at the pace that is required, but you can't argue with the prettiness of any Babar innings.
Hamza Tahir to Shoaib Malik, 1 run,length ball well outside off, cuts it through point
Hamza Tahir to Babar Azam, SIX,boom. Down the track, gets to the pitch and belts the cover off the ball with a flat six over long-on
Hamza Tahir to Babar Azam, 1 run,length ball outside off, cuts through point
Hamza Tahir to Shoaib Malik, 2 runs,drags it short, Malik swivels a long way to pull to deep square leg
Hamza Tahir to Shoaib Malik, 1 run,dragged short again, Malik pulls hard again but this time straight to the deep square leg fielder, who collects on the bounce
Watt to Shoaib Malik, 1 run,goes wide of the crease and angles it into the batter, who whips it off his toes to long-on
Watt to Babar Azam, no run,good ball, yorker on middle stump and Babar can only defend it

Watt to Babar Azam, 1 run,cleverly bowled, saw him dancing down the track and bowled it fast and flat, very wide outside off. If Babar missed, it was a stumping chance but he stretches out and slaps it through point
Watt to Shoaib Malik, SIX,that is some bottom-hand power by Malik. Tossed up outside off, he had his weight back, got his front knee down and unfurled a huge on-drive that carries over the ropes
Watt to Shoaib Malik, 1 run,full toss on the stumps, yorker gone wrong, Malik blasts it across the line but there's a fielder right there on the midwicket boundary

Watt to Babar Azam, SIX,just over the fingertips of long-on. Can't really call it a catch, he did well to leap up and get any touch on the ball at all. This was flatter but Babar makes a bit of room and hammers another flat lofted on-drive and gets it all the way
Greaves to Shoaib Malik, 1 run,punched to long-on
Greaves to Babar Azam, 2 runs,dragged shorter, Babar loses his shape while trying to slog sweep, one hand comes off the bat, and the ball bounces to deep square leg. They hustle hard and get two

Greaves to Babar Azam, OUT,holes out to long-on. Wasn't quite short enough to pull, Babar went for it anyway, got it higher on the bat and the ball just loops up in the air and drops safely into the hands of the fielder stationed at a slightly wide long-on.

Greaves to Shoaib Malik, 2 runs,too short, Malik pulls hard, more power than timing, but the placement is good and they can run back for two with the fielder at deep midwicket having to run to his right to stop it
Greaves to Shoaib Malik, 2 runs,good running again. Length ball coming into him, pats it softly through midwicket. Man is right back on the boundary so they can get two
Greaves to Shoaib Malik, no run,good length and quicker one, pushed back to the bowler
Sharif to Asif Ali, 1 run,full ball angling into him, punches an on-drive to deep midwicket
Sharif to Shoaib Malik, 2 runs,good ball, yorker length on a fifth stump line, swung across the line, gets a thick bottom edge to deep midwicket
Sharif to Shoaib Malik, SIX,bang. Malik's gone downtown on this. Another full ball, Malik deep in his crease and has a big swing of the bat to send this over deep midwicket
Sharif to Shoaib Malik, 1 run,yorker outside off, driven to cover

Sharif to Asif Ali, 1 run,good bowling by Sharif. Took the pace off and kept it wide outside off on a yorker length, Asif can only swat it back past the bowler with a horizontal bat. No timing on it so long-off cleans up

Sharif to Shoaib Malik, SIX,blasted over the long-on boundary low and flat. Full again, Malik goes deep in his crease again and uses all his power to hit this. The man at long-on is a bit wide, he's running to his left with hand outstretched but can't reach the ball. Maybe a good thing - could have done some damage with how hard it was hit. More power than timing on it.
Greaves to Asif Ali, 2 runs,shorter on off, with pace off, pulled to deep midwicket
Greaves to Asif Ali, 1 run,dug into the pitch back of a length, he was skipping down the track, slaps it through cover

Greaves to Shoaib Malik, SIX,dug into the pitch again but Malik has been expecting that, so he's hanging on the back foot, rocks back further and unleashes violence on the ball, pulling it over deep backward square leg
Greaves to Shoaib Malik, FOUR,and this is not as short but Malik is in unstoppable form. Swats a pull in front of square this time, flat and hard, hit so powerfully that no fielder has a chance

Greaves to Shoaib Malik, SIX,Malik is on fire. Was hanging back first ball, stayed more sitll second, comes down the track third ball and deposits it over long-on with another powerful swing of the bat
Greaves to Shoaib Malik, 1 wide,and the pressure tells on the bowler as he bowls it well down legside for a wide

Greaves to Shoaib Malik, SIX,short ball again and Malik has rocked on to the back foot and dealt with the ball as if he has personal enmity with it. Another one that's had the leather belted off it, pulls it way over midwicket and raises an 18-ball fifty with a last-ball six. Whew.
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munsey, no run,rapped on the pads, but the umpire turns him down, possibly because he felt it was going down
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munsey, no run,full, arrowing into the stumps. Munsey digs it out
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munsey, 1 wide,sends this one down legside. Rizwan claimed it flicked the pad
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munsey, no run,banged into the surface, defended to the offside
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munsey, FOUR,squeezed this out from underneath the bat and drove it uppishly past mid-off. Babar didn't seem to see at at mid-off and was late to react
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munsey, no run,driven to cover
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munsey, no run,crunched to mid-off to conclude the over
Imad Wasim to Coetzer, no run,darts it in towards the stumps, he defends off the back foot
Imad Wasim to Coetzer, no run,skidded on, Coetzer tried to chop it through cover, missed
Imad Wasim to Coetzer, FOUR,comes forward to slash it past extra cover, and gets himself off the mark with a boundary
Imad Wasim to Coetzer, no run,rushes it through again at 99kph. Coetzer looked to make room but had none to play with
Imad Wasim to Coetzer, 1 run,looked to hoick it over the off side but manages an edged single down the ground
Imad Wasim to Munsey, 1 run,skids it in at 102 kph, Munsey keeps the strike
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munsey, 1 wide,that one's well down legside, and definitely a wide
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munsey, 1 no ball,took the pace off slightly, defended to the offside - and it's a no-ball. Shaheen has overstepped
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munsey, 1 run,full, he went deep in his crease but the pace - 149 kph - meant he could only get it down to mid-on.
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Coetzer, no run,nasty pace! Bounced it into the ground at full pelt and sent the Scottish captain ducking for cover
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Coetzer, 1 run,went through the shot too quickly, 127 kph, and Coetzer toe-ended it into a vacant region around midwicket
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munsey, FOUR,makes room and places one exquisitely through cover for four. That's the best shot of the evening, and Scotland continue to pick up a boundary an over
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munsey, no run,yorker angling into leg stump, tucks him up brilliantly
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munsey, no run,clattered to mid-off. Connected well but sends it straight to Babar Azam
Imad Wasim to Coetzer, no run,tried to step away from it but found himself tucked up
Imad Wasim to Coetzer, no run,underedges it down to fine leg
Imad Wasim to Coetzer, no run,darts it in at 100 kph again, swing and a miss
Imad Wasim to Coetzer, 1 run,tries to give himself room and Imad just follows him. Just a single to square leg
Imad Wasim to Munsey, no run,reverse sweep and a miss. Clever work from Imad to send it down legside and Rizwan collects smartly
Imad Wasim to Munsey, no run,ends the second straight over with a smash down to mid-off
Haris Rauf to Coetzer, 1 run,starts off with one at 140 kph that's timed well to deep square
Haris Rauf to Munsey, no run,rapped on the pads after it lands outside leg, but has that ever stopped Rauf from bellowing for an lbw decision?
Haris Rauf to Munsey, 1 run,gorgeous drive which deserved four but gets just one. Smashes into the stumps at the non-striker's end. Haris and Munsey exchange a snigger
Haris Rauf to Coetzer, 1 run,took the pace off that one (128kph), forcing Coetzer to check his shot and chip it into the onside
Haris Rauf to Munsey, no run,tried to slash it over backward point but at 147 kph, the ball bounces over the bat
Haris Rauf to Munsey, no run,141 kph bouncer. Watertight start to Rauf's spell
Hasan Ali to Coetzer, no run,a little clip into the onside - Pakistan have kept Scotland very quiet thus far
Hasan Ali to Coetzer, no run,slower ball beats him all ends up, he was well through his shot by the time it trickled through to him and then onwards to the keeper

Hasan Ali to Coetzer, OUT,cleans him up - Hasan has his first! Real battle for Coetzer, this innings, just 9 off 16 balls, and you sensed something had to give. Went for the slog over the top again, while Hasan's slower ball was arrowing into off-stump
Hasan Ali to Cross, no run,watchful defensive shot to begin
Hasan Ali to Cross, 1 leg bye,rapped on the pads, it was really tailing back in. Hasan implored the umpire for a favourable decision but it might have been heading down, or even over the stumps
Hasan Ali to Munsey, no run,slower ball to end the over, and a Powerplay over which Pakistan have enjoyed a vice-like grip
Shadab Khan to Cross, no run,a little extra bounce does for the batter
Shadab Khan to Cross, 1 run,swept in front of the stumps; looked a bit of an lbw candidate but manages to get it away
Shadab Khan to Munsey, 1 run,think that was a topspinner, edges it away to short third
Shadab Khan to Cross, 1 bye,attempted to smear it over midwicket, but that was the googly. Misses the leg stump by a whisker, and Shadab has hands on head
Shadab Khan to Munsey, 1 run,worked through the offside
Shadab Khan to Cross, 2 runs,eased through the covers and the pair circle back for a couple
Imad Wasim to Munsey, no run,driven back to the bowler
Imad Wasim to Munsey, 1 wide,flights this one and sends it wide of off stump
Imad Wasim to Munsey, 1 wide,and this one's wide down leg side; Rizwan does well to collect it
Imad Wasim to Munsey, 1 run,rushes it through flat and carves it past cover
Imad Wasim to Cross, 1 run,this one's bowled slower. Cross clips it into the vacant midwicket/square leg region
Imad Wasim to Munsey, 1 run,eased through the offside
Imad Wasim to Cross, 1 run,chipped down to long-off

Imad Wasim to Munsey, OUT,smashed down the ground, and Imad effects a run-out at the non-striker's end. That's unfortunate for the Scots, but Cross had wandered down the crease slightly, and when the drive was clattered back, Imad made sure to get a hand to it on its way through.
Shadab Khan to Berrington, no run,defended back to Shadab Khan
Shadab Khan to Berrington, no run,this is the wrong'un. Defended
Shadab Khan to Berrington, no run,so unlucky not to pick up a wicket. The perfect googly which outfoxed Berrington all ends up, but also misses off stump, just
Shadab Khan to Berrington, 1 run,reached for it and swept it from well outside off. Playing with a horizontal bat to take the spin out of the equation
Shadab Khan to Munsey, no run,defended back to Shadab, who collects smartly
Shadab Khan to Munsey, no run,clipped on the pads, and that ends another masterful over from Shadab
Imad Wasim to Berrington, 1 run,tosses it up, driven to the offside
Imad Wasim to Munsey, no run,bit of a long hop; he tried to pull in front of square but only got the inside edge
Imad Wasim to Munsey, 1 run,worked into the onside
Imad Wasim to Berrington, no run,made room and tried to slash through the offside. Again, misses the off stump by a couple of centimetres
Imad Wasim to Berrington, 1 run,driven to wide long-on

Imad Wasim to Munsey, 1 run,eased to long-on and Imad's done. 4-0-17-0, and a very clever run-out. Decent evening's work he's done. Less stellar from me, but that's my comms stint done too, with Saurabh to pick it up from here
Shadab Khan to Munsey, OUT,he's gone first ball after drinks. Given some air outside off, he makes room to crash it through off but skewers it off the outside edge to short third man
Shadab Khan to Budge, no run,length outside off, cut to point

Shadab Khan to Budge, OUT,castled. Nice loop on the ball, drifting into him and dipping, he's looking to whip it through midwicket, but is beaten by the googly, and the ball thuds into stumps off his pads
Shadab Khan to Leask, no run,good length leg-break outside off, lets it go
Shadab Khan to Leask, 1 run,length ball on off, pushed to cover
Shadab Khan to Berrington, 1 run,flatter and fuller on off, allows him to reach out and sweep to deep square leg
Hasan Ali to Berrington, 2 runs,full ball tailing into him, clipped off his toes through midwicket
Hasan Ali to Berrington, (no ball) 1 run,length outside off, punched through cover
Hasan Ali to Leask, no run,swing and a miss. Hard length on a fifth stump line, he was looking to send it to cow corner, can't connect

Hasan Ali to Leask, 1 run,back of a length outside off, cuts it nicely from close to body to deep point. Bit of a mix up with Leask looking for the second but sent back, just in time to make it safely back before ball comes back
Hasan Ali to Berrington, 1 wide,loses his radar on this slower bouncer and sends it way down legside
Hasan Ali to Berrington, FOUR,super shot. Danced down the track and slapped this length ball on off over extra cover
Hasan Ali to Berrington, 2 runs,full toss on off, swiped through midwicket
Hasan Ali to Berrington, FOUR,and he's got hold of that nicely, powerfully whipped through midwicket to find the boundary
Shadab Khan to Leask, no run,tossed up leg break on a sixth stump line, swings hard at it aiming a drive, can't connect
Shadab Khan to Leask, no run,beaten by a beauty. Dips and turns past the bat on a length on off as he's looking to drive
Shadab Khan to Leask, no run,slightly quicker, pushed back to the bowler
Shadab Khan to Leask, FOUR,tossed up too much, ends up a full toss and he smacks it to the midwicket boundary
Shadab Khan to Leask, 1 run,down the track, bowler saw him and shortened the length a bit, and he manages to work it off pads in front of square
