Shadab Khan to Berrington, 1 run,stays back to this and clips it through midwicket
Haris Rauf to Berrington, 1 run,good length on off, cross-batted slap to mid-off
Haris Rauf to Leask, FOUR,makes room and thrashes this back of a length ball outside off through cover.
Haris Rauf to Leask, 1 run,full toss on leg stump, making room again, swats it to long-on
Haris Rauf to Berrington, 1 run,digs it into the pitch, pulled through the backward square leg area

Haris Rauf to Leask, 1 run,backing away again, Rauf follows him with a bouncer, so he has to modify his pull shot into something resembling an overhead tennis smash which he's not in control of. Shaheen at deep midwicket stays still and collects on the bounce
Haris Rauf to Berrington, 2 runs,another full toss, on the pads, whipped through midwicket
Hasan Ali to Leask, 1 run,short outside off, fetches the pull and hits it towards wide long-on
Hasan Ali to Berrington, no run,yorker on off stump, dug back out to the bowler, who fields and makes as if to shy at the stumps, drawing a reflex evasion from the batter
Hasan Ali to Berrington, 2 runs,he's doing very well with those heaves into the legside fetched from outside off. Another one that's hit to the deep midwicket region, from a full ball outside off
Hasan Ali to Berrington, 2 runs,ack of a length into him, pulled off the bottom half of the bat to short fine leg
Hasan Ali to Berrington, no run,back of a length in the channel, angling in, he looks to swipe across the line again but ball goes under bat
Hasan Ali to Berrington, 1 run,full on a fourth stump line, swung to deep midwicket
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Berrington, 1 wide,full ball down leg, too far away to connect with his flick. He'll have to re-bowl that.
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Berrington, no run,pacy off-cutter back of a length on leg stump, jagging across, he's beaten on the swat across the line

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Berrington, FOUR,angling across him in the channel on a length, goes for a big drive, gets a thick edge that flies past Rizwan to his right. He had no chance of getting there even with a dive.
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Berrington, 1 run,making room, opens the face to drive this full ball to third man

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Leask, OUT,stumps shattered. They've been backing away to make room against Shaheen's full, fast ones, but this one is a bit too quick, and he's late on the attempted thrash through off, by which time the stumps have been re-arranged by a Shaheen special.
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Greaves, no run,beaten on the outside edge, as this goes across him. Was looking to steer it away
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Greaves, no run,good length angling in, beaten on the punch again, but the ball whistles past the stumps
Haris Rauf to Berrington, 2 runs,slower ball, full on off, whips it in the air to deep midwicket. Bit sloppy from Pakistan to allow an overthrow
Haris Rauf to Berrington, FOUR,shot. Angling into him at pace, he uses that pace to sweep it hard and fine through backward square leg
Haris Rauf to Berrington, 1 run,length ball on off, at full pace, pulls through square leg. Not timed, came off the bottom half of the bat
Haris Rauf to Greaves, 1 run,full and fast into him, tapped to cover

Haris Rauf to Berrington, no run,slower yorker dipping on him, he misses the flick and is struck on the pads. Rauf appeals, not given, so Pakistan are reviewing. Very well bowled but that's probably heading down leg. In fact it's pitched outside leg too and is going further down.

Haris Rauf to Berrington, 2 runs,another slower ball, this time he connects with the short-arm jab sweep, hits it off the top edge though. But it's landing safely between deep square leg and deep midwicket

Hasan Ali to Greaves, no run,gone through him. Back of a length angling into him, and he's had a poke at it, but it goes between bat and body. Might have had a thin inside edge too. Rizwan takes it and appeals. Umpires checking if the catch is clean</>. Soft signal is not out. And yes, it's bounced just in front of Rizwan's gloves. He immediately signalled after his appeal that he wasn't sure if it carried. It was dipping on Rizwan forward to his left and he did well to get to it.
Hasan Ali to Greaves, 1 run,length ball into the pads, tucked to midwicket
Hasan Ali to Berrington, no run,back of a length on the stumps, tapped back down the pitch
Hasan Ali to Berrington, SIX,smoked. Slower one in the slot on off, he picked it up early and got his weight forward and swung through the line to deposit it over long-on
Hasan Ali to Berrington, 2 runs,slides on the pads with this one, and is glanced through backward square leg

Hasan Ali to Berrington, 2 runs,made him reach for it, bowling wide outside off, Berrington throws his bat at it and carves it over cover, raises a really good fifty. He's got it in just 34 balls too, and while wickets were falling all around him, against a high-quality attack.
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Greaves, no run,walks way across his stumps to try and scoop it. can't connect and the ball goes just past the off stump
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Greaves, 1 run,yorker on middle stump but he was making room so can carve it through point
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Berrington, 1 run,near-yorker, dipping on him on middle, ends up as a very low full toss, squirted to fine leg
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Greaves, no run,another yorker, tihs one on a fifth stump line. Batter can't connect with the drive

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Greaves, 1 no ball,slower ball does him. Oh no it doesn't, because he's overstepped. The length remains the same, yorker on the stumps, he's too early into his punch and chips it tamely in the air to mid-off. But no wicket because it's a no-ball.
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Berrington, 1 run,length ball on off, mis-timed punch to mid-off

Shaheen Shah Afridi to Greaves, 1 run,another slower ball yorker, this one outside off, he adjust his drive a bit and doesn't spoon a catch but it's not timed at all, goes to mid-off. Babar fumbles a bit so they are not in danger while running a quick single
Haris Rauf to Greaves, 1 wide,loses his radar, goes well down legside. Batter was shaping to scoop but can't reach it.
Haris Rauf to Greaves, no run,dug into the pitch with pace off, he was looking to make room and crash it through off but didn't read the change of pace, ends up tamely bunting it back down the pitch
Haris Rauf to Greaves, OUT,length ball at normal pace outside off, and he's had a thrash at it, but only manages an under-edge that is dragged back onto the stumps.
Haris Rauf to Watt, no run,length ball on the stumps, kept very low, Watt had to get really low and keep it out
Haris Rauf to Watt, 1 run,fuller outside off, looks to make room and drive, gets it off the toe-end, trickling through cover
Haris Rauf to Berrington, 1 run,slower ball, back of a length well outside off, drags his sweep towards wide long-on
Haris Rauf to Watt, 1 run,full on leg stump, makes room and drives to long-off, and that's that.
Southee to Hazratullah Zazai, 1 wide,full and too wide outside off, left alone, extra gets play underway.
Southee to Hazratullah Zazai, 1 leg bye,full swinging into the pads, misses a flick off the pads and goes to fine leg for another extra.
Southee to Mohammad Shahzad, FOUR,pitched up on fifth stump, encourages a drive from Shahzad lofted over mid-off to the rope.
Southee to Mohammad Shahzad, no run,Shahzad walks down the pitch to flick a full ball to midwicket.
Southee to Mohammad Shahzad, no run,good length ball on the legs, flicked to short fine leg and picks out the fielder on the ring.
Southee to Mohammad Shahzad, no run,fullish length nips in off fifth stump line and Shahzad heaves past this.
Southee to Mohammad Shahzad, no run,back of a length on fourth stump, defended to midwicket.
Boult to Hazratullah Zazai, 1 run,full outswinger on fourth stump at 136 kph, mistimes a drive off a thick edge behind square for one.
Boult to Mohammad Shahzad, no run,inswinging yorker on fifth stump, jammed out to backward point.
Boult to Mohammad Shahzad, no run,bouncer over leg stump, ducked under.
Boult to Mohammad Shahzad, no run,good length ball on off stump, prodded into the covers to the fielder.
Boult to Mohammad Shahzad, no run,another short ball over middle ducked under.
Boult to Mohammad Shahzad, no run,another short and wide ball, Shahzad late on a cut to a 132 kph delivery.
Milne to Hazratullah Zazai, 1 run,back of a length on fourth stump, guided into the covers for a tight run.

Milne to Mohammad Shahzad, OUT,what a catch! Short ball on off stump, Shahzad tries to uppercut this over wicketkeeper and slip. Gets it off the toe of the bat and it flutters up high to Conway's right. He was wrong-footed but is still able to reach up with his right hand to stab this taking some steam off it initially before clutching on fully after a bobble and tumbling to the turf. Acrobatic but effective!
Milne to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run,short on fifth stump, sways away to leave.
Milne to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, FOUR,good length on middle at 137 kph, shuffles well across to flick through fine leg to the rope.
Milne to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run,back of a length defended on off stump into the covers.
Milne to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run,back of a length again on off, defended into the off side.

Boult to Hazratullah Zazai, OUT,another short ball finally pays off for Boult at 138 kph! Zazai cramped back of a length on the body, goes to flick this off the back foot over midwicket but instead a leading edge balloons to midwicket in the ring, simple catch for Santner.
Boult to Gulbadin Naib, no run,good length ball on fifth stump, shoulders arms.
Boult to Gulbadin Naib, no run,fullish length on sixth stump, Gulbadin with a flat-footed swat at a 137 kph delivery and is beaten.
Boult to Gulbadin Naib, no run,back of a length on off, Gulbadin finally puts bat on ball in defense to extra cover.
Boult to Gulbadin Naib, no run,back of a length on middle, defended into the off side.
Boult to Gulbadin Naib, FOUR,bouncer on the body at 137 kph, top edge hook clears the keeper Conway to the rope. Afghanistan will take runs any way they can get them after the two early wickets.
Milne to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 1 run,bouncer on the body, top edge hook to deep fine leg for one.
Milne to Gulbadin Naib, 1 run,fullish length outside off on sixth stump, thick-edged drive to deep third man for one.
Milne to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run,back of a length on fifth stump, shuffles across to flick to midwicket but inside edges into his pads on this 146 kph delivery.
Milne to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run,short on middle, shuffles way across off stump to pull and misses.
Milne to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 1 run,full on fifth stump, punched firmly to mid-off for a tight run.
Milne to Gulbadin Naib, no run,short ball on fourth stump at 141 kph, backs away for an awkward pull and beaten by the extra bounce.

Southee to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, OUT,full and straight, Rahmanullah loses his bearings shuffling across his stumps to flick and misses. Big lbw shout upheld. Gulbadin talks him out of burning a review. Wisely. He was stone dead hit on the shin in front of middle. Would've been three reds on DRS.
Southee to Najibullah Zadran, 2 runs,full outside off, drives through cover to get off the mark.
Southee to Najibullah Zadran, no run,short on fourth stump, goes to pull and flubs this back just short of Southee.
Southee to Najibullah Zadran, no run,short on fifth stump, swats this into the ground mistiming a shot for the off side.
Southee to Najibullah Zadran, no run,short on fifth stump angled across, sways back to leave.
Southee to Najibullah Zadran, 2 runs,full on leg stump, flicked with ease behind square for a pair.
Neesham to Gulbadin Naib, 2 runs,full on fourth stump, heaves this high over wide long-on for a pair.
Neesham to Gulbadin Naib, 1 run,overpitched on fourth stump, driven firmly to long-on.
Neesham to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,full on the legs, flicked into midwicket for one.
Neesham to Gulbadin Naib, no run,bouncer over middle stump, Gulbadin withdraws from a hook to this 134 kph delivery.
Neesham to Gulbadin Naib, 1 run,full and wide slower ball at 105 kph flayed high over cover for one.
Neesham to Najibullah Zadran, no run,back of a length on off, defended into the covers.
Santner to Gulbadin Naib, 1 run,good length on middle, goes back to flick into midwicket.
Santner to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,short and wide at 95 kph, cut behind point for one to the sweeper.
Santner to Gulbadin Naib, 1 run,full on middle, flicked into midwicket for one.
Santner to Najibullah Zadran, FOUR,overpitched on fifth stump, width for Najibullah to cream a drive flat over Santner to the mid-on rope.
Santner to Najibullah Zadran, no run,full and straighter on middle this time, forces a front foot defensive prod back to Santner.
Santner to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,full on fourth stump, flicked to long-on for one.
Neesham to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,full on fourth stump, driven to the cover sweeper for one.
Neesham to Gulbadin Naib, 1 run,back of a length on fifth stump, punched into the cover again for one.
Neesham to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,back of a length on fifth stump, guided with an open face to third man.
Neesham to Gulbadin Naib, 1 run,back of a length on the stumps, pulled behind square for one.
Neesham to Najibullah Zadran, FOUR,Overpitched on fifth stump, shovels this high over mid-off who was up in the ring, and goes to the rope.
Neesham to Najibullah Zadran, FOUR,some life now from Afghanistan spurred by the lefty! Full and wide, goes to drive hard, thick edge wide of Conway to the third man rope.
Sodhi to Gulbadin Naib, 1 run,starts with a googly on fifth stump landing short, goes back to punch to long-on.
Sodhi to Najibullah Zadran, FOUR,flighted full on the legs, flicks it high behind deep midwicket and deep backward square finding the gap to the rope.
Sodhi to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,good length on off stump, shuffles across to flick into midwicket.
Sodhi to Gulbadin Naib, 1 run,short on fourth stump, hammers a pull flat to midwicket.
Sodhi to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,good length on fifth stump, prodded to mid-off for one.

Sodhi to Gulbadin Naib, OUT,drag on!  Frankly the worst ball of the over. Short and wide, spinning even wider outside off, might have been called a wide had he left it alone. Instead Gulbadin tries to drag this with a pull down the ground and drags a toe/bottom edge back onto off stump. Gulbadin will be wishing he could have that one back. Definitely won't be posting that on his Instagram Stories.
Milne to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,good length on fifth stump, guided with an open face to third man.
Milne to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run,good length ball flicked away through the ring to get off the mark.
Milne to Najibullah Zadran, no run,back of a length on middle, defended to backward point.
Milne to Najibullah Zadran, no run,short on fourth stump, slower ball at 123 kph that Najibullah is way out in front of trying to pull.
Milne to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,fullish length on fifth stump, drives hard behind point for one.
Milne to Mohammad Nabi, 2 runs,back of a length on fourth stump, guides this with soft hands behind point to deep third man for a pair.
Sodhi to Najibullah Zadran, no run,full on off, prodded into extra cover.
Sodhi to Najibullah Zadran, 1 wide,flighted full down leg side, misses a sweep, wide called.
Sodhi to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,flighted full on fourth stump, sweeps firmly to deep square leg.
Sodhi to Mohammad Nabi, no run,full on off, driven back to Sodhi.
Sodhi to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run,back of a length on fourth stump, punched to long-off.
Sodhi to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,full on off, backs away to drive inside out to long-off.
Sodhi to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run,full on fifth stump, driven to long-off for one.
Southee to Mohammad Nabi, no run,back of a length on off at 131 kph, shuffles across to flick straight to midwicket.
Southee to Mohammad Nabi, no run,back of a length tailing down leg at 131 kph, misses a flick off the thigh pad that goes through to the keeper.
Southee to Mohammad Nabi, no run,full on fourth stump, flicked to midwicket.
Southee to Mohammad Nabi, no run,back of a length on the legs at 132 kph, Nabi misses another flick off the pads.
Southee to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run,back of a length on the legs at 132 kph, finally Nabi is able to get off strike with a flick to midwicket.
Southee to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,good length on the legs, flicked behind square for one.
Santner to Najibullah Zadran, SIX,Santner digs this in too short on fifth stump, sits up for him to slaughter this back over Santner's head to the long-on rope.
Santner to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,short again on the body this time, mishits a pull to deep midwicket for one.
Santner to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run,good length ball on the legs, shuffles across to tap this into midwicket.
Santner to Najibullah Zadran, SIX,flighted too full on fifth stump, Najibullah frees the arms for a big heave over midwicket and Phillips leaps above the rope but can't swat this back into play.
Santner to Najibullah Zadran, 2 runs,full toss floated on the hips, Najibullah taps it gently into the leg side for a pair.
Santner to Najibullah Zadran, 1 wide,darted in short and too wide for Najibullah to play a cut. Wide called.
Santner to Najibullah Zadran, 2 runs,floated up full on middle this time, flicked into the deep midwicket gap for another pair.
Milne to Mohammad Nabi, no run,short on the stumps, tap and run into cover. But picks out a fielder and has to turn back.
Milne to Mohammad Nabi, no run,bouncer over leg stump, Nabi misses a pull.
Milne to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run,slower ball lands full on fourth stump, tapped gently into mid-on for one.
Milne to Najibullah Zadran, no run,slower ball short and wide, Najibullah is way out in front of a pull.

Milne to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,back of a length slower ball at 119 kph outside off, tapped into the off side for a single to bring up a 33-ball half-century. His second 50 in this T20 World Cup and sixth overall in T20Is.
Milne to Mohammad Nabi, 2 runs,short on the stumps, pulled high and deep wide of deep midwicket for a pair.
Neesham to Najibullah Zadran, no run,slower ball full outside off, out in front of a leg side heave.
Neesham to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,full on the legs, flicked to midwicket.
Neesham to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run,full on the stumps, flicks through the ring for one.
Neesham to Najibullah Zadran, 2 runs,full on the stumps, taps this gently through the ring into midwicket and weighted perfectly to come back for two.
Neesham to Najibullah Zadran, no run,back of a length on the hips, defended back to Neesham.
Neesham to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,back of a length on fifth stump, slapped into the covers for one.
Boult to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,137 kph yorker on off, guided out in front of point for one.
Boult to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run,back of a length slower ball on off stump at 115 kph, punched into the covers for one.
Boult to Najibullah Zadran, no run,slower ball bouncer on fifth stump at 103 kph, Najibullah way out in front of a pull shot again. He's racked up a lot of dots to these slower balls.

Boult to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,length ball on the legs, flicks this in the air toward Mitchell at deep square leg who slides forward but it short hops him and they come back for a sharp pair. But the umpires signal one short on Najibullah at the non-striker's end, who was not really close to ground his bat across the line. Sloppy cricket.
Boult to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run,full on the legs, flicked to deep midwicket for one.
Boult to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run,full on off, punched into the covers for one.
Southee to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run,short ball on middle at 131 kph, Nabi backs away to pull and mistimes this to long-on.

Southee to Najibullah Zadran, SIX,finally he adjusts to a slower ball! Najibullah not fooled at 116 kph on a good length on sixth stump, flays this basically with wrists and forearms only over long-off. Not even a full flourish.
Southee to Najibullah Zadran, 2 runs,full on off, flicked to wide long-on for a pair.
Southee to Najibullah Zadran, FOUR,short on fourth stump, goes to pull, top edge to the fine leg rope.
Southee to Najibullah Zadran, 1 bye,yorker on fifth stump, goes to jam this out and misses. Conway fumbles the take to allow Nabi to get on strike.

Southee to Mohammad Nabi, OUT,back of a length on fourth stump at 135 kph, Nabi backs away for a leg side heave but is beaten for pace a touch and slams this back into Southee at thigh height. The wily medium pacer clutches on reaching forward with sharp reflexes.
Boult to Najibullah Zadran, FOUR,overpitched on the stumps searching for yorker, big heave takes an inside edge through fine leg to the rope.

Boult to Najibullah Zadran, OUT,Neesham with another stupendous diving catch at long-off!  Full and straight on off, tries to clear the ground straight for another six but gets this more off the toe and it lobs up toward Neesham, who was fielding quite wide and has to track 20 yards left before diving to clutch on 10 yards inside the rope.
Boult to Karim Janat, 2 runs,short on fifth stump, mistimes a pull to long-on and they scamper a tight two.

Boult to Karim Janat, OUT,full on the legs, flicks this high and deep to Sodhi at deep fine leg, who judges this well before lunging forward to take a safe catch at knee height about five yards inside the rope.
Boult to Rashid Khan, 1 run,full on off, driven to extra cover.
Boult to Mujeeb Ur Rahman, no run,132 kph short on the stumps, goes to pull but is cramped for room and comes off the body to backward point.

Neesham to Rashid Khan, 2 runs,tremendous athleticism by Mitchell to save a six! Short on the stumps, pulls this high and wide to cow corner. He leaps and catches this one-handed but is falling over the rope and flicks it back into play to save four runs.
Neesham to Rashid Khan, no run,full toss at thigh height follows Rashid backing away from leg stump and he swings through this. Might want to check his bat. Think there may be a hole in it.
Neesham to Rashid Khan, no run,another full toss at knee height on fifth stump, another swing and miss by Rashid. Seriously, big hole in that bat.
Neesham to Rashid Khan, no run,attempted wide yorker, another wild heave and it's a hat-trick of swings and misses to full tosses as this one passed at shin height outside off.
Neesham to Rashid Khan, no run,finally a genuine wide yorker and Rashid swings and misses as Rashid falls down reaching out.

Neesham to Rashid Khan, OUT,another full toss at knee height on fifth stump, Rashid finally makes contact but mishits this in the air over cover and it's a sliding catch on the ring by the captain Williamson. On another day, that over would've gone for 24, but no such luck for Rashid failing to score on a series of full tosses.
Mohammad Nabi to Guptill, no run,flighted up outside off, driven hard, but straight to extra cover
Mohammad Nabi to Guptill, 2 runs,slower in the air, middle and leg, pushed towards long-on, where Najib is a little slow and Mitchell steals the second
Mohammad Nabi to Guptill, 1 run,pushed wide of mid-off for one
Mohammad Nabi to Mitchell, no run,on a length, slight dip, Mitchell punches this back to Nabi
Mohammad Nabi to Mitchell, no run,short of a length, outside off, turning in, pushed to cover
Mohammad Nabi to Mitchell, FOUR,arm ball, a touch too shirt, swinging away, and he has punched this between extra cover and mid-off for four. Lovely timing
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Guptill, 1 run,full delivery, drifting in late, drifting in big time, but Guptill keeps it out well and gets a single to square leg
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Mitchell, no run,drifting in like an inswinger again even though it is released like a carrom ball. Defended
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Mitchell, 2 runs,shimmies down the wicket to place this wide of mid-on for two
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Mitchell, no run,short, has the width, but Mitchell doesn't get all of this and plays it straight to cover-point
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Mitchell, FOUR,not as short as the last one but wide enough and flat enough for him to go back and late-cut it between slip and short third man
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Mitchell, 1 run,leans forward, uses soft hands, drops this length ball towards point and charges through for a single
Naveen-ul-Haq to Mitchell, FOUR,gentle length ball, Mitchell has had enough sighters, and plays a lovely lofted off-drive over mid-off
Naveen-ul-Haq to Mitchell, 1 run,slower ball, on a length, he picks it in the air, plays with soft hands and steals a single to mid-off
Naveen-ul-Haq to Guptill, no run,another slower ball, Guptill still tries to crash it through covers, but gets a bottom edge
Naveen-ul-Haq to Guptill, FOUR,pace on, half-volley, Guptill stands tall and drives this between mid-off and extra cover. All looking too easy
Naveen-ul-Haq to Guptill, 1 run,slower ball now, Guptill ends up dragging it to long-on for one
Naveen-ul-Haq to Mitchell, 1 run,slower ball, short of a length, tucked off the hip for a single to short fine leg

Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Mitchell, OUT,Mujeeb strikes. The carrom ball takes the feather. He has got his rhythm going now. On a length, wide outside off, strong square field on the off side. Mitchell looks to open the face on the drive, the ball turns away a touch, and Shahzad doesn't drop these
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Williamson, no run,lovely slow carrom ball, Williamson plays for the offbreak, he is lucky this is wide and well outside the line of his bat. Beaten
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Williamson, 1 run,flatter, quicker, punched down to long-n for one
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Guptill, 1 run,overpitched, Guptill drives it off his toes for a single to long-on
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Williamson, 1 run,carrom ball, Williamson picks it, goes back, punches it down to long-on
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Guptill, 1 run,on a length, looks like an offbreak, Guptill not to its pitch but still manages to keep it down with an extension of his long arms. Gets a single to long-on
Hamid Hassan to Guptill, FOUR,gentle low full toss to start off with, and he has driven it straight of mid-off for four
Hamid Hassan to Guptill, no run,on a length, wicket to wicket, defended to leg

Hamid Hassan to Guptill, 1 run,lucky to get away with it. Slower ball, long-on back, but Guptill still looks to loft it in that direction. Lucky to have mis-hit it so bad that it doesn't carry as far as long-on
Hamid Hassan to Williamson, no run,short of a length, no room, defended back to him
Hamid Hassan to Williamson, no run,short of a length, just outside off, punched with an open face, but can't get it past point
Hamid Hassan to Williamson, 1 run,short of a length, cramps him up, inside edge into the body, and Guptill calls him through for a quick single
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Williamson, no run,really slow, good hang time, defended back to him
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Williamson, no run,quicker, on a length, no room, defended back to him

Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Williamson, 1 run,nearly a wicket. Soft, soft shot from Williamson. Premeditates a sweep, the length is not there, and he just paddles it instead of hitting it hard. The top edge nearly carries to short fine where Hamid doesn't really put in a big dive
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Guptill, no run,leading edge as this sits in the surface a little, but it doesn't carry to Mujeeb
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Guptill, FOUR,too short, Guptill rocks back and pulls it through midwicket. That should ease the pressure
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Guptill, FOUR,overcompensates, overpitches, right under Guptill's eyes, and he crunches a drive between mid-off and extra cover for four more
Rashid Khan to Williamson, 1 run,starts off with a legbreak, Williamson opens the face and runs it past slip for one
Rashid Khan to Guptill, 1 run,too full, driven to long-off for one
Rashid Khan to Williamson, 1 run,wrong'un, Williamson picks it, pushes it into the leg side for one. Covers the line and then closes the face at the last moment
Rashid Khan to Guptill, 1 run,another wrong'un, Guptill plays it off the pitch, uses his wrists to control it and takes a single to long-on
Rashid Khan to Williamson, no run,quick legbreak, starts around leg, turns towards middle. Defended back to him
Rashid Khan to Williamson, 1 run,down the wicket to take this on half-volley, and takes a single to square leg
Mohammad Nabi to Williamson, 1 run,stays back to punch a length ball to deep cover for one
Mohammad Nabi to Guptill, 1 run,short of a length, outside off, punched to deep cover again
Mohammad Nabi to Williamson, no run,short of a length, wide, gets the bottom edge on the cut
Mohammad Nabi to Williamson, 1 run,on a length, wicket to wicket, punched down to long-on for one
Mohammad Nabi to Guptill, no run,really slow in the air, no turn, takes the outer half of the bat to short third man
Mohammad Nabi to Guptill, no run,appeal for lbw but Guptill has got an inside edge on this as this turns from outside off
Rashid Khan to Williamson, 1 wide,wrong'un, starts too straight, wide down the leg side
Rashid Khan to Williamson, 1 run,legbreak, Williamson doesn't seem to have picked it, runs off the soft outside edge for a single to short third man
Rashid Khan to Guptill, 1 run,short, skiddy, bottom edge on the pull as they get a single to deep square
Rashid Khan to Williamson, 1 run,legbreak, this time Williamson is right behind it and punches it down to long-on for one
Rashid Khan to Guptill, no run,wrong'un, Guptill plays it off the surface and defends it right in front of off

Rashid Khan to Guptill, OUT,seems to have picked this wrong'un as he is slog-sweeping it to leg but picking it is one thing and connecting it quite another. He has missed altogether, and has been castled. Wicket No. 400 in T20 cricket for Rashid
Rashid Khan to Conway, 1 run,flighted outside off, it is a legbreak and he plays it with the turn to long-on for one
Mohammad Nabi to Conway, 1 run,drifting into the pads, worked away for a single around the corner
Mohammad Nabi to Williamson, no run,really slow offbreak, on off, defended back to Nabi
Mohammad Nabi to Williamson, no run,flatter, wicket to wicket, turning into middle and leg, pushed to straight short midwicket
Mohammad Nabi to Williamson, no run,flat length ball, opens the face, has no pace to work with, short third man fields
Mohammad Nabi to Williamson, no run,slows it down, defended back to Nabi. Williamson careful not to make any more mistakes here
Mohammad Nabi to Williamson, 2 runs,slow again, just a touch too full, and he has been driven wide of long-off for two
Hamid Hassan to Conway, no run,on a length, no room, pushed to mid-off, that extra man in
Hamid Hassan to Conway, no run,short of a length, skids on, angles in, hits the pad high

Hamid Hassan to Conway, no run,beaten. After the last one skidded on and angled in, this one holds its line outside off, against the angle. Beaten on a defensive shot. Apparently there is a slight murmur on the snicko. He possibly edged it but no one appealed
Hamid Hassan to Conway, no run,short of a length, no room, opens the face, can't get it past point
Hamid Hassan to Conway, 1 run,really full this time, pushed to the left of mid-off for a single
Hamid Hassan to Williamson, 1 run,short of a length, gets good bounce, Williamson rides it and punches it straight of point for one
Rashid Khan to Williamson, 1 run,on a length, into the pads, punched to deep midwicket for one
Rashid Khan to Conway, 1 run,soft hands, opens the face, takes a single to short third man

Rashid Khan to Williamson, FOUR,short of a length, into the pads, and with a short leg in you have to sacrifice a fielder somewhere. It is deep midwicket here. So all Williamson needs to do is punch this past short leg and beat midwicket in the circle
Rashid Khan to Williamson, 1 run,flighted outside off, opens the face, takes the single
Rashid Khan to Conway, no run,on a length, no room, punched to leg, can't beat the short straight midwicket
Rashid Khan to Conway, no run,similar delivery but a touch slow off the surface and beats him to hit the pad. Headed down leg, though
Gulbadin Naib to Williamson, 1 run,short of a length, no room, punched down to long-on for one
Gulbadin Naib to Conway, 1 run,slower ball, middle and leg, whipped away off the hip for one to deep square leg
Gulbadin Naib to Williamson, 1 run,slower again, short of a length, punched to deep cover for another single
Gulbadin Naib to Conway, 1 run,short of a length, around off, punched to long-off for a single
Gulbadin Naib to Williamson, FOUR,lovely shot. Naib goes full with the slower ball this time, but he has the field for short-of-a-length balls. Williamson caresses this past extra cover for four
Gulbadin Naib to Williamson, no run,on a length slower ball again, opens the face, plays it straight to point
Mohammad Nabi to Conway, 2 runs,Conway skips down the wicket and chips this over extra cover for a couple
Mohammad Nabi to Conway, FOUR,quicker, into the pads, and Conway sweeps this over short fine leg for four. Draws that flat delivery by using his feet first ball
Mohammad Nabi to Conway, FOUR,powerful sweep just in front of square this time. All along the ground. Deep square leg doesn't have much to move to his right but he can't catch up with this
Mohammad Nabi to Conway, 1 run,reverse-paddle this time for a single to short third man
Mohammad Nabi to Williamson, 1 run,wide on the crease, flat, on a length, Williamson dabs this for a single to short third
Mohammad Nabi to Conway, 1 run,pitched up outside off, driven to deep cover for one
Rashid Khan to Conway, FOUR,pitched up outside off, Conway reverse-sweeps this square of short third man for a four all along the ground
Rashid Khan to Conway, 1 run,flatter, shorter, punched down to long-on for one
Rashid Khan to Williamson, 1 run,pitched up, driven down to long-on for one
Rashid Khan to Conway, 1 run,looks for the powerful sweep but Rashid pushes this wide outside o0ff. Too late to withdraw from the shot, but the top edge falls safely short of deep square leg
Rashid Khan to Williamson, 1 run,wrong'un, bunted into the leg side for another single
Rashid Khan to Conway, 2 runs,another big sweep attempted, another top edge, and this time he manages to clear short fine leg for a couple
Hamid Hassan to Williamson, 1 run,on a lwength, top of off, dabbed away to third man for one
Hamid Hassan to Conway, no run,Conway skips down the track and is beaten by extra bounce on this shortish delivery
Hamid Hassan to Conway, no run,pulled, but straight to short midwicket
Hamid Hassan to Conway, 1 leg bye,dug in short, Conway looks to pull, is beaten and is hit in the midriff. He has struggled against Hamid all afternoon
Hamid Hassan to Williamson, FOUR,full toss, and he opens the face slightly to caress this wide of mid-off for four
Hamid Hassan to Williamson, 1 run,wide on the crease, angling in, hits the inside half of the bat for another single
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Williamson, 1 run,down the wicket, reaches the pitch of this, takes a single to long-off

Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Conway, FOUR,down the wicket, just the right distance between him and the pitch of the ball to be able to drive his arms through. Crashes this all along the ground but straight of long-on
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Conway, no run,beaten on the sweep, but manages to get a glove onto the pad
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Conway, 1 wide,wide down the leg side
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Conway, 2 runs,reverse-sweep, gets enough timing and placement for a couple to deep point
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Conway, no run,down the wicket again, Mujeeb shortens the length, punched to short cover
Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Conway, 2 runs,short of a length, angling in, punched wide of mid-on for two
Naveen-ul-Haq to Williamson, 2 runs,Williamson down the wicket to chip this length ball over extra cover for two more
Naveen-ul-Haq to Williamson, no run,slower ball, short of a length, stays low, hits the bottom edge
Naveen-ul-Haq to Williamson, 1 run,slower again, dug into the surface, dabbed away for another single
Naveen-ul-Haq to Conway, 1 run,on a length, on the pads, clipped away for one
Naveen-ul-Haq to Williamson, 1 run,full, driven with an open face, gets it wide of mid-off but can't get past Zazai's dive there
Naveen-ul-Haq to Conway, 1 leg bye,wide on the crease, slower ball outside leg, Conway gets a leg-bye. Scores are level now
Gulbadin Naib to Conway, 1 run,slower ball, punched down to long-on, and New Zealand are through to the semi-finals
Ali to Hendricks, no run,full on fourth stump, prodded into cover.
Ali to Hendricks, 1 run,good length on off, goes back and across to punch to long-on.
Ali to de Kock, no run,full on the pads, can't flick it away.
Ali to de Kock, FOUR,class! overpitched on off, de Kock backs away from leg to carve this high over extra cover to the rope on one bounce.
Ali to de Kock, 1 run,backs away from leg again, Moeen follows him and is flicked over midwicket for one.
Ali to Hendricks, no run,short on fifth stump, cuts this just short of backward point.
Woakes to de Kock, no run,full on fourth stump, defended.
Woakes to de Kock, 1 run,good length ball on fourth stump, prods forward in defense with soft hands but recognizes a sharp single on offer at mid-off.
Woakes to Hendricks, 1 run,back of a length on fifth stump, tap and run into the covers.
Woakes to de Kock, no run,back of a length on fifth stump, flicks this to mid-on off the back foot.
Woakes to de Kock, 1 run,back of a length on fifth stump, punched to mid-off for one.
Woakes to Hendricks, no run,good length ball on off, pushed into the covers.
Ali to de Kock, FOUR,de Kock shuffles down the track to a flighted ball on off and cracks a lofted drive over mid-off to the rope.
Ali to de Kock, 2 wides,flighted down the leg side, misses a sweep, escapes Buttler for another extra.
Ali to Hendricks, no run,short and wide, cut to point.
Ali to Hendricks, no run,back of a length on fifth stump, slapped to extra cover.

Ali to Hendricks, OUT,goes to slog sweep and the Zing bails and stumps light up. Hendricks was bogged down, tried to play a release shot after being unable to access the off side and misses a flighted ball full on middle stump. The length was right for the shot but he had no touch his entire time at the crease.
Ali to van der Dussen, 1 run,full on off, flicked into midwicket.
Ali to de Kock, no run,good length ball on off, prodded into the covers and Roy charges in to deny a run.
Woakes to van der Dussen, FOUR,clever from Rassie. Full on off, shuffles well across picking the right ball landing full on fifth stump and scoops this over fine leg to the rope.
Woakes to van der Dussen, no run,gem! Back of a length on fifth stump at 135 kph/84 mph, Rassie fiddles at this and is beaten.
Woakes to van der Dussen, no run,full on off, punched to mid-off.
Woakes to van der Dussen, no run,back of a length on off, defended back to Woakes.
Woakes to van der Dussen, no run,full on off, punched to mid-on.
Woakes to van der Dussen, 1 run,full on the stumps, flicked to midwicket for an extremely tight single.
Ali to van der Dussen, 1 run,good length ball on off, flicked into midwicket for one.
Ali to de Kock, 1 run,good length on fifth stump, goes back to pull this flat over midwicket for one. Protection on the rope.
Ali to van der Dussen, no run,flighted full on fifth stump, chipped short of mid-on.
Ali to van der Dussen, 1 run,back of a length on middle, punched wide of mid-off for one.
Ali to de Kock, 1 run,full on the stumps, flicked to deep midwicket.
Ali to van der Dussen, 1 run,full on the stumps, flicked into midwicket for another single.
Woakes to van der Dussen, FOUR,fullish length on fifth stump, Rassie charges and heaves to the leg side, thick inside edge beats deep fine leg to the rope.
Woakes to van der Dussen, SIX,uses his feet again to shuffle down to a full ball on fifth stump and shovels this high and deep over cow corner.
Woakes to van der Dussen, 1 run,slower ball lands full as Rassie came down the track again and adjusts to flick along the turf through midwicket for one.
Woakes to de Kock, 1 run,good length ball on fourth stump, tap and run into the covers.
Woakes to van der Dussen, 1 run,spears in a leg stump yorker, flicked straight to deep fine leg, Rashid.
Woakes to de Kock, 1 run,full again and flicked away for another single to end the Powerplay.
Ali to de Kock, 1 run,Moeen follows de Kock again backing away from leg, pushes this into the covers for one.
Ali to van der Dussen, 1 run,good length on leg, flicks this into midwicket.
Ali to de Kock, FOUR,flighted full outside leg stump, de Kock goes for a reverse sweep this time and clears short third man high over the ring bouncing over the rope.
Ali to de Kock, 1 run,good length ball flicked through the ring for one.
Ali to van der Dussen, 1 run,good length on the legs, flicked away through square leg for one.
Ali to de Kock, 1 run,full on off, pushed to the cover sweeper.
Rashid to de Kock, 1 run,floats up a juicy full toss at knee height to start on off stump but de Kock just taps it along the turf for one to long-on to bring up the team 50.
Rashid to van der Dussen, FOUR,flighted full on fifth stump, reverse sweep picks the gap between short third man and backward point to the rope.

Rashid to van der Dussen, no run,flighted full on fifth stump, goes to sweep and there's a noise as it passes. Appeal for caught behind given not out but Buttler coerces Morgan into going for the review.  Rashid didn't look particularly interested. Nothing on Ultraedge. May have been bat on ground. England lose a review.
Rashid to van der Dussen, 1 run,full on fifth stump, drives along the turf to long-on.
Rashid to de Kock, 1 run,good length ball on the legs, flicked into midwicket for one.
Rashid to van der Dussen, no run,good length ball on off, flicked straight to short fine leg.
Jordan to de Kock, 1 run,short and wide, cut to deep third man for one.
Jordan to van der Dussen, no run,good length ball on fourth stump, defended into cover.
Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 run,good length ball on off, pushed to long-on for one.
Jordan to de Kock, 1 run,full on the stumps again, flicks it down the ground for one.

Jordan to van der Dussen, 2 leg byes,full on off, shuffles way across and misses a flick. Big appeal for lbw denied. Looked stone dead live. They go for the review.  He was so far across his stumps and missed with leg stump showing. Ball-tracking shows umpire's call on impact at off stump, even though leg stump was lit up red like Christmas lights. My my my.... I say Rassie is quite fortunate. Stays not out.
Jordan to van der Dussen, FOUR,good length ball on leg stump, Rassie shuffles across again but this time gets bat on ball flicking through fine leg to the rope.
Rashid to de Kock, 1 run,full on the legs, chipped over midwicket for one.
Rashid to van der Dussen, 1 run,good length ball on the legs, flicked to midwicket for one.
Rashid to de Kock, FOUR,flighted full on off, de Kock breaks out the reverse sweep and sends this behind third man to the rope.
Rashid to de Kock, 1 run,short on fifth stump, slapped to long-off for one.
Rashid to van der Dussen, no run,flighted full on fifth stump, shuffles across to sweep and misses. Stifled lbw shout. Hit well outside off stump.
Rashid to van der Dussen, 1 run,full on fifth stump, stands upright this time to punch to long-off for one.
Wood to van der Dussen, 1 run,length ball, skidding on straight and tucked for one
Wood to de Kock, 1 run,short ball wide of the stumps, de Kock sticks out the broom handle and pokes behind square
Wood to van der Dussen, SIX,145 clicks, and scooped for six! RvD gets cute, and gets rewards, expertly done jumping across his stumps early and using Wood's pace on the ball
Wood to van der Dussen, 1 run,short on the body, 144kph, tucked down to fine leg
Wood to de Kock, 1 run,back of a length, de Kock brings out the 3 wood but only skews one through square
Wood to van der Dussen, 1 wide,slammed into the surface, 146kph/91mph, Rassie flinches under it... called wide on height. But Wood's made his point

Wood to van der Dussen, 1 run,banged in and spliced... but lands safely! van der Dussen in a complete tangle there, but the ball drops between three fielders converging around point. The batter then cops a blow on the arm diving full length for his ground in taking a hasty single
Rashid to van der Dussen, 1 run,tossed up outside off, comes forward and nudges leg side

Rashid to de Kock, OUT,chipped to long-on! Rashid makes the breakthrough for England, after a solid second-wicket stand. QdK has his best score of the tournament, but he would have wanted to go on... in the end, a mishit down the ground flew hard and flat to Roy running around
Rashid to van der Dussen, 2 runs,tossed up, straigtening on the pads, RvD plays it so late but gets bat on ball for a couple
Rashid to van der Dussen, 1 run,floated up and pushed down the ground
Rashid to Markram, 1 run,rocks back and pulls to long-on
Rashid to van der Dussen, 1 run,pushed through on the stumps, 89kph and squirted away through square leg going back
Wood to van der Dussen, 1 run,tapped down into the off side, Markram would have been struggling with a direct hit... Fifty for van der Dussen, playing nicely here tonight
Wood to Markram, 1 leg bye,banged in, 148kph/92mph, gets in a tangle but they scramble through as the ball comes off the body
Wood to van der Dussen, 1 run,short and swatted down to fine leg
Wood to Markram, 2 runs,length at 148kph/92mph and Markram plays it well, shovelling in front of deep square leg for a couple
Wood to Markram, 1 run,back of a length, 144kph and this is pulled away for a single to the sweeper
Wood to van der Dussen, SIX,creamed into the stands, raises the SA 100! Pace on, pace off... a swirling hook shot sends the ball soaring for six. Some Rassie razzle-dazzle
Rashid to Markram, 1 run,tossed up and swept hard to deep midwicket
Rashid to van der Dussen, 1 run,pushed through on the stumps, worked to leg
Rashid to Markram, 1 run,tosses up the legbreak, Markram walks out and punches to long-off
Rashid to van der Dussen, 1 run,tossed up outside off, shuffles across and taps one square
Rashid to Markram, SIX,boom goes the dynamite! Markram dances down, he's not to the pitch but keeps his eye on it and swings a meaty blow over deep midwicket
Rashid to Markram, 1 run,googly to finish, not sure Markram picked it but gets away with a thick inside edge for one
Jordan to Markram, 1 run,length in the channel, 137kph/85mph and Markram skips out to drive through cover point

Jordan to van der Dussen, no run,ooh err, not so sure about that, Rassie... standing outside leg, he attempts a reverse-scoop, bat held out in front of him and looking to deflect it over third. Ball just misses leg stump
Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 run,shuffles across and gets a tickle on a flick to leg
Jordan to Markram, 1 run,short of a length, hammered out towards deep extra cover for one
Jordan to van der Dussen, no run,and there's another dot, as Rassie attempts a more conventional scoop and ends up deflecting the ball through to Buttler via his pads
Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 run,nudged leg side, Jordan hares after it and has a shy at the non-striker's end. Good, tight over for England
Woakes to van der Dussen, SIX,length ball, and blammo! van der Dussen swings a baseball blow over long-on! Stands tall and nails this straight over the bowler's head
Woakes to van der Dussen, SIX,hammered into the crowd at deep midwicket! Pitched up and he's waiting for it, clean swing towards the 57m leg-side boundary, connects a treat
Woakes to van der Dussen, 2 runs,banged in wide of the stumps, 135kph/84mph and he's cut for a couple
Woakes to van der Dussen, 1 run,full and wide, RvDDDDDinks it through backward square down to the sweeper for one
Woakes to Markram, SIX,full toss, clumped over the ropes! Woakes gets it wrong and all Markram has to do is flick the wrists to deposit the ball into the stands
Woakes to Markram, no run,a wide half-tracker gets Woakes out of the over, Markram swings hard but only gets a toe-end through to Buttler on the bounce
Wood to van der Dussen, no run,dug in back of a length, Rassie pulls at it and deflects the ball through to the keeper... came off the hip, I think
Wood to van der Dussen, 1 run,quick ball, 146kph/91mph but calmly clipped leg side for one
Wood to Markram, FOUR,goes wide on the crease but Markram makes room, slices it over short third! Used the pace on the ball, 147kph/92mph, and he whipped the hands through while opening the face
Wood to Markram, no run,back of a length, 144kph/89mph and Markram can't get this away
Wood to Markram, 2 runs,short and pulled, comes off the splice but the lack of power enables them to scurry two into the leg side
Wood to Markram, FOUR,pace off but it's short, wide and slapped! The <del>wide long-hop</del> slower-ball bouncer doesn't fool Markram, as he muscles a cut in front of square. Brings up the SA 150
Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 run,goes full outside off, 136kph/84mph and dug out for one
Jordan to Markram, 3 runs,miscued over the covers, a wide full toss from Jordan and Markram doesn't really get hold of it... but the throw is wide of the bowler and they manage to steal a third
Jordan to van der Dussen, no run,short of a length and skidding through, Jordan went up for caught behind as van der Dussen pulled at it... Buttler not interested in the appeal
Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 bye,goes length in the channel, RvD swings and misses... but England are sloppy again, Buttler's underarm bypasses Jordan and this pair are alert, pinch the single
Jordan to Markram, 1 run,banged in and Markram swats it off the back foot

Jordan to van der Dussen, FOUR,gets the reverse-scoop going this time! Joe Root-esque, dare I say it... comes across and sets himself for another length ball outside off, reaches forward and frying pans it over short third. Masterfully done
Wood to Markram, no run,short of a length and zipping through as Markram attempts a scoop and misses
Wood to Markram, 2 runs,chopped into the ground backing away, they run anyway... and Wood then volleys the ball wide of Buttler! Another needless single given up
Wood to Markram, SIX,cutter from Wood, powered into the boundary boards! Sits back and crrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrunches a sweet hit over deep midwicket!
Wood to Markram, 1 run,length ball, 145kph/90mph, swings across the line and just gets an inside edge for one this time
Wood to van der Dussen, 2 runs,moves across early, think that was another offcutter from Wood, swung leg side into a gap
Wood to van der Dussen, 2 runs,shortish and tucked leg side again, Wood gives chase but won't prevent them coming back for a second
Jordan to Markram, 1 run,goes for the wide yorker first up, thick-edged into his back pad and they take one
Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 run,hits a length in the channel, van der Dussen looks to swing for the short leg-side boundary, squirted to fine leg
Jordan to Markram, SIX,but Markram has fuel to burn, slammed over long-off! Missed the yorker and he takes it on the half-volley, sends it screaming over the ropes. Magnificent way to go to fifty
Jordan to Markram, 1 run,pitched up on off stump, can't get under this one, punched down to long-on

Jordan to van der Dussen, SIX,high and handsome, a golf swing leg side... Roy is racing around from long-on but won't prevent it from going for six! He tripped over the boundary marker as he stretched out a hand, but the ball squirted away just beyond the rope

Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 run,short and wide and flapped for a single, van der Dussen finishes on 94 not out, a career-best and it's given SA a shot at overhauling Australia for a semi-final spot here
Maharaj to Roy, no run,good length ball on fourth stump, punched back to the bowler.
Maharaj to Roy, no run,full on off, defended back to Maharaj again.
Maharaj to Roy, no run,good length ball on off sticks in the wicket, prodded back just short of Maharaj.
Maharaj to Roy, 1 run,good length ball on off, punched to long-off for one.
Maharaj to Buttler, no run,good length ball on off, prodded to cover. Rabada denies the run.
Maharaj to Buttler, 1 leg bye,good length on the legs, misses a clip off the pads into the leg side for an extra.
Nortje to Buttler, 1 run,full on fifth stump, driven to extra cover, Bavuma denies four with a one-handed slap on a diving effort as a ricochet goes to mid-off.

Nortje to Roy, no run,back of a length skids onto middle and leg, massive lbw shout denied. Looked very out live. Bavuma calls for a review.  He was hit extremely deep in the crease hopping on his toes just above the knee roll. This may be a bail-clipper. Not even. Ball-tracking shows it is going over the stumps. Big moment but luck goes England (and Australia's) way. South Africa lose a review.
Nortje to Roy, no run,fullish length on middle again, inside edge into the pads before it trickles to midwicket.
Nortje to Roy, FOUR,full on middle, driven past the ball through mid-off to the rope.
Nortje to Roy, 1 run,full on off, pushed to mid-off taking on Miller for a very tight single.
Nortje to Buttler, FOUR,fullish length outside off, driven on the up over mid-off to the rope.
Maharaj to Roy, FOUR,flighted full on middle, uses his feet to chip this high over mid-on, two bounces to the rope.
Maharaj to Roy, no run,full outside off, driven to mid-off.
Maharaj to Roy, no run,good length ball on middle, pushed to cover.
Maharaj to Roy, FOUR,short on the legs, backs away and hammers a pull through square leg for another boundary.
Maharaj to Roy, 1 run,full on the legs, flicked through midwicket for one.
Maharaj to Buttler, 1 run,full outside off, driven wide of mid-off for one.
Rabada to Buttler, FOUR,length ball at 144 kph/89 mph sits up on fifth stump, elegant punch through cover to the rope.

Rabada to Buttler, FOUR,Rabada goes fuller and tighter on fourth stump at 141 kph/88 mph, Buttler with a heave through the leg side, doesn't time it crisply but still enough lumber behind the thickish inside edge to go past midwicket to the rope.
Rabada to Buttler, 1 run,117 kph back of a length slower ball on the hips, flicked behind square for one.
Rabada to Roy, FOUR,Australia starting to breathe easier now... too full and straight on the legs, just a simple tickle to a 143 kph misfired yorker and it goes to the fine leg rope.
Rabada to Roy, 1 run,short on the legs, pulls this fine but cut off at deep fine leg for one.
Rabada to Buttler, 1 run,yorker full on middle, dug out to mid-off for one.
Maharaj to Buttler, 1 run,fullish length on the legs, flicked into midwicket after a charge to settle for a single.
Maharaj to Ali, 1 run,good length ball on fifth stump, sliced behind point for one.
Maharaj to Buttler, 1 leg bye,comes down the track and flicks off the pads behind square for an extra.
Maharaj to Ali, 1 wide,speared in full and too wide outside off, left alone. Wide called. He's trying to deny Moeen the short leg side rope to the lefty.
Maharaj to Ali, 1 run,good length ball heaved flat to midwicket for one.
Maharaj to Buttler, 1 run,good length ball on the legs, flicked into midwicket for one.

Maharaj to Ali, (no ball) FOUR,my goodness... an overstep from the left-arm spinner! No words for this... The delivery was speared in full and wide, flayed over extra cover and trickles into the rope. Overstep, spotted by the third umpire, compounds the error. His foot landed on, not behind, the line.

Maharaj to Ali, 2 runs,overpitched full on off, skies a drive off a thick edge over backward point. Should be an easy catch off the free hit for one but Nortje clumsily spills it and it continues going toward the rope for a second run to happen.
Nortje to Buttler, SIX,length ball on middle, Buttler clears the front leg to hammer this 147 kph/91 mph delivery high over wide long-on into the stands.

Nortje to Buttler, 2 runs,full on middle, backs away again to access the off side this time to a 148 kph/92 mph delivery, drives between mid-off and extra cover for a pair before it's relayed back in.

Nortje to Buttler, OUT,slower length ball on fifth stump, driven to Bavuma at mid-off. Nortje took some steam off this with a legcutter at 133 kph, causes Buttler to mistime this and it flutters toward Bavuma just barely carrying as he stretched forward to claim this at ankle height on the ring.
Nortje to Bairstow, 1 run,back of a length on the stumps at 148 kph, flicked into midwicket for one.
Nortje to Ali, no run,back of a length on fourth stump at 141 kph/88 mph, defended into point.
Nortje to Ali, no run,back of a length on the hips at 139 kph/87 mph, defended awkwardly into cover.
Shamsi to Bairstow, no run,good length ball on off, defended.

Shamsi to Bairstow, OUT,back of a length on leg stump straightens and skids on with Bairstow missing a back foot flick, big shout upheld! Bairstow goes for DRS immediately.  Main doubt was whether it pitched in line with leg stump or not. Definitely no bat and was hitting the stumps. Three reds light up on ball-tracking. Bairstow burns a review. Awfully quick trigger by him going for a review on what was a stone dead decision.
Shamsi to Malan, 1 run,good length ball outside off on fifth stump, cuts this through to the point sweeper.
Shamsi to Ali, no run,good length ball on sixth stump, Moeen goes to cut and is beaten. Sounded like a noise but no appeal.
Shamsi to Ali, 1 run,fuller on leg stump, Moeen goes back to flick into midwicket for one.
Shamsi to Malan, no run,fullish length ball flighted on fifth stump spins past Malan's attempted drive.
Markram to Ali, no run,back of a length on off, punched into the covers to the fielder.
Markram to Ali, 1 run,full on middle and leg, chipped to long-on where Miller fields.
Markram to Malan, no run,full and wide, goes to drive and beaten.
Markram to Malan, 1 run,fuller and straighter on fourth stump, driven to long-off.
Markram to Ali, 1 run,charges to turn a full ball into a low full toss driven past Malan to long-on for one.
Markram to Malan, no run,good length ball on the stumps, defended.
Shamsi to Ali, no run,full on off stump at 89 kph, prodded into the off side.
Shamsi to Ali, FOUR,charges to convert this into a full toss at shin height on the legs, swats this over midwicket to the rope.
Shamsi to Ali, no run,short and wide, skids low and misses a slap to the off side.

Shamsi to Ali, 2 runs,fullish length ball flighted more on sixth stump, Moeen through the shot a touch early lofting this toward extra cover on the ring but clears Bavuma easily to the sweeper for a pair.
Shamsi to Ali, no run,good length ball skidded on a bit quicker on sixth stump, cuts this to backward point.
Shamsi to Ali, no run,good length ball on sixth stump again, sliced to backward point.
Rabada to Malan, 1 run,full on the stumps, driven down the ground for one.
Rabada to Ali, 1 run,118 kph good length slower ball on the legs, flicked over square leg for one.
Rabada to Malan, FOUR,wide yorker attempted, Malan toe edges a drive past de Kock through third man to the rope.
Rabada to Malan, FOUR,overpitched wide outside off again at 136 kph/84 mph, bowling machine pace to drive through cover to the rope again.
Rabada to Malan, no run,good length on middle and off at 133 kph, pushes this into the covers for one.
Rabada to Malan, 1 run,back of a length on the hips, goes back to flick into the leg side for one.
Shamsi to Malan, 2 runs,floated up from over the wicket, Malan reverse-sweeps and gets it fine for a couple
Shamsi to Malan, 3 runs,ripper from Shamsi, finds the outside edge with Malan going back, but that only diverts it wide of the keeper and fine of short third and they pick up three
Shamsi to Ali, no run,flattish stock ball wide of off, Moeen cuts and finds the man at cover
Shamsi to Ali, 1 run,looped up, Moeen shuffles across on to off stump, aims a heave leg side... it squirts off the pads, and that single puts England into the semis
Shamsi to Malan, no run,flighted and Malan reverse-sweeps... for some reasons Shamsi started to go up for lbw. Ambitious, but SA will take the dot
Shamsi to Malan, 2 runs,flat outside off and he's back to cut through the infield to deep backward point
Markram to Ali, no run,punched back to the bowler
Markram to Ali, SIX,smoked over extra cover, Moeen strolls down and belts this hard and flat for six!
Markram to Ali, FOUR,hammered straight! Might have been half of a quarter of a chance, Markram stuck out his right paw as the ball fizzed by. Rabada's dive from long-off is in vain
Markram to Ali, 1 wide,sprayed down the leg side as he attempts to sweep - brings up the England 100
Markram to Ali, 1 wide,fired past the pads again, trying to cramp Moeen but giving up extras
Markram to Ali, 1 run,flat on the pads and worked leg side
Markram to Malan, 1 run,tossed up and he jams this for one
Markram to Ali, 1 run,floated up and Moeen is once again happy to tuck this through midwicket
Shamsi to Ali, SIX,Moeen, Moeen, gone! Tossed up and down come the batter, absolutely <I>clatters it through the line over long-on. He's put it on the roof!

Shamsi to Ali, OUT,pushed through and Moeen holes out this time! Tried to repeat the trick but couldn't get under this, pounded hard but flat, straight into the safe hands of Miller on the rope at long-on! Moeen's brief is to take down spin, and he's fallen on his sword going after Shamsi
Shamsi to Livingstone, no run,tossed up and this spins, Livingstone pushes forward, thick-edged past his stumps
Shamsi to Livingstone, no run,stays back and nudges to midwicket
Shamsi to Livingstone, 1 run,tossed up on off stump, clipped to long-on
Shamsi to Malan, 1 run,goes back on the stumps and works one more into the leg side
Nortje to Malan, no run,lickety-split! 148kph/92mph into the keeper's gloves as Malan hangs back and is beaten
Nortje to Malan, no run,cranks it up further, 150kph/93mph and again Malan swings and it and misses
Nortje to Malan, FOUR,shuffles across and whips leg side, uses the pace on the ball and sends it fizzing through backward square leg to the short boundary
Nortje to Malan, no run,banged in, 150kph/93mph and this claps him a blow on the leg looking to pull
Nortje to Malan, 1 run,dug in short at 148kph/92mph and Malan is hurried, manages to swat a pull for one
Nortje to Livingstone, no run,tally ho! Livingstone tries to give Nortje the charge, aiming a blow leg side, but fails to connect
Pretorius to Malan, no run,round the wicket, pace off in the channel wide of the stumps, Malan moves across and misses with a slog-sweep
Pretorius to Malan, no run,length, 114kph/71mph and angling in, Malan fails to connect again
Pretorius to Malan, 1 run,cutter in the corridor, Malan gives up on trying to go for the short boundary and punches a driven single
Pretorius to Livingstone, no run,over the wicket and on a length, 118kph wide of off stump, Livingstone mistimes a cut
Pretorius to Livingstone, 1 run,comes down and swipes, gets a thick inside edge to the leg side
Pretorius to Malan, SIX,collared from the final ball of the over! Malan steps across and takes him down town, arms fully extended through a thump over long-off

Rabada to Livingstone, SIX,OUTTA HERE!! There's some Homer for the night! Length ball, in the arc... and out of the park from Livingstone, sailing over the horizon at deep midwicket. Measured at 112 metres by the TV guys, the longest hit of the T20WC!
Rabada to Livingstone, SIX,six more, on the roof! England go past 131 in the most brutal fashion, Rabada bowled a wide half-volley and Livingstone hoyed it high over wide long-on!
Rabada to Livingstone, SIX,blammo, straight down the ground this time! Livingstone is channeling Yuvraj Singh at the 2007 tournament, he's three from three and Rabada is under the pump now
Rabada to Livingstone, no run,goes back of a length, wide of the stumps, Livingstone is stretching and can only bottom edge through to the keeper
Rabada to Livingstone, no run,flings this full and wide, can't reach it - but the umpire signals that he had moved across
Rabada to Livingstone, 1 run,pace off and dug into the pitch, swiped away for one on the pull
Pretorius to Livingstone, 1 run,wide cutter from Pretorius, chopped into the turf out towards the cover sweeper

Pretorius to Malan, OUT,miscues a slog at a slower ball... caught just outside the ring! Rabada is the man, no time to brood on his previous over, he circles around from short third and takes it well coming down over his shoulder. SA still scrapping to win this
Pretorius to Livingstone, 1 run,shortish length, pace off and worked leg side
Pretorius to Morgan, FOUR,full and wide, but he moves way across and paddles four! Gets it past short fine leg and away for a boundary
Pretorius to Morgan, 1 run,skips down and swings across the line, gets a thick edge to short fine leg
Pretorius to Livingstone, FOUR,slapped over backward point! He had all his protection leg side but sent this short and wide, Livingstone cashes in
Nortje to Morgan, 1 run,back of a length, 145kph/90mph and sliced for one to third
Nortje to Livingstone, 1 run,excellent wide yorker from Nortje, only able to chop it into the turf through the covers
Nortje to Morgan, FOUR,slashed through the covers, Morgan makes a bit of room and carves it past the dive of Bavuma on the ring
Nortje to Morgan, no run,chopped towards backward point, there's a run-out chance with Livingstone backing up - but Nortje can't gather van der Dussen's throw cleanly!
Nortje to Morgan, FOUR,steps away and throws the bat, gets it past third! Shamsi was the fielder, he flung himself full length but couldn't reel it in on the rope!
Nortje to Morgan, no run,finishes with another pinpoint wide yorker and Morgan can't lay bat on it

Pretorius to Livingstone, OUT,goes big, but picks out long-off! Back-of-the-hand slower ball from Pretorius and Livingstone can't quite generate enough power, it went pretty high but not far enough and Miller settles under the catch a few yards in from the boundary
Pretorius to Morgan, no run,round the wicket, full outside off and he can only drag a mistimed shot into his pads
Pretorius to Morgan, (no ball) 1 run,fullish slower ball, plinked down to long-on for one... uh oh, but he's overstepped!
Pretorius to Woakes, SIX,forehand smash out of the ground! Looks like Woakes has been playing tennis at the hotel... slower ball and it sits up, he climbs into it with a mighty swipe over long-off
Pretorius to Woakes, 1 run,pitched up, another big swing but this squirts away leg side
Pretorius to Morgan, no run,sneaks a cutter through, Morgan setting himself to swing hard but fails to connect
Pretorius to Morgan, 2 runs,skips down, heaves leg side and he wants two, going to be a tight second... but Rabada's throw from deep square leg is high and de Kock has too much to do!

Rabada to Woakes, OUT,heaved leg side... but he's not quite got enough! Nortje is the man running around at deep midwicket and he holds a slightly awkward catch under pressure. There's a lengthy check for the no-ball, but Rabada's foot is okay. Well held by the big man, clutching it to his chest as he thundered around a few inches in front of the rope

Rabada to Morgan, OUT,picks out deep backward square leg! Two in two for Rabada, and South Africa look like holding their nerve here... Pace off that delivery, I think, and Morgan underclubbed it trying to hit to the longer part of the ground

Rabada to Jordan, OUT,HAT-TRICK! Clubbed to long-off! Third hat-trick of the tournament, and Rabada is laughing - all three of them caught in the deep, but never mind that. Another slower delivery, and England have taken a vow to going down swinging. Jordan stands still and plops it into the safe hands of Miller coming in
Rabada to Rashid, 1 run,short and into the pitch, Rashid bottom-edges a single
Rabada to Wood, 1 run,short length and Wood plinks one backing away
Rabada to Rashid, 1 run,banged in, Rashid slaps another single to long-on - South Africa win by 10 runs, but it won't be enough to see them through to the semi-finals
Starc to Gayle, 2 runs,full and yorker length on off first up, inside edge goes through backward square leg off an attempted drive
Starc to Gayle, 1 run,another yorker length one on middle stump, pushed towards mid-off and Gayle hustles a quick single. Seeing the ball fairly well with the shades, is Gayle...
Starc to Lewis, 1 leg bye,length ball on leg stump, looks to turn it away legside, plops near short leg off the pad
Starc to Gayle, no run,good length in the channel, left alone by Gayle
Starc to Gayle, no run,another good length ball, probing in the channel, left alone
Starc to Gayle, no run,good length angled into him on the stumps, looks to tuck it away but the ball just gently rolls back down the pitch

Hazlewood to Lewis, FOUR,hammered. There's a deep square leg but he still went for the pull to a ball that's back of a length. Got into position early and very nicely, blasts it to the deep fielder's right, no chance for him to cut it off

Hazlewood to Lewis, FOUR,now he goes fuller, Lewis looks for the booming drive but gets a thick inside edge that runs away to the fine leg boundary. So the man in the deep has seen balls go to the fence on either side of him, last two balls.

Hazlewood to Lewis, FOUR,clears mid-on this time and gets his third boundary in a row. Not timed well enough, came off the outside half of the bat, as he played a lofted on-drive to a fullish ball. Enough to clear the fielder and trickle over the boundary
Hazlewood to Lewis, 1 run,back of a length on the stumps, looks to pull again, gets it off the bottom half of the bat through square leg

Hazlewood to Gayle, SIX,Gayle-smash. He should have been in shades from the start of the tournament! This is another back of length ball on the stumps, Gayle transfers weight back and unleashes a pull over wide long-on
Hazlewood to Gayle, 1 leg bye,length ball going down leg, ball goes to fine leg off the pad as he misses connecting with the flick

Cummins to Gayle, SIX,boom. Cummins also tries to hit that hard length, going across Gayle, he just stands still and generates immense power while swatting across the line and sends this soaring over long-on

Cummins to Gayle, OUT,stumps clattered. The entertainment's over. Gayle was looking good, but has to go. Fuller ball around off, looking to punch on the up, gets an inside edge that goes onto the stumps. Gayle's wearing a disappointed look as he walks off, but he's played his part in getting West Indies off to a flier. Walking off the field with sunglasses under the helmet after an innings that featured two big sixes - not a bad way to walk off, if this is Gayle's final innings for West Indies.
Cummins to Pooran, no run,length ball on the pads, turned to backward square leg
Cummins to Pooran, FOUR,gorgeous shot. Full on the stumps and he just leans into a straight drive that goes to the bowler's left but also beats mid-on.
Cummins to Pooran, 1 leg bye,length ball ends up on leg stump, looking to turn it, goes off the pad towards cover. Cummins thinks that's close but I'm pretty sure it pitched outside leg
Cummins to Lewis, no run,length ball on the stumps, a bit early into the push, ball trickles towards mid-on from the outside half of the bat

Hazlewood to Pooran, OUT,he's picked out cover. Back of a length outside off, he was looking to get on top of it and crash it through the offside, but that probably bounced a bit more than he expected and was much closer to offstump too, so he couldn't get on top of it as he wanted to, ball flies in the air straight to the fielder for an easy catch.
Hazlewood to Chase, no run,Good length around off, punched to cover

Hazlewood to Chase, OUT,castled. West Indies suddenly rickety after a rocket start. Perfect length just outside off, think there was a hint of movement inwards, Chase beaten while trying to play an expansive drive and has his off-stump knocked out of the ground. Chase was to be the glue around which the other hitters functioned, but he's gone in just two balls.
Hazlewood to Hetmyer, 1 run,length ball on off, steered to third man
Hazlewood to Lewis, 1 run,length ball on the stumps, flicked off his pads through square leg
Hazlewood to Hetmyer, no run,fuller on off, driven to mid-off
Cummins to Lewis, 1 run,fuller on the pads, flicked through square
Cummins to Hetmyer, 1 run,good length going across him, steered to third man
Cummins to Lewis, no run,pace off that one, on a length outside off, has to wait a bit and pushes it towards point by opening the bat face
Cummins to Lewis, 1 run,fuller ball into him, flicked off his toes to deep square leg. He was very front-on while playing the shot, get a bit of an inside edge on it
Cummins to Hetmyer, FOUR,lovely shot. Fuller length going across him, punches through cover, bisects the field and the timing is so good it purrs all the way to the boundary
Cummins to Hetmyer, no run,back of a length, looking ot pull, gets a bottom edge to square leg
Maxwell to Lewis, 1 run,length ball outside off, stands tall and punches towards backward point
Maxwell to Hetmyer, no run,closer line outside off, jabbed back down the pitch
Maxwell to Hetmyer, 1 run,keeps it tight on off stump, Hetmyer goes on the back foot and whips through midwicket
Maxwell to Lewis, FOUR,flatter and quicker but strays down legside so Lewis just slogs it past the short fine leg to pick up an easy boundary
Maxwell to Lewis, no run,fuller into him, jabs it to mid-on
Maxwell to Lewis, no run,flatter on off stump on a good length, can't get hold of the cut, chops it into the ground near him
Marsh to Hetmyer, 1 run,fuller on off, driven through extra cover. Long-off has to run to his right to field
Marsh to Lewis, no run,fuller outside off, steered to point, who tumbles to his right to stop it well

Marsh to Lewis, no run,length ball on off, clips the pad on the way to the keeper as he's beaten on the pull. Marsh thinks it could be lbw and Australia review. But the impact was well outside off, so that's one review gone.
Marsh to Lewis, 1 run,fuller outside off, glided through point
Marsh to Hetmyer, 1 run,slower bouncer, waits for it and controls his pull shot down to deep backward square leg
Marsh to Lewis, no run,swing and a miss. Length ball angled across him, well outside off, stands and swings at it, looking to go straight over, can't connect
Zampa to Hetmyer, 1 run,fuller on off, stretches forward to get to the pitch and pushes it gently to long-off
Zampa to Lewis, 1 run,length on leg stump, goes across and clips it through midwicket
Zampa to Hetmyer, 1 run,tossed up on the stumps, on the front foot to turn it through midwicket
Zampa to Lewis, no run,googly tossed up on leg stump, goes down on one knee to slog-sweep, but can't connect. Wear sit on the pads

Zampa to Lewis, 1 leg bye,run out chance missed. googly that hits him on the pads as he misses the pull. Ball rolls to short leg. Zampa is appealing but that's pitched outside leg. They steal a single, keeper goes across and has a shy - would have been out at the bowler's end if he hit
Zampa to Hetmyer, no run,pushed to mid-off
Marsh to Lewis, 1 run,stroked through cover
Marsh to Hetmyer, 1 run,fuller on the stumps, driven to long-off
Marsh to Lewis, 1 run,fuller outside off, steers to deep point

Marsh to Hetmyer, FOUR,long-off can't stop it, such was the power in that shot. Opens his stance up and belts the leather off it in this off-drive. Warner - one of the best fielders in the world - runs to his left and gets to the ball, but it's hit so hard he can't stop it
Marsh to Hetmyer, 1 run,back of a length, can't quite time the pull well, one run through midwicket
Marsh to Lewis, no run,gets away with a marginal one. Very full and very wide outside off, just inside the tramlines I think. He let the ball go but it's not a wide.
Zampa to Hetmyer, 1 run,skips down the track to get to the pitch and flicks through midwicket
Zampa to Lewis, FOUR,shot. Zampa's been tossing them up on or outside leg, so Lewis opens his stance a bit, goes down on one knee and slog sweeps to the backward square leg boundary

Zampa to Lewis, OUT,super catch by Steve Smith at long-on. Googly on a length on leg, Lewis looking to hit against the turn, long-on side, gets a leading edge that swirls up high. Smith moves in from the boundary and has to dive forward to grab this safely.
Zampa to Hetmyer, 1 run,plays and gets a leading edge square into the off side
Zampa to Pollard, 1 run,very full at off stump, driven to long-off
Zampa to Hetmyer, 1 wide,full and down the leg side, called wide
Zampa to Hetmyer, 1 run,an appeal for lbw as he plays across this, taken on the pad but that's outside leg
Starc to Hetmyer, no run,full outside off, driven firmly to cover
Starc to Hetmyer, 1 run,full at middle and off, worked down to long-on with a flick of the wrists
Starc to Pollard, 2 runs,neatly flicked off the pads wide of midwicket
Starc to Pollard, no run,an appeal for lbw, think he might have squeezed this, was a good-length ball that he came forward. Appeared as though Starc bowled it with a slightly round-arm action
Starc to Pollard, 1 wide,a short delivery, down the leg side, nice carry to Wade but it's an extra
Starc to Pollard, 1 leg bye,full at the pads, doesn't make a connection and he deflects towards fine leg
Starc to Hetmyer, 2 runs,terrific yorker, but Hetmyer manages to dig it out backward of square and comes back for the second. Was some late tail on that

Zampa to Pollard, no run,dropped! And can't get the rebound as it loops above his head as he falls in the crease. Low full toss chipped straight back to him. Should have held that. He had a second chance at it, too, but agonisingly couldn't grab it behind him
Zampa to Pollard, 1 run,a googly skids on, worked into the leg side
Zampa to Hetmyer, no run,touch short outside off, a strong square cut and it's well intercepted at backward point
Zampa to Hetmyer, no run,another one skids through! Hetmyer caught playing back and he's fortunate to get the toe end on it
Zampa to Hetmyer, 1 run,drives a full delivery to long-off
Zampa to Pollard, FOUR,that's a lovely piece of placement, a full delivery outside off, opens the face and drives it through point
Hazlewood to Hetmyer, no run,over the wicket, back of a length and straight, played into midwicket
Hazlewood to Hetmyer, 2 runs,touch fuller at the stumps, driven down the ground and long-off comes across
Hazlewood to Hetmyer, 1 run,good length at off stump, pushed square into the point region
Hazlewood to Pollard, 1 run,works this off stumps through midwicket

Hazlewood to Hetmyer, OUT,gloved down the leg side! A short ball from Hazlewood, at good pace, climbs around leg stump and Hetymer gets himself into a bit of a tangle. Glances it through to Wade. Big wicket. Excellent bowling
Hazlewood to Bravo, 1 run,back of a length, straight, tucked off the pads to long leg
Zampa to Bravo, no run,clipped into midwicket
Zampa to Bravo, 1 run,drives through the off side to the cover sweeper
Zampa to Pollard, no run,full at middle, defended
Zampa to Pollard, 1 run,worked off the pads in front of square
Zampa to Bravo, no run,stretches forward and plays this square into the off side, wants the single but it's not there
Zampa to Bravo, no run,good length again, hint of turn, pushed towards point. Another very good spell from Zampa
Marsh to Pollard, 2 runs,short of a length, Pollard walking at the bowler and nudges off his hip. Placed well enough for a second
Marsh to Pollard, no run,comes down the pitch again, this is short outside off, Pollard goes for a square cut and it loops over the top edge
Marsh to Pollard, no run,full and wide outside off, driven straight to cover on the edge of the ring
