Marsh to Pollard, 2 runs,straighter delivery, tucked off the body backward of square and again he can make it back for the second
Marsh to Pollard, 1 run,blimey, he's hammered this straight into Bravo at the non-striker's end. The bat flies from his grip. After all that they complete a single to long-on
Marsh to Bravo, no run,full at off stump, pushed back to the bowler
Starc to Pollard, 1 run,over the wicket, a low full toss at the stumps, driven towards mid-off who is able to cut it off

Starc to Bravo, 1 run,gets the yorker in, jabbed towards cover and they take the single...almost a run out trying to steal a second from an overthrow. Bravo would have been out if Starc had collected the ball
Starc to Pollard, 1 run,short on leg stump, tapped into the on side
Starc to Bravo, no run,starts to come down the pitch and can only play over the top of a yorker that slides past off stump...146kph
Starc to Bravo, SIX,fantastic stroke! Full outside off, he stands his ground this time and drives over extra cover.
Starc to Bravo, 1 run,a straight full toss, looking to work to the leg side but it shoots off the outside edge to deep point
Cummins to Bravo, 1 leg bye,back of a length, follows Bravo outside leg, rebounds off the pad towards third man

Cummins to Pollard, 2 runs,full outside off, he launches into a drive over cover, looks like it's going for four but Warner throws himself around the rope. Has he done enough? Brilliant work, yes he has
Cummins to Pollard, FOUR,power! Full toss outside off, thumped straight down the ground and Warner has no chance with this one
Cummins to Pollard, no run,goes short, well bowled, took the pace off as well and Pollard is through his shot early. Deflects off the toe end and lands short of Wade
Cummins to Pollard, SIX,he's up and running! It's another short one, he goes for the hook, it's a bit more top edge than middle but travels all the way over backward square leg
Cummins to Pollard, 1 run,a slower ball dug in, tapped around the corner to keep the strike
Hazlewood to Pollard, 2 runs,full at off stump, a big heave across the line, takes a thick inside edge towards fine leg
Hazlewood to Pollard, 1 run,a slower ball, full outside off, dragged along the ground to deep midwicket as he loses his shape

Hazlewood to Bravo, OUT,how much has he got of this? Not enough! It's four for Hazlewood. A full delivery, Bravo aiming straight down the ground, slices it high in the air, leaning back on the stroke, and very well-judged catch at long-on
Hazlewood to Pollard, FOUR,full and straight, powerfully flicked through midwicket. Excellent timing and placement
Hazlewood to Pollard, 1 wide,very wide outside off, going for the wide yorker
Hazlewood to Pollard, FOUR,a length delivery, a slower ball, angling into the pads, tickled away fine and Hazlewood's figures taking a bit of dent
Hazlewood to Pollard, 1 run,full outside off, driven to long-on
Cummins to Pollard, 1 run,low full toss, speared into the pads, clipped straight to deep square leg
Cummins to Russell, FOUR,gets this away! Wasn't a bad ball. Fired in at the toes as he moves to the leg side but Russell clips it wide of short fine leg
Cummins to Russell, no run,swings to leg and doesn't connect, was there for shot...a full delivery in the swinging arc. Inside edge into his back pad
Cummins to Russell, 1 run,a slower ball, short outside off, cracked over cover but can't beat the sweeper
Cummins to Pollard, 1 run,full at leg stump, clipped firmly but one bounce to deep square...a few metres either side and that was a boundary
Cummins to Russell, no run,another slower short ball, defeats Russell as he pulls. That's an excellent over from Cummins, just seven from it
Starc to Pollard, no run,attempts to scoop a very full delivery, doesn't connect and ends up falling over in the crease. Not a shot you see often from Pollard
Starc to Pollard, OUT,full at leg stump, long way up in the air and Maxwell has plenty of time to judge it from long-on
Starc to Russell, 1 run,round the wicket, banged in short, Russell pulls but it takes a toe end and early carries to long-on
Starc to Holder, 1 run,stays round the wicket, gets the yorker in at the stumps, can only drive to mid-off
Starc to Russell, SIX,gets hold of this one! Short of a length and that's certainly out of the middle as he pulls it way back over deep midwicket. TV says 111 metres. That's a big 'un
Starc to Russell, SIX,and another! Terrific finish from Russell. It's a low full toss and it's lofted back over long-on. That's a boost for West Indies
Hosein to Warner, no run,keeps it full and wide outside off, maybe Warner was looking to reverse swat, had to adjust and drive, misses it
Hosein to Warner, 1 run,flatter on a length on the stumps, tapped back past the bowler
Hosein to Finch, no run,sharply jagging into him from a length outside off, looking to make room and whip it, misses and wears it on the pad
Hosein to Finch, 1 run,all sorts of action in the first over, with Finch getting an inside edge to another one that comes in sharply, looking to punch. Past leg stump for a single
Hosein to Warner, 2 runs,a touch too full, whipped off his toes through midwicket
Hosein to Warner, 1 run,flatter and fuller on the stumps, tucked to long-on
Chase to Warner, no run,length ball on the stumps, punched to mid-off
Chase to Warner, no run,fuller and into him, patted back to the bowler
Chase to Warner, FOUR,flatter, but dragged shorter, Warner makes use of the length to make room and crash it through cover
Chase to Warner, 1 run,tossed up fuller outside off, made as if to reverse but was faking the bowler, who sticks to his line anyway. Warner drives to mid-off for a single

Chase to Finch, FOUR,tossed up outside off, and he unleashes a violent drive through cover. The fielder there is Hetmyer who dives to his right and gets a hand to it, but it's still hit so hard it goes to the boundary
Chase to Finch, (no ball) 2 runs,full toss dipping on him, flicked through midwicket. Dre Russ fumbles in the field and they pick up a second
Chase to Finch, 1 run,was clearing his front leg and looking to slug it out of the ground, full bal outside off, swats it across the line but not timed, so only a single to deep midwicket
Holder to Finch, no run,back of a length outside off, was giving himself room and slaps it hard, but can't beat extra cover
Holder to Finch, no run,pinged into his ribs. Back of a length coming into him, he's opening up to pull, can't quite judge the bounce and he wears it on the body
Holder to Finch, 1 run,length ball coming into him, shuffles across and tucks through midwicket
Holder to Warner, FOUR,crashed over mid-on. Back of a length, went right back and swatted it hard over the fielder

Holder to Warner, FOUR,edge flies past Pooran. Back of a length and that climbed steeply, cramped for room is Warner trying to steer it, gets a thick edge. Pooran flies to his left but it just eludes him. Also too far to the right of Dre Russ at short third man

Holder to Warner, SIX,this is Gayle and Bravo's farewell but another T20 legend is bringing out his greatest hits. Warner has picked up the length very quickly again, and rocks back to hammer a pull to the deep midwicket boundary
Hosein to Finch, no run,tight line on the stumps and denying him room, tapped back
Hosein to Finch, no run,keeps it tight on the stumps and Finch can only push it towards mid-on

Hosein to Finch, OUT,chopped on!. Flat outside off and coming in, not short enough to cut but that's the shot Finch was attempting, and he gets an under-edge that shatters stumps. Too close to his body too. First breakthrough made for West Indies
Hosein to Marsh, 1 run,length ball on off, angling in, pushed to long-off
Hosein to Warner, 1 run,flicked through midwicket on the back foot
Hosein to Marsh, no run,keeps it slidly wider outside off but he's getting balls to swerve in considerably, so it's not a safe ball to leave alone or swing through the line. Punched to cover

Bravo to Warner, FOUR,and that is stunningly executed. Too full outside off and Warner stands stock still, and lofts his extra cover drive disdainfully to the boundary. Great bottom-handed power in that
Bravo to Warner, no run,slower ball, straighter line too, on the stumps, on the front foot to defend solidly
Bravo to Warner, no run,pace off again, length on leg stump to deny room, Warner backing away to make room, taps it towards mid-off with a horizontal bat
Bravo to Warner, no run,fuller but closer to off stump, driven to cover
Bravo to Warner, 1 run,slower ball, almost yorker length on middle stump, adjust and taps it softly to mid-off for a quick single
Bravo to Marsh, 1 run,slower ball, off cutter into him, ends up on the pads, flicked to deep midwicket
Hosein to Marsh, 1 run,darted into him a bit full, turned to square leg
Hosein to Warner, SIX,bang goes Warner. It was a full ball sliding down leg and Warner spotted that to go across, get down on one knee and slog-sweep it over fine leg. Fine shot
Hosein to Warner, no run,better line and length, outside off, punched to cover
Hosein to Warner, no run,slides on the pads again but this is not too full and Warner can only tuck it into the legside to the fielder in the circle at midwicket
Hosein to Warner, FOUR,super shot. Vintage Warner. A bit short outside off, but not very far from the stumps. Warner makes a tiny bit of room and cuts it fiercely through backward point
Hosein to Warner, 1 run,fuller on the stumps, clipped through midwicket
Walsh to Warner, no run,starts with a googly to the leftie, defended
Walsh to Warner, 1 leg bye,tossed up on leg stump, tickled fine to short fine leg
Walsh to Marsh, FOUR,googly that's been dealt with magnificently. Mitchell Marsh unveils the reverse sweep. Length on leg stump, got down on one knee and nailed the shot through backward point
Walsh to Marsh, 1 run,that's been thumped, but only a single. Drags it short, March opens up and pulls fiercely. Fielder collects on the bounce
Walsh to Warner, 1 run,another googly, Warner makes room and slaps it through midwicket
Walsh to Marsh, 1 run,not short enough, but he went back to pull, got it off the bottom half of the bat through midwicket. The bowler sprints across to field it
Hosein to Marsh, 1 run,another reverse sweep but Walsh at backward point dives to his right to stop it. Length ball again, Marsh made good connection too, but Walsh is a gun fielder.
Hosein to Warner, 1 run,that strikes him on the pad as he's looking to reverse paddle. West Indies will review. Warner had moved across to hit it. But there's an inside edge which is why he's safe.
Hosein to Marsh, SIX,down the track and over the top. Marsh has absolutely blasted that, straight back over the bowler's head by getting to the pitch and golf-swinging clean through the ball
Hosein to Marsh, 1 run,on the front foot to flick this ball from off stump through midwicket
Hosein to Warner, 1 run,top edge drops in no man's land. Flatter and quicker, Warner goes back to pull, gets the edge but it lands at mid-on, where there's no one
Hosein to Marsh, no run,fuller into him, tapped back

Walsh to Warner, SIX,smoked. Tossed up on the stumps, Warner clears his front leg a long way and swings this way over midwicket. He's well and truly back to his best in this innings. Quite unstoppable when he's going like this.
Walsh to Warner, 2 runs,shorter and flatter, swats a sweep forward of deep square leg and raises a fine, fine fifty. Warner's running away with this game
Walsh to Warner, 1 run,googly on leg stump, tucked to deep square leg
Walsh to Marsh, no run,length ball outside off, pushed to cover
Walsh to Marsh, 1 run,googly, a bit short, sits back and pulls to deep midwicket
Walsh to Warner, 1 run,flatter googly going across him, Warner sweeps in front of square
Russell to Warner, no run,that kept low a bit outside off, Warner was looking to smash a drive through cover but missed it. Took the pace off too, did Dre Russ, rolling fingers over ball
Russell to Warner, 1 run,fullish outside off, chopped to point
Russell to Marsh, SIX,shot!. Strays on the pads with a full one, and Marsh flicks it off his pads. Hits it hard enough that it goes for a flat six over fine leg

Russell to Marsh, FOUR,misfield by Hosain allows four. Not a great ball either, full down legside again, flicked off his pads again but along the round. Hosain right there and it just goes through his legs

Russell to Marsh, FOUR,stunning. I'm not quite sure how Marsh had that four four. This was full outside off, seemingly a good ball but Marsh just angled his bat and drove, picks out the gap at point and finds another boundary.
Russell to Marsh, 1 run,full on off, driven to long-off
Bravo to Marsh, 1 wide,round the wicket, pushed across very wide outside off, misses a booming drive but gets the wide call
Bravo to Marsh, 2 runs,full at the toes, clipped wide of long-on and Warner hustles back
Bravo to Marsh, 2 runs,full outside off, driven through cover without much timing but, again, they get back for the second
Bravo to Marsh, no run,straighter, at off stump, driven to mid-off
Bravo to Marsh, 1 run,another solid drive out to the cover sweeper
Bravo to Warner, no run,steps to leg then drives at a slower ball outside off and is beaten
Bravo to Warner, 1 run,digs out a full delivery square through the covers
Russell to Warner, 1 run,well bowled, a yorker at leg stump, jabbed out and they scamper through
Russell to Marsh, 1 run,flicks a low full toss through midwicket
Russell to Warner, FOUR,somehow he gets a boundary for that! A well-directed bouncer, Warner is ducking out the way, flaps his bat at it and gets it over short fine leg
Russell to Warner, 1 run,steps outside leg and crunches a drive along the ground to deep point
Russell to Marsh, 1 run,whipped off the toes backward of square
Russell to Warner, 1 run,a slower ball, full outside off, tapped towards point
Bravo to Warner, no run,a very full, loopy, delivery outside off, through the keeper...just inside the tramline
Bravo to Warner, 1 wide,and that one is certainly too wide, an 80kph slower delivery, barely lands on the pitch...and Warner falls over. Has this game lost its edge?
Bravo to Warner, 1 run,slices a drive in the air through cover
Bravo to Marsh, no run,round the wicket, back of a length and pushed across, Marsh has a huge swing and doesn't connect
Bravo to Marsh, 1 run,full on the pads, flicked very firmly to deep square, reaches him one bounce
Bravo to Warner, FOUR,that's a brilliant stroke! A wide yorker and he's able to square drive it with power through point
Bravo to Warner, 1 run,comes down the pitch this time, on a leg stump line, drives to deep cover
Holder to Warner, no run,short of a length, angled across outside off, Warner goes for a reverse swat and again finishes on his backside in the crease
Holder to Warner, 1 wide,very short, very wide, quite loopy, outside off and called wide
Holder to Warner, 1 run,full at middle and leg, he clears the front leg and swings to deep midwicket
Holder to Marsh, FOUR,round the wicket, full outside off, throws everything at a drive and gets a thick edge well wide of the keeper
Holder to Marsh, FOUR,down to third man again! Swings hard at a full delivery outside off, flies squarer off the edge this time, the other side of short third man, and races away
Holder to Marsh, 1 run,clips a low full toss down to long-on and takes Marsh to a 28-ball fifty. He hasn't lost that form
Holder to Warner, no run,misses a drive this time, defeated by the change of pace
Bravo to Marsh, 1 wide,full outside leg stump, just misses the boot, given wide
Bravo to Marsh, 2 runs,swings across the line and sends it backward of square, a tumbling save on the ope
Bravo to Marsh, 2 leg byes,full toss on the pads, aims to flick it away, only comes off the pad yet they can take two
Bravo to Marsh, 1 run,full and wide outside off, picks out mid-off on the edge of the ring
Bravo to Warner, FOUR,goodness me! Bravo over the wicket, it's a slower ball angling across, Warner switches his hands, dances across the crease, and swats it out to deep point
Bravo to Warner, SIX,that's huge over square leg! A length ball on leg stump, Warner gets underneath and pulls it high and handsome
Bravo to Warner, 1 run,full at off stump, driven down to long-off. The end of a great career. Well bowled, DJ Bravo.
Gayle to Warner, no run,round the wicket, Warner starts a reverse sweep then goes for the conventional sweep
Gayle to Warner, 1 wide,sweeps again, appeal for a catch down the leg side
Gayle to Warner, no run,now he reverse sweeps, picks out short third man...plenty of smiles from Gayle
Gayle to Warner, 1 wide,missed stumping! Pushes this down the leg side, Warner stumbles out of his crease but Pooran can't gather
Gayle to Warner, 2 runs,a lofted drive inside out over cover, much more control in that
Gayle to Warner, 2 runs,angled into the pads, tucked backward of square, Warner sprints back for the second and hurls himself across the crease. Not sure that was entirely needed
Gayle to Warner, 1 run,pushed off the pads to deep square leg

Gayle to Marsh, OUT,driven to mid-off, Gayle has a wicket! And he hugs Mitchell Marsh. Not sure Marsh really appreciated that. A full ball, Marsh trying to finish, thumps his drive but head-height to Holder
Chase to Warner, no run,full at the toes, clipped to backward square
Chase to Warner, FOUR,tucked off the pads, just wide of Gayle at leg slip
Bumrah to Munsey, no run,full ball, misses the flick and is hit on the pad. Pitched outside leg, so no appeal

Bumrah to Munsey, no run,full outside off, reaches out and drives to mid-off. May have wanted to hit that through the covers, but it went off the inside half of the bat. Seemed to be a touch early on the shot
Bumrah to Munsey, 1 run,very full outside off, takes out the front of the wicket with that length and line. Opens his bat face and steers to deep third

Bumrah to Coetzer, 1 leg bye,attempted yorker, angling down leg and ending up as a low full-toss. Coetzer tries to get his feet out of the way and flick, only manages to get pad onto it, ricochets into the point region
Bumrah to Munsey, no run,back of a length, angling across to finish outside off, punched into the covers

Bumrah to Munsey, SIX,ah, that's a glorious way to bring up the first boundary of the day. Looks for the yorker on the stumps, and Munsey just gets his front leg out of the way to create just enough room for a whip of the wrists. That's all he needs to send the ball soaring over the square leg boundary
Varun to Coetzer, no run,quickish, angling into off stump, stays on the back foot to block to midwicket
Varun to Coetzer, no run,a bit slower, turning in from just outside off, presses forward to block into the covers
Varun to Coetzer, 1 run,inward turn again, the wrong'un, flatter and finishing on leg stump, nudged away through square leg
Varun to Munsey, no run,full on middle stump, blocked back to the bowler

Varun to Munsey, FOUR,terrific. Looks for the carrom ball spinning in from outside off, and as soon as he sees the line, his hands move in a flash to reverse-sweep into the big gap behind backward point
Varun to Munsey, no run,similar line, a bit quicker and fuller, and he misses the reverse-sweep on this occasion
Bumrah to Coetzer, no run,in the blockhole on middle and leg, defended to midwicket

Bumrah to Coetzer, no run,back of a length, nipping in from just outside off. Seemed to stop on Coetzer as he looked to defend. Ended up meeting it further out in front of his body than he would like, and it pops up in the air, but safely on the bounce to mid-on

Bumrah to Coetzer, OUT,bowled him. Another offcutter, and Coetzer looks to drive it through the covers. No footwork there. It came in a little off the pitch, but it didn't go between bat and pad. Coetzer was early on his shot, and it ended up beating the outside edge and hitting off stump
Bumrah to Cross, no run,in the blockhole again, attacking the stumps. Keeps his front pad out of the way and blocks into the cover

Bumrah to Cross, no run,slower ball outside off, and Cross picks it late. Just pushes his hands at it in defence, and it pops up in the air, juuuust lands in front of Suryakumar diving forward at point
Bumrah to Cross, no run,back of a length, nipping in towards off stump, defended towards midwicket
Ashwin to Munsey, no run,length ball, keeps going with the angle into the stumps. Blocked back to the bowler

Ashwin to Munsey, no run,sees him looking to make room and follows him with one that drifts into leg stump. Looks to drive, and it rolls towards midwicket off the inside half of the bat. Good diving stop to the left there, from Varun
Ashwin to Munsey, no run,length ball drifts in and keeps going that way, towards the pads. No room, and he works it to square leg

Ashwin to Munsey, FOUR,makes a lot of room this time, exposes all his stumps. Has to do that, because it's sliding in towards middle stump, but he's made enough room to flat-bat it and bisect extra-cover and mid-off. Shot

Ashwin to Munsey, FOUR,superb stuff. This time he holds himself back an instant longer. Ashwin knows the reverse is coming, and slows it down, gets it to drift in towards middle and leg, but Munsey watches it well, and reverses it over the gap between short third and backward point

Ashwin to Munsey, FOUR,wow, another. This one's not quite controlled, but it doesn't matter. Through the reverse-sweep a touch early as Ashwin drifts another in towards leg stump, slower, and the top-edge flies over short third, a little to his right
Varun to Cross, no run,wrong'un, spinning in from just back of a length outside off. Punched to mid-off
Varun to Cross, 1 run,a bit more flight on off stump, spinning in again. Uses his wrists nicely to clip it down to long-on

Varun to Munsey, no run,full on off stump, spinning away from the left-hander. Driven firmly, and the fielder at mid-off nearly overruns the ball while going to his right, then dives left to make up for it
Varun to Munsey, no run,looks to reverse-sweepo, misses the wrong'un, is hit on the pad outside leg stump
Varun to Munsey, 1 run,makes a ton of room and Varun follows him with a loopy ball outside leg stump, driven hard to the left of mid-off
Varun to Cross, no run,wrong'un again. Jams his bat down to keep it out of his stumps while playing it from the crease, and plays it back to the bowler
Mohammed Shami to Munsey, no run,very full around off stump, makes a bit of room and drives to mid-off with a flat-bat swing

Mohammed Shami to Munsey, OUT,got him, the danger man is gone. Full on off stump, and it was probably there for the big hit, but he simply doesn't get hold of it. He clears his front leg and is probably looking to hit over mid-on, and he ends up hitting a flat, low catch to the fielder, who does well to dive forward and take it with both hands
Mohammed Shami to Berrington, no run,back of a length on off stump, rides the bounce and defends into the on side
Mohammed Shami to Berrington, no run,some shape into the right-hander there. Is not far enough forward to defend, and it sneaks past the inside edge to hit pad, but it's swinging down the leg side
Mohammed Shami to Berrington, no run,shortish and quick, angling into the front hip. Berrington's feet are stuck, and he ends up looking to fend it away. Can't put bat to it and gets hit on the side

Mohammed Shami to Berrington, no run,oh wow, that nearly sneaked through! In the blockhole, on the stumps, and Berrington is a touch late bringing his bat down to keep it out. Gets a tiny bit of bottom edge on it, and it rolls away past leg stump
Jadeja to Cross, no run,length ball, keeps going with the angle towards leg stump as Cross looks  to make room. Can only punch it back to the bowler
Jadeja to Cross, 1 run,flat length ball angling in towards off stump, steps across and gets down low to sweep to deep backward square leg

Jadeja to Berrington, OUT,got him, Berrington played completely down the wrong line there. Jadeja's previous two balls just kept going with the angle, and Berrington probably played for that as he angled a good-length ball in and pitched it on around middle and off. Comes forward to defend, looking for the slider, and it just holds its line to beat his outside edge and hit middle stump. Not the best look for a batter, because that didn't turn all that much
Jadeja to MacLeod, no run,length ball straightening towards off stump, defended into the covers
Jadeja to MacLeod, 1 run,tossed up slightly slower on off stump, stretches out and lap-sweeps to long leg

Jadeja to Cross, OUT,big appeal, and that's surely out. Yup, no hesitation from Rod Tucker, and Matt Cross consults with his partner and reviews. More out of hope than belief, I think. Struck on the back pad, and it was straightening towards the stumps. On the shorter side of a length, straightening just a touch after pitching on off stump, and it skids through quicker than Cross expects, and perhaps a touch lower too. Sneaks past the inside edge as he looks to work it into the leg side, and it smacks his back knee roll. Hitting middle and leg, says ball-tracking, and Scotland are four down
Ashwin to MacLeod, no run,back of a length, keeps going with the angle outside off, defended to short cover
Ashwin to MacLeod, 1 run,tossed up slow outside off, swept to the right of deep backward square leg
Ashwin to Leask, 1 run,another flighted ball outside off, driven to deep point
Ashwin to MacLeod, no run,flat carrom ball straightening slightly towards off stump, back and across to defend to midwicket

Ashwin to MacLeod, 1 run,is that the reverse-carrom? Seemed to come out the front of his hand, but it kept going inwards towards middle and leg. Bat comes down like a curtain rail in defence, and he just manages to get an outside edge into the backward point region
Ashwin to Leask, no run,all the tricks are on show now. Loopy and slow outside off, and he stretches out to defend, only for the ball to turn away and beat the outside edge
Jadeja to MacLeod, no run,flat and full on middle and off, defended back to the bowler
Jadeja to MacLeod, 1 run,length ball sliding on towards off stump, reverse-swept firmly and Varun dives left at backward point to make a good stop

Jadeja to Leask, 1 run,full, a bit slower, pitching just outside off. Wants to drive through the covers, the ball doesn't turn and he ends up playing it towards long-on off the inside half off the bat
Jadeja to MacLeod, no run,length ball on middle and leg, played back to the bowler while looking to clip to long-on

Jadeja to MacLeod, 1 run,looks to sweep one that straightens from middle and leg, gets a top-edge as he checks his shot, and it loops up and lands in the vacant midwicket region. No one in the circle there
Jadeja to Leask, 1 run,goes back to a length ball sliding into the stumps, clips it watchfully to deep midwicket
Varun to Leask, no run,loopy outside off, turning in. Looks for the cover-drive and inside-edges into the leg side
Varun to Leask, 2 runs,looks to cut one that's coming into him, not sure he picked that, and he inside-edges past his stumps and into the short fine leg region
Varun to Leask, FOUR,runs, finally .Legbreak with a bit of flight, and he meets the sweep in front of off stump and finds the gap to the right of deep square leg
Varun to Leask, 1 run,flat length ball going with the angle just outside off, chopped into the point region
Varun to MacLeod, no run,quicker and fuller, angling in towards off stump, jams his bat down at an angle and defends to midwicket
Varun to MacLeod, 1 run,full-toss in front of off stump, slapped to deep point
Mohammed Shami to MacLeod, 1 run,good length and into middle stump, hangs deep in the crease and flicks to long-on

Mohammed Shami to Leask, SIX,sails over fine leg! This is a decent short ball, rising steeply at the face. Leask watches it on late enough as he brings out the hook and then manages to get a top edge on this that takes it far

Mohammed Shami to Leask, FOUR,drilled! Good length offcutter, lots of width outside off. He gets low, clears the front foot, and reaches out to have a slap at this. Past the bowler and then mid-off, on the up
Mohammed Shami to Leask, 1 run,length and into leg stump, clipped through midwicket

Mohammed Shami to MacLeod, no run,lbw shout as his front leg gets locked and his head falls over trying to flick this full one. It's dipping towards leg stump and away from the inside edge. Umpire says not out and he was right, that was going down
Mohammed Shami to MacLeod, 1 run,full toss at knee height on leg stump, hurriedly flicked through midwicket
Jadeja to MacLeod, 1 run,good length and gripping and turning away from middle stump, watchfully punched to long-on off the back foot

Jadeja to Leask, OUT,that is plumb. Good length, sliding on with the arm and tight at the stumps. He gets down for the sweep but isn't quick enough to sort out his swish across that. Cops that on the back thigh right in front of the stumps
Jadeja to Greaves, 1 run,full on leg stump, gets forward and flicks to midwicket's right
Jadeja to MacLeod, no run,short of a length and turning away outside off, under-edge on the cut to backward point
Jadeja to MacLeod, no run,good length at middle stump, defended on the front foot
Jadeja to MacLeod, 1 run,good length and tight at the stumps, waits deep in the crease and opens the face to pat this through cover
Bumrah to MacLeod, no run,dipping slower ball outside off, a touch too full for the yorker. He's beaten by the trajectory, can't come close to touching that
Bumrah to MacLeod, no run,yorker at middle stump, jams it out towards midwicket
Bumrah to MacLeod, 1 run,good length at off stump, opens the face and chops this down to third man
Bumrah to Greaves, no run,dipping yorker at off stump, met on the full and pushed down the pitch off the toe end
Bumrah to Greaves, no run,bouncer at a middle stump line, walks into the line of this and looks to hook. He's got no room to do that and this fizzes past his face
Bumrah to Greaves, no run,atempted yorker on off stump, met on the full and punched towards mid-off
Ashwin to MacLeod, 1 run,good length just outside off, gets on the back foot and punches to deep point's right

Ashwin to Greaves, no run,late review for lbw. By India. Good length ball, loopy and at middle stump. He looks for the reverse sweep and is struck in front of middle stump. But that looks like it's hit the left side of his ribs. It looks high. Yes it is. India lose the review, that was going over middle and leg
Ashwin to Greaves, no run,short of a length carrom ball at middle stump, backs away for the punch, gets an under edge down the pitch
Ashwin to Greaves, 1 wide,length and down leg side, left alone

Ashwin to Greaves, OUT,taken at long-off. Another carrom ball, but this one tossed up at a length outside off. Makes him step out, draws him in, then beats him in flight. His body's already at a stop as he stretches the hands to try and go long. Can't get anything on it and Pandya takes it some 15 yards inside
Ashwin to MacLeod, 1 run,full at middle stump, gets forward and flicks with the turn to long-on
Ashwin to Watt, no run,good length and sliding on from around the wicket, possibly the arm ball. Plays for the turn but that forward block has come off the inside half
Jadeja to MacLeod, 1 run,good length and sliding outside off, clears the front foot and chops to sweeper
Jadeja to Watt, no run,good length and at off stump, blocked on the front foot
Jadeja to Watt, no run,good length outside off, steps out and drives towards long-off, Jadeja stretches to the right and stops

Jadeja to Watt, FOUR,misfield at sweeper cover. Shami with a very ordinary chase to his left. Short ball and wide outside off, waits on that and punches it firmly in front of square. Shami sprints to the left and makes his ground but that effort to get down for it is in slow motion
Jadeja to Watt, no run,length at middle stump, pushed to midwicket off the back foot
Jadeja to Watt, 1 run,good length and sliding on outside off, steps out and looks to punch through cover. Thick inside edge
Ashwin to Watt, FOUR,full and wide outside off, steps out and is forced to have a slash because he's made too much room. Thick outside edge is fine enough of short third to run away
Ashwin to Watt, 1 run,good length at off stump, steps out and drives firmly to long-off's left. Jadeja sprints and keeps to a single
Ashwin to MacLeod, 1 run,good length at off stump, gets down and sweeps to deep backward square
Ashwin to Watt, no run,good length outside off, defended into the covers
Ashwin to Watt, 2 runs,top edge as he brings out the reverse sweep. This is length outside off, he's swished inside the line. Just clears short third

Ashwin to Watt, 2 wides,missed stumping. Pant has fluffed that. Ashwin sees Watt stepping out and pushes this full and very wide outside off. There's no chance for him to make contact on this. Pant is hurriedly grabbing to his left as this skid on low, but he doesn't gather
Ashwin to MacLeod, 1 run,full toss at off stump, gets down and sweeps to deep backward square

Mohammed Shami to MacLeod, OUT,rattles off stump via the pad. This is full and fast and straight. Just shy of 140kph. MacLeod plants the front leg down and looks to flick, but he's not quick enough in bringing the bat down

Mohammed Shami to Sharif, OUT,Kishan jogs to the stumps and clips the bails off. It's a leg-stump yorker that he's looked to flick. Sharif can't get bat on it and India are appealing for lbw as he runs down the pitch. He's sent back but can't turn around fast enough after his sprint and just gives up. Kishan is alive to the possibility, he runs in from midwicket and picks up one-handed before completing the run-out with Sharif not in the picture
Mohammed Shami to Evans, OUT,hits leg stump! What an absolute peach this is. The perfect yorker, landing on the crease at a leg stump line, and through Evan before he can get the bat down at it
Mohammed Shami to Wheal, 1 run,full and at the stumps, driven off the front foot to mid-off
Mohammed Shami to Watt, 1 run,full and just outside off, clears the front leg and drives through cover
Mohammed Shami to Wheal, no run,offcutter at a length outside off, looks for the square drive on the up, gets an inside edge that just misses the stumps
Bumrah to Watt, 1 run,dipping yorker at leg stump, exposes the stumps to try and drive, gets it off the thick inside edge
Bumrah to Wheal, no run,good length and angled into the corridor, hangs leg side of that and tries to slash behind square on the off side. Beaten
Bumrah to Wheal, 1 run,full and into middle and leg, looks to flick, gets a thick inside edge onto pad
Bumrah to Watt, OUT,tonks leg stump on the half-volley. Watt jumps into the off side, a long long way, in an attempt to try and scoop this over short fine. This is full and fast and too much for him
Watt to Rahul, 1 run,full on middle and leg, clipped to deep square leg
Watt to Sharma, no run,wide length ball, seems to kind of drift away in the air and make Rohit reach out for it. Pushed towards cover point
Watt to Sharma, 1 run,quick length ball drifting into middle and leg, clipped watchfully to the right of midwicket
Watt to Rahul, 1 run,round-armish from wide of the crease, fired full at the feet, clipped to deep square leg

Watt to Sharma, FOUR,some turn from a wide-ish line outside off, quite full. Rohit made room, and he ends up almost making too much room, but he reaches out and throws his hands at a sliced drive over point
Watt to Sharma, 1 run,fired into the pads, clipped to deep square leg
Wheal to Sharma, 1 run,length ball on the pads, clipped to the right of deep square leg

Wheal to Rahul, FOUR,terrific shot. Fullish, angling into the stumps, and he gets his front leg out of the way and lofts it over mid-on, just a full extension of the arms and met it with the straightest of bats

Wheal to Rahul, FOUR,length ball angling down leg. Not sure Rahul wanted to hit it there, but he ends up whipping it away to the vacant midwicket boundary. He was looking to whip that past short fine leg, and he ends up hitting it with the back of his bat, or the leading edge
Wheal to Rahul, 1 wide,full, angling down leg, past the attempted flick
Wheal to Rahul, no run,back of a length close to off stump, opens his bat face and stabs to short third
Wheal to Rahul, FOUR,shot. Full, angling in towards middle and leg, and he steps across and plays a super pick-up shot over short fine leg, to the left of the fielder
Wheal to Rahul, 1 run,full, close to off stump, too full to get any elevation, punched towards mid-off, who's on the edge of the circle
Evans to Rahul, FOUR,starts with a bad ball, full and offering width, and Rahul loves it there, just lifts it easily over the covers, great use of the hands to get under the ball and force it upwards
Evans to Rahul, SIX,another typical Rahul shot. Fullish, angling into leg stump, and a wristy pick-up shot sends it soaring into the stands to the right of deep square leg
Evans to Rahul, 1 run,length ball nipping in from outside off, presses forward and dabs gently into the point region
Evans to Sharma, no run,shortish, fairly wide outside off, reaches out for a crouched cut but can't connect
Evans to Sharma, FOUR,full, angling into middle stump, and that's superb timing. Gets his front leg out of the way and drives inside-out over the gap between mid-off and extra-cover

Evans to Sharma, 1 run,down the track, making room. Sees him coming and bowls a slower ball outside off, shortening his length a bit. Wants to force it through the covers, but doesn't time it at all, ends up squeezing it into the mid-on region instead

Sharif to Sharma, SIX,and Rohit welcomes him with a mighty hit into the stands at deep midwicket. Wants to bowl a length offcutter, but ends up pushing it a touch too full. Clears his front leg and absolutely monsters it over midwicket. It's a slog, but it's Rohit Sharma so it looks nice

Sharif to Sharma, no run,back of a length, offcutter coming in from just outside off. Doesn't get the room he wants to punch into the covers, ends up hitting it one-handed, without much power, in front of extra-cover
Sharif to Sharma, FOUR,a touch full again, and this time he offers width too, leans back to make a bit of room for his arms, and drives with an open face over cover point
Sharif to Sharma, no run,length ball on off stump, makes some room for a square slap, and point dives to his left to stop it

Sharif to Sharma, FOUR,once again a touch too full, and it's on the pads too. Rohit gets his front leg out of the way, and flicks it up and over midwicket. Too easy. One bounce and over the rope. That brings up India's fifty
Sharif to Sharma, no run,short, wide, but bouncing too much for Rohit to be able to connect with the uppercut

Wheal to Rahul, 2 runs,shortish, angling in to finish close to off stump. Skiddy bounce, and Rahul is cramped on the pull. Ends up hitting the high part of his bat but clearing the circle, to the left of mid-on. Good chase back from Coetzer to stop it from running away for four
Wheal to Rahul, FOUR,half-volley outside off stump, and Rahul isn't going to miss out. Drives, and finds the gap to the left of the diving cover fielder

Wheal to Rahul, SIX,short ball, gets up to just over chest height around off stump. Has to fetch the pull from outside the line of his body, and he hits it in the air, and the man at deep square leg is a few yards in. Leaps up and reaches desperately over his head with his left arm, but he can't quite pluck it out of the air
Wheal to Rahul, 1 run,back of a length, angling into off stump, clipped to deep midwicket
Wheal to Sharma, FOUR,short outside off, doesn't quite get hold of the pull, but mid-on is inside the circle. Clears him comfortably, and the ball runs away for four more

Wheal to Sharma, OUT,big appeal, and it's given! That came out of nowhere! Yorker homing in towards the stumps, and Rohit, already deep in his crease with his back foot, probably looking for something he can hit over the leg side, is caught unawares, and is struck on the full on the right foot. Right in front of off stump. Rohit doesn't bother reviewing, it just looked too plumb
Watt to Rahul, FOUR,full toss and drifting away outside off, reaches out and drives this wide of mid-off
Watt to Rahul, no run,full and just outside off, drilled firmly to mid-off's right

Watt to Rahul, SIX,bowled from about two yards behind the popping crease but to no avail. This is full and at middle stump, gets down on one knee and swings this over the long leg boundary with a sweep
Watt to Rahul, 1 run,full at middle stump, jammed down towards long-on and that is fifty for Rahul
Watt to Kohli, 1 run,good length and at off stump, gets forward and flicks to mid-on's right

Watt to Rahul, OUT,he's found long-on! This looked like it had gone further than it did. Tossed up again and gets a lot of dip on this. At leg stump. Rahul stretches his arms and looks to finish the game by launching this over the fielder. It comes off the inside part of the toe end and is taken easily
Greaves to Kohli, 1 run,short and at leg stump, looks to muscle this pull, mistimes it off the inside half to deep square
Greaves to Yadav, no run,short of a length and skidding on outside off, rising as well, to beat his cut
Greaves to Yadav, SIX,launched over the bowler and that is that. This is full and at middle stump, he gets the front leg out of the way and offers the full face as he lofts this on the half-volley
Scholtz to Guptill, 1 run,ambles across past the umpire to bowl from round the wicket, tossed up and nudged leg side
Scholtz to Mitchell, 1 run,flighted, 86kph/53mph and Mitchell leans out to punch down the ground
Scholtz to Guptill, no run,tossed up, slightly quicker on off stump, tapped back
Scholtz to Guptill, SIX,smoked! Guptill still in the groove, it seems. Head fixed on the pitch of the ball, and it goes up-up-and-away, clean as a whistle over the sight screen
Scholtz to Guptill, no run,pushed through, defended on the front foot
Scholtz to Guptill, 1 run,fires this in fast and flat, Guptill is across and jabs it into a gap in the covers
Trumpelmann to Guptill, no run,over the wicket, slightly back of a length and shaping a fraction in the channel, Guptill leaves it alone
Trumpelmann to Guptill, no run,ooh, beauty in the channel, 123kph/76mph, comes back a fraction but still Guptill manages to play just inside the line
Trumpelmann to Guptill, FOUR,no-nonsense biffing! Slightly overpitched and Guptill pounces, ramming a drive through mid-off and away
Trumpelmann to Guptill, no run,shorter, maybe a cutter, this is defended with a straight bat
Trumpelmann to Guptill, no run,straighter line and Guptill misses out looking to whip off his pads
Trumpelmann to Guptill, no run,whoops, stays low... we've seen this at Sharjah, almost a shooter as Guptill hangs back, breaks away off the pitch and through to the keeper
Wiese to Mitchell, 3 runs,tad short in the channel and Mitchell pings his second ball through point, won't quite run all the way
Wiese to Guptill, 1 run,hard length, 122kph/76mph, Guptill punches firmly wide of mid-off for a single
Wiese to Mitchell, 1 run,short of a length, 128kph and Mitchell drops it short into the off side
Wiese to Guptill, 1 run,comes across and taps into the covers

Wiese to Mitchell, 1 run,back of a length and Mitchell pulls himself up to rap a back-foot drive, Wiese gets a hand on it... and Guptill would have been stranded if the deflection had gone on to the stumps!
Wiese to Guptill, 1 run,shortish again, no room to free the arms, nudged leg side for one
Smit to Guptill, no run,back of a length, dabbed down into the pitch, they won't sneak one this time
Smit to Guptill, 2 runs,short at 124kph/77mph, Guptill sets himself and hammers a pull in front of deep square leg, picks up a couple

Smit to Guptill, 1 run,fantastic effort from Williams in the covers! Gets one hand to the ball, which was flying off the meat of Guptill's bat... goes down as a drop, I suppose, but he did brilliantly to get near it (and saved a boundary, too)
Smit to Mitchell, FOUR,chipped down the ground, Mitchell is out of his crease and just plays up and over with a high front elbow, gets it past mid-on
Smit to Mitchell, no run,shortish outside off, lashed straight to backward point
Smit to Mitchell, 2 runs,worked into a gap on the leg side, and they come haring back for two

Wiese to Guptill, OUT,drilled to mid-off, Guppy's gone! Pitched up and he was looking to go up over the off side, but the ball skids on and hits low on the bat, he can't get the elevation and Trumpelmann stoops to claim a simple catch. Namibia bag themselves the bug fush
Wiese to Williamson, no run,short of a length, defended softly from the crease
Wiese to Williamson, 1 run,pitched up, 129kph/80mph and Williamson steers one in front of extra cover
Wiese to Mitchell, 1 run,length ball on off, 132kph and punched down the ground
Wiese to Williamson, no run,offcutter and this zips back past the edge, Williamson just looking to defend but he's beaten

Wiese to Williamson, FOUR,touch wide and guided expertly through backward point! Williamson threads his first boundary, hanging back and although the bounce is low, he just wants to use the pace and steer it through the infield
Trumpelmann to Mitchell, no run,over the wicket, prodded into the off side
Trumpelmann to Mitchell, no run,hammers a length and Mitchell can only drop this just off the cut strip again
Trumpelmann to Mitchell, 1 run,fullish and this is clipped off the pads
Trumpelmann to Williamson, 1 run,similar line, swinging a fraction but easy enough for Williamson to punch in front of deep midwicket
Trumpelmann to Mitchell, FOUR,too straight and this is whipped for four, bit of a gimme for Mitchell, with no one behind square on the leg side
Trumpelmann to Mitchell, 1 run,length, 127kph/78mph and Mitchell tips and runs towards mid-off
Scholtz to Mitchell, no run,tossed up and he reverses straight to backward point

Scholtz to Mitchell, OUT,skied into the off side! Scholtz from the blue, Namibia have a second! Mitchell skips down but gets nowhere near the pitch and sends a yawning leading edge over cover, where it is <del>smartly</del> just about taken by van Lingen running in
Scholtz to Williamson, 1 run,flighted, some spin on middle and leg, jabbed down to long-on
Scholtz to Conway, 1 run,over the wicket to the left-hander, tucked off the pads and midwicket can't reel it in
Scholtz to Williamson, 1 run,Williamson goes back and dabs one towards backward point
Scholtz to Conway, no run,fired in full, 97kph/60mph, comes off the toe of the bat towards mid-on
Loftie-Eaton to Williamson, 1 run,fizzed down on middle, Williamson gets forward and clips to long-on
Loftie-Eaton to Conway, 1 run,tossed up, 83kph/52mph and Conway flicks with the spin through midwicket
Loftie-Eaton to Williamson, 1 run,floated full on the stumps, Williamson nudges into a gap at midwicket... he was looking for two but wisely rethinks
Loftie-Eaton to Conway, 2 runs,tossed up full and Conway gets across, belts it straight for a couple as Smit comes across at long-off
Loftie-Eaton to Conway, FOUR,looped up on off and this one goes, battered straight back past the bowler for four! Smit no chance of getting across this time
Loftie-Eaton to Conway, no run,pushed through wide of off and chopped to the man at extra cover
Scholtz to Williamson, no run,round the wicket and angled in, Williamson taps gently to leg
Scholtz to Williamson, 1 run,lobbed up and dinked through mid-off for a single
Scholtz to Conway, 1 leg bye,over the wicket, tossed up and spinning leg side, tucked off the pads
Scholtz to Williamson, no run,nicely flighted, 89kph/55mph and dipping on middle and leg, Williamson happy to keep those out
Scholtz to Williamson, 1 run,pushed in on the stumps, patted back down the ground
Scholtz to Conway, 1 run,quicker and swept off the front pad, stopped by the scrambling Trumpelmann on the 45
Erasmus to Conway, 1 run,round the wicket, looped up and worked off the pads
Erasmus to Williamson, no run,skip and a jump, pushed through at 90kph on off, Williamson jabs it back
Erasmus to Williamson, 1 run,flighted, stays a touch low, clipped off the back foot down to long-on
Erasmus to Conway, 1 run,gets away with a full toss, Conway is across and sweeps hard for a single to deep square leg
Erasmus to Williamson, no run,flat on the stumps, punched back
Erasmus to Williamson, no run,floated up outside off, driven straight to cover - tidy from Namibia's captain
Loftie-Eaton to Conway, 1 run,fuller on the stumps, swept behind square leg

Loftie-Eaton to Williamson, 1 run,use of feet to drill it straight towards the bowler. Loftie-Eaton fails to get a hand on it as the ball crashes into the stumps at his end. Conway was way out. A single off the deflection
Loftie-Eaton to Conway, 1 run,another sweep towards deep square leg
Loftie-Eaton to Williamson, 2 runs,length ball on the stumps, punched towards long-on and they rush back for the second
Loftie-Eaton to Williamson, SIX,Williamson unleashes the slog sweep. A touch too full, just outside off. Williamson goes down and sends it over deep midwicket. That's the shorter side too

Loftie-Eaton to Williamson, FOUR,skips out of the crease this time and smashes it down the ground. The wicketkeeper shouts catch, the bowler stretched his right hand but cannot latch onto it. Might have got a finger on it. The umpire shows great reflexes to move away from the line of the ball
Birkenstock to Conway, no run,length ball angling across. goes for the cut but misses as the ball stays low
Birkenstock to Conway, 1 run,fuller around off, a mistimed drive down the ground
Birkenstock to Williamson, no run,length ball at the stumps, pushed back but the bowler does well to dive and stop it in his follow-through
Birkenstock to Williamson, 1 run,use of feet but still not to the pitch of the ball. He is cramped as well. Just pushes it towards long-on in the end
Birkenstock to Conway, 1 run,length outside off, cuts it towards point. Straight towards the fielder but takes the single
Birkenstock to Williamson, 1 run,a length ball outside off, swipes it towards deep midwicket

Erasmus to Williamson, OUT,played on! Erasmus gets his opposite number. It was fuller but a touch too outside off, Williamson once again eyed that shorter boundary with the slog sweep but this time, the ball hit the inner half of the bat before clattering into the stumps
Erasmus to Phillips, no run,fuller and wider. Almost in the blockhole. Phillips fails to get his bat on it
Erasmus to Phillips, no run,fired in flatter outside off. Left alone by the batter
Erasmus to Phillips, no run,fuller outside off, pushed towards extra cover
Erasmus to Phillips, no run,length outside off, some swerve and turn. Phillips cannot connect the attempted cut
Erasmus to Phillips, 1 run,a low full toss outside off, driven towards long-off. An excellent over from Erasmus, just a single and Williamson's wicket from it
Birkenstock to Phillips, 1 run,length ball angling in. Moves across and helps it towards deep square leg

Birkenstock to Conway, 1 run,length ball, Conway takes a couple of steps down the ground and nudges it back towards the bowler, who fails to get a hand on it and the ball dislodges the bails at the other end and stops nearby. Conway manages to complete the single though
Birkenstock to Phillips, 1 run,tucked towards midwicket for one
Birkenstock to Conway, no run,fuller and wider outside off, throws his bat at it but fails to connect
Birkenstock to Conway, 1 run,length ball at the stumps, punched down the ground. Conway was looking for a second but will have to sett;e for one only

Birkenstock to Phillips, 1 run, OUT,a risky call for a second and we go upstairs. A length ball on the stumps, flicked towards midwicket. This time they are going for the second. The fielder charges in, fires in the throw to the bowler who collects and breaks the stumps. Conway is found short by third umpire
Erasmus to Neesham, no run,length ball at the stumps, defended
Erasmus to Neesham, no run,length outside off, blocked again
Erasmus to Neesham, 1 run,fuller on the pads, flicked in front of square leg
Erasmus to Phillips, 1 run,flatter, a touch shorter around off. Punched towards midwicket
Erasmus to Neesham, no run,fuller around off, flatter and quicker. Neesham was stuck on the back foot. Pushes at it and gets beaten
Erasmus to Neesham, 1 wide,fuller but down the leg side. Neesham leaves it alone
Erasmus to Neesham, 1 run,length ball on the stumps, pushed towards midwicket. Erasmus chases it himself to keep it to one
Wiese to Neesham, 1 run,length ball outside off, dabbed behind point for one
Wiese to Phillips, 1 run,length ball at the stumps, punched towards long-on
Wiese to Neesham, no run,fuller outside off, steered towards short third man but no run
Wiese to Neesham, no run,a slower one, keeps a touch low as well after landing around the good length spot. Neesham fails to get anything on it
Wiese to Neesham, 1 run,a touch fuller on the pads, flicked towards deep-backward square leg

Wiese to Phillips, 2 runs,banged into the pitch once again but Phillips nails a pull towards deep square leg. The fielder charges in and puts in the slide to his right to flick it inside. For a moment it looked like the ball will still roll on to the boundary line but he recovered quickly and picked it up just inside
Erasmus to Neesham, 1 run,down the ground in an attempt to go big but fails to middle. Only a single to long-on
Erasmus to Phillips, SIX,a full toss from Erasmus and and Phillips doesn't miss out. Sends it over deep midwicket into the vacant stands
Erasmus to Phillips, 1 run,flatter at the stumps this time, punched towards long-on
Erasmus to Neesham, 2 runs,goes round-arm this time. Fuller outside off, Neesham launches it towards deep extra cover, long-off puts in the chase, picks it up and flicks it inside
Erasmus to Neesham, 2 runs,ever more round-armish from Erasmus. Flicked towards midwicket and that's another brace
Erasmus to Neesham, 2 runs,length ball on the stumps, flicked towards midwicket for the third two of the over. Fourteen in all from the over
Wiese to Phillips, 2 runs,length ball around off, a mistimed pull into the ground towards midwicket. A bit of a fumble there means an easy two
Wiese to Phillips, 2 runs,backs away but Wiese follows him and bowls fuller. Digs it out towards midwicket for two more

Wiese to Phillips, SIX,a slower one, but it's fuller outside off and Phillips carves it over deep extra cover. The fielder signals a six but the umpires want to check upstairs. Replays show it hit the boundary skirting on the full
Wiese to Phillips, 1 run,short of length outside off, pace-on delivery. Worked towards deep midwicket
Wiese to Neesham, SIX,smoked over long-on. Fuller outside off and Neesham joins the party. Goes down and drags it for a maximum
Wiese to Neesham, FOUR,squeezed between short third man and backward point. Was fuller and wider from Wiese but Neesham opens the face of the bat to pocket four more. That makes it 21 from the over
Trumpelmann to Phillips, FOUR,length ball around off, dragged across and beats the man sprinting to his left from deep square leg
Trumpelmann to Phillips, SIX,muscled! Short of length, into the pitch. Phillips stands back and pulls it in front of square leg
Trumpelmann to Phillips, 1 run,a length ball around off, flat-bats it towards long-on. Didn't get the timing right on this
Trumpelmann to Neesham, no run,short of length outside off, Neesham goes for the pull but the ball sneaks underneath the bat
Trumpelmann to Neesham, 2 runs,another short of a length delivery. Pulled towards deep square leg and Neesham sprints back for the second
Trumpelmann to Neesham, 1 run,a slower one, into the pitch. Dragged towards deep-backward square leg
Smit to Neesham, no run,short of length, way outside off, Neesham goes for the pull but ends up playing over it
Smit to Neesham, SIX,150 is up for New Zealand. Goes for the bouncer but it sits up for Neesham who waits before pulling it over deep square leg, the shorter side
Smit to Neesham, 2 runs,length, well outside off. Dragged towards deep midwicket. Erasmus fumbles there and allows the second run
Smit to Neesham, 1 wide,that's been called a wide. Tight call. Fuller, wider outside off. Neesham leaves it alone as the ball lands on the blue marker
Smit to Neesham, 1 wide,length ball outside off, Neesham goes for the pull but ends up hitting over it. But this too has been given wide, another close call but think the umpire has got it right

Smit to Neesham, 1 run,a brilliant yorker, Neesham was standing at the off stump and was looking to work it on the leg side but gets an inside edge into the right shoe and the ball rolls towards the off side
Smit to Phillips, 2 runs,another attempted yorker, but just misses his mark there. Flicked towards deep midwicket

Smit to Phillips, 2 wides,banged it into the pitch. Phillips changes his grip pretty early and was standing like a left-hander well before the ball arrived. Went for the pull but fails to connect as it's too high, which also means it's a wide. They run a single to the keeper
Smit to Neesham, 1 wide,another wide, that's fourth of the over I think. Fuller but way, way outside off. The easiest call of the over
Smit to Neesham, 2 runs,fuller outside off, throws his bat at it and gets it towards deep point. Phillips is charging back for the second. The keeper fumbles and he makes it easily
Southee to Baard, no run,fullish around off stump, tight lines at 132kph/82mph and Baard defends it back to the bowler
Southee to Baard, 1 run,full length and swinging a touch for Southee, watches it well and punches one back fine of mid-on
Southee to van Lingen, no run,dug in back of a length and angling across the left-hander, but van Lingen misses out
Southee to van Lingen, 1 run,pitched up and curling back, 134kph/83mph and van Lingen steps into a compact drive, Williamson scurrying after it in the covers
Southee to Baard, no run,scuds into the pads, Southee raises his red-wrist-banded left arm in appeal... heading down leg

Southee to Baard, FOUR,edged for four! Thick connection as he pushed forward and it went quickly to Conway's right... the slip had been removed but was standing wide anyway, and I don't think would have got there
Boult to van Lingen, 1 run,over the wicket, touch short of a length and it's worked away through square leg
Boult to Baard, 1 wide,angled across the right-hander - but Boult has pushed that too wide
Boult to Baard, no run,tighter line, 136kph/84mph and Baard prods it down square
Boult to Baard, no run,bangs in a bumper, ducked
Boult to Baard, 1 run,back of a length and this time he gets a mishit pull away
Boult to van Lingen, 2 runs,swung leg side and it needs two NZ fielders to hunt the the ball down in partnership
Boult to van Lingen, no run,short of a length, doesn't get up and van Lingen takes a blow on the body looking to pull
Milne to Baard, 2 runs,driven off a length, uppish but safely fine of mid-on for a couple
Milne to Baard, 1 run,skidding on in the channel, goes back and chops down on it for one... direct hit from Neesham would have had van Lingen in trouble
Milne to van Lingen, no run,back of a length, 140kph/87mph on off, steered down towards cover point
Milne to van Lingen, no run,bangs a length, maybe a cutter from Milne, down at 129kph, tapped to backward point
Milne to van Lingen, 1 run,short ball, slugged through midwicket but Phillips hares in to keep them to one
Milne to Baard, no run,punched back to the bowler at the top of the bounce
Southee to van Lingen, 1 run,pitched up and punched through the off side, extra cover comes across
Southee to Baard, no run,shortish, zips through at hip height, just over leg stump as Baard swipes and misses
Southee to Baard, 1 run,dug in, swung away on the pull behind square, Southee has cover out there
Southee to van Lingen, no run,short of a length, a cross-batted swipe sees the ball cannon into the turf just past leg stump
Southee to van Lingen, no run,round the wicket, 134kph/83mph in the channel and it just holds its line, beats a forward push
Southee to van Lingen, no run,over the wicket again, full on off and van Lingen picks out cover with a correct-looking drive
Boult to Baard, 1 run,full length and driven crisply, looks to be beating mid-off... only for Williamson so swoop into view like a greased seal and make a one-handed stop
Boult to van Lingen, no run,pitched up and driven to the edge of the ring... good effort to catch out Baard backing up from Mitchell
Boult to van Lingen, 1 run,dug in and swatted leg side
Boult to Baard, FOUR,slugged over midwicket! Lovely connection, stepping out to wrist a length ball elegantly up and away
Boult to Baard, no run,dug in, Baard ducks the bumper
Boult to Baard, 1 run,fired in on the stumps, tucked leg side for one more
Milne to Baard, no run,shortish and sliding on, can't get it away
Milne to Baard, 1 leg bye,into the body, deflected into a gap as he looks to pull
Milne to van Lingen, FOUR,bullied straight back down the ground! Pace on just back of a length and van Lingen sets himself up to slap hard through mid-off for four
Milne to van Lingen, no run,knuckle ball, down at 122kph from Milne, right off the toe of the bat into the covers
Milne to van Lingen, SIX,picks the slower ball and hoists it down the ground! Another knuckler into the pitch but he waits on this one, cracks it high over long-on for Namibia's first six
Milne to van Lingen, 1 run,swung to deep backward square on the pull
Santner to van Lingen, no run,over the wicket, full down the leg side... maybe some pad on it
Santner to van Lingen, 1 run,skips out and drills one to long-off
Santner to Baard, 3 runs,gets the sweep away towards fine leg, Daryl Mitchell racing around to prevent four
Santner to van Lingen, no run,pushed through on off stump, 98kph/61mph, van Lingen prods into the covers
Santner to van Lingen, FOUR,edged past short fine leg, this will run away to the fence! Fired in as van Lingen looked to make room, ended up squeezing out a fortunate boundary
Santner to van Lingen, 1 leg bye,on the pads and nurdled leg side
Neesham to van Lingen, 2 runs,back of a length and angling across, sliced wide of third, where Sodhi makes a tumbling stop

Neesham to van Lingen, OUT,bowled him, neck and crop! Neesham rascals one straight through van Lingen as he swipes across the line... touch short, scrambled seam and it skids on fiendishly to clatter middle and leg. The batter collapses to his haunches and inspects the damage. NZ needed that
Neesham to Erasmus, 1 run,straight line, tucked off the pads
Neesham to Baard, 1 run,fuller, 135kph/84mph and worked through midwicket
Neesham to Erasmus, 1 run,short of a length outside off and Erasmus drops back, plays a late cut for one
Neesham to Baard, 1 run,fullish, angling in on the stumps, Baard works it into a gap but Sodhi is up quickly from fine leg and prevents a second

Santner to Baard, OUT,cleaned him up! Some turn for Santner from the perfect length and Baard is caught playing across the line. Smacks into the top of middle and leg, Namibia's other opener hears the death rattle. Two in six balls for New Zealand
Santner to Green, no run,pushed through and hits the pads from over the wicket, doing too much
Santner to Green, 1 run,darted outside off, 91kph and jabbed square for Green's first run
Santner to Erasmus, 1 run,bit of loop on this, still quick at 95kph/59mph and Erasmus punches to long-on
Santner to Green, no run,pushed through from over the wicket, tapped back
Santner to Green, 1 run,tossed up outside off, leans into a cover drive to the sweeper
Sodhi to Green, 1 run,flighted legbreak from over the wicket, tucked calmly through midwicket

Sodhi to Erasmus, OUT,nicks a low leggie to the keeper! Paul Wilson is quick to raise the finger as Erasmus goes back and pokes at one just leaving him in the channel. Sodhi pops up with yet another wicket, the NZ net is tightening
Sodhi to Wiese, no run,a length ball around off, looked like a googly. Defended from the crease
Sodhi to Wiese, no run,length ball on the pads, goes for the flick but misses and is hit on the pads. An appeal for lbw but this was going down
Sodhi to Wiese, no run,length ball around middle and off, punched towards extra cover
Sodhi to Wiese, 1 run,dragged short, it got stuck in Sodhi's hand but Wiese fails to take advantage of it. Mistimes the pull towards deep-backward square leg
Santner to Wiese, 1 run,length ball around off, punched towards sweeper cover
Santner to Green, 1 run,length ball around off, pushes it towards cover-point

Santner to Wiese, FOUR,fuller around off, Wiese looks to smash it towards long-off but is beaten as the ball turns big with a puff of dust coming off. The umpire thinks there was an outside edge as the ball went past the keeper
Santner to Wiese, no run,fuller around off, pushed towards covers
Santner to Wiese, no run,length outside off, finds the point fielder with the cut
Santner to Wiese, 1 run,length ball outside off, punched towards sweeper cover

Sodhi to Wiese, no run,down the track and smashes right back towards the bowler, at head height. Sodhi tried to catch it but it doesn't stick. He is on the ground, rubbing his head. The physio rushes out. I guess it burst through his hands and hit his forehead. Taking on some fluids, looks like he's smiling. Southee having a longish chat and making sure he's alright, looks like he's finishing his over
Sodhi to Wiese, 1 wide,fuller but down the leg side. Called a wide
Sodhi to Wiese, 1 run,front of the hand. A length ball outside off, cuts it towards sweeper cover
Sodhi to Green, no run,length ball on the pads, pushed on the leg side. Sodhi fields himself
Sodhi to Green, no run,tossed up outside off, cuts it towards the cover fielder
Sodhi to Green, 2 runs,length outside off, cuts it through covers and comes back for the second
Sodhi to Green, 1 run,flighted around off, digs it out towards long-off
Santner to Green, no run,length around off, chops the cut into the ground and towards the bowler
Santner to Green, 1 run,fuller on the stumps, pushed towards mid-on. Short midwicket makes a sliding stop
Santner to Wiese, 1 run,fuller outside off, Wiese hits it towards sweeper cover with a high backlift
Santner to Green, no run,flatter and quicker around off, mistimes the punch towards short midwicket
Santner to Green, no run,length outside off, bunted towards extra cover
Santner to Green, no run,length ball around off and spinning in, goes back and pushes it towards short midwicket
Sodhi to Wiese, 1 wide,fuller but way outside off, ignored
Sodhi to Wiese, SIX,Wiese goes big! Fuller length around off, Wiese comes down the track and launches it way over long-off - 81 metres
Sodhi to Wiese, no run,bowled slower, fuller on the leg stump. Goes for the flick but misses and is hit on the pad
Sodhi to Wiese, no run,Sodhi shortens his length as Wiese was looking to come down the track. Looks to punch it through covers but mistimes it towards the bowler
Sodhi to Wiese, 1 run,length ball on the stumps, pulls it towards deep square leg
Sodhi to Green, SIX,into the stands. Walks towards the off side, gets low and slog sweeps it with the turn over deep midwicket. This one is 84 metres
Sodhi to Green, 1 run,flatter and angling across the left-hander, who flat-bats it towards long-on
Southee to Green, no run,length ball outside off, goes for the pull but it keeps low and goes under the bat
Southee to Green, 1 run,length ball outside off, stays back and pushes at it. Gets a thick outside edge towards third man

Southee to Wiese, OUT,celebrappeal from Southee. And the finger goes up as well. A length ball around off that nipped back in to rap Wiese on the pads. He was stuck on the crease and failed to get his bat down in time. He thinks of reviewing it but decides against it in the end

Southee to Smit, no run,an appeal for lbw. Denied but Williamson is keen for the review. Think it's going down. A length ball on the stumps and once again nipping back. Oh, there's an inside edge as well
Southee to Smit, no run,hit in the box, down on the knees. A length ball on the stumps, Smit went for the pull but missed
Southee to Smit, no run,length ball outside off, punched towards extra cover
Milne to Green, 1 run,length ball outside off, punched towards deep backward point
Milne to Smit, no run,beats the inside edge. A length ball outside off, Smit pushes away from the body and is beaten
Milne to Smit, no run,length ball outside off, stays leg side of the ball and pushes it towards backward point. Guptill dives to his right to make a two-handed stop
Milne to Smit, no run,short of legnth, angling, rising towards the batters, who arches back and somehow manages to dab it towards backward point
Milne to Smit, FOUR,fuller, in the slot and Smit, who is homed on middle and leg, crunches it over covers for four
Milne to Smit, 1 leg bye,length ball on the pads, misses the flick but gets a leg bye to square leg
Boult to Smit, 2 runs,length ball angling across, cuts it towards deep backward point where the fielder fumbles and allows the second run
Boult to Smit, 1 run,fuller outside off, almost in the blockhole. Digs it out towards sweeper cover
Boult to Green, no run,moves across, gets down and looks to scoop it over. No connection
Boult to Green, no run,a bouncer from Boult. Just outside off. Green goes for the pull but is late on it. Called one for the over
Boult to Green, no run,down the pitch but Boult showing his class here. Not only he follows him but also yorks him. Once again no willow on the leather
Boult to Green, 1 run,fuller on the stumps, flicked in front of square leg
Southee to Green, 1 run,length ball around off, pulls it down towards deep midwicket
Southee to Smit, no run,a length ball around off, swings across but misses
Southee to Smit, 1 run,length ball around off, pushes it towards covers
Southee to Green, FOUR,a slower one, length around off. Green stays back and smashes it down the ground. Beats long-on. 100 up as well
Southee to Green, OUT,fails to repeat it. Another length ball, Green once again goes for the pull but this time he hits it in the direction of long-on, where Boult comes in and takes a tumbling catch
Southee to Smit, no run,length ball in the channel, backs away and looks to hit it through the off side. Misses
Boult to Loftie-Eaton, 1 wide,fuller but down the leg side. Called a wide
Boult to Loftie-Eaton, no run,an excellent yorker. Loftie-Eaton gets his bat down in time

Boult to Loftie-Eaton, OUT,a dolly by Guptill's standards. A slower one, banged into the pitch, Loftie-Eaton backs away and forehands it towards mid-off. Guptill moves back and sideways to take it over his right shoulder
Boult to Smit, 1 run,fuller around off, hits it towards long-off
Boult to Williams, no run,A wide yorker. Williams cannot get his bat on it
Boult to Williams, 1 wide,fuller length but way outside off. Williams cannot connect here. On the bounce to the keeper who does well to get his body behind it. Ah, there was a big outside edge on it
Boult to Williams, OUT,fuller outside off, goes back and throws his bat at it, looking to go leg side. But all he gets is a thick outside edge and Phillips pouches it at backward point
Boult to Trumpelmann, 1 run,fuller outside off, squeezes it out towards backward point
Milne to Trumpelmann, no run,length ball outside off, 117kph. Looks to punch at it but misses
Milne to Trumpelmann, FOUR,fuller outside off, smashed over mid-off. Boult puts in the jump but it just evades his outstretched right hand
Milne to Trumpelmann, 1 run,fuller around off, looks to go downtown once again, mistimes it towards long-on
Milne to Smit, no run,a slower ball banged into the pitch. Smit was too early into the pull and is beaten
Milne to Smit, no run,a yorker, just outside off. Squeezes it out towards backward point
Milne to Smit, no run,another slower bouncer, another swing and a miss
